2297
2298static bool checkAvailabilityAttr(Sema &S, SourceRange Range,
2299 IdentifierInfo *Platform,
2300 VersionTuple Introduced,
2301 VersionTuple Deprecated,
2302 VersionTuple Obsoleted) {
2303 StringRef PlatformName
2304 = AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(Platform->getName());
2305 if (PlatformName.empty())
2306 PlatformName = Platform->getName();
2307
2308 // Ensure that Introduced <= Deprecated <= Obsoleted (although not all
2309 // of these steps are needed).
2310 if (!Introduced.empty() && !Deprecated.empty() &&
2311 !(Introduced <= Deprecated)) {
2312 S.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_availability_version_ordering)
2313 << 1 << PlatformName << Deprecated.getAsString()
2314 << 0 << Introduced.getAsString();
2315 return true;
2316 }
2317
2318 if (!Introduced.empty() && !Obsoleted.empty() &&
2319 !(Introduced <= Obsoleted)) {
2320 S.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_availability_version_ordering)
2321 << 2 << PlatformName << Obsoleted.getAsString()
2322 << 0 << Introduced.getAsString();
2323 return true;
2324 }
2325
2326 if (!Deprecated.empty() && !Obsoleted.empty() &&
2327 !(Deprecated <= Obsoleted)) {
2328 S.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_availability_version_ordering)
2329 << 2 << PlatformName << Obsoleted.getAsString()
2330 << 1 << Deprecated.getAsString();
2331 return true;
2332 }
2333
2334 return false;
2335}
2336
2337/// Check whether the two versions match.
2338///
2339/// If either version tuple is empty, then they are assumed to match. If
2340/// \p BeforeIsOkay is true, then \p X can be less than or equal to \p Y.
2341static bool versionsMatch(const VersionTuple &X, const VersionTuple &Y,
2342 bool BeforeIsOkay) {
2343 if (X.empty() || Y.empty())
2344 return true;
2345
2346 if (X == Y)
2347 return true;
2348
2349 if (BeforeIsOkay && X < Y)
2350 return true;
2351
2352 return false;
2353}
2354
2355AvailabilityAttr *Sema::mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2356 NamedDecl *D, SourceRange Range, IdentifierInfo *Platform, bool Implicit,
2357 VersionTuple Introduced, VersionTuple Deprecated, VersionTuple Obsoleted,
2358 bool IsUnavailable, StringRef Message, bool IsStrict, StringRef Replacement,
2359 AvailabilityMergeKind AMK, int Priority, unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
2360 VersionTuple MergedIntroduced = Introduced;
2361 VersionTuple MergedDeprecated = Deprecated;
2362 VersionTuple MergedObsoleted = Obsoleted;
2363 bool FoundAny = false;
2364 bool OverrideOrImpl = false;
2365 switch (AMK) {
2366 case AMK_None:
2367 case AMK_Redeclaration:
2368 OverrideOrImpl = false;
2369 break;
2370
2371 case AMK_Override:
2372 case AMK_ProtocolImplementation:
2373 OverrideOrImpl = true;
2374 break;
2375 }
2376
2377 if (D->hasAttrs()) {
2378 AttrVec &Attrs = D->getAttrs();
2379 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Attrs.size(); i != e;) {
2380 const auto *OldAA = dyn_cast<AvailabilityAttr>(Attrs[i]);
2381 if (!OldAA) {
2382 ++i;
2383 continue;
2384 }
2385
2386 IdentifierInfo *OldPlatform = OldAA->getPlatform();
2387 if (OldPlatform != Platform) {
2388 ++i;
2389 continue;
2390 }
2391
2392 // If there is an existing availability attribute for this platform that
2393 // has a lower priority use the existing one and discard the new
2394 // attribute.
2395 if (OldAA->getPriority() < Priority)
2396 return nullptr;
2397
2398 // If there is an existing attribute for this platform that has a higher
2399 // priority than the new attribute then erase the old one and continue
2400 // processing the attributes.
2401 if (OldAA->getPriority() > Priority) {
2402 Attrs.erase(Attrs.begin() + i);
2403 --e;
2404 continue;
2405 }
2406
2407 FoundAny = true;
2408 VersionTuple OldIntroduced = OldAA->getIntroduced();
2409 VersionTuple OldDeprecated = OldAA->getDeprecated();
2410 VersionTuple OldObsoleted = OldAA->getObsoleted();
2411 bool OldIsUnavailable = OldAA->getUnavailable();
2412
2413 if (!versionsMatch(OldIntroduced, Introduced, OverrideOrImpl) ||
2414 !versionsMatch(Deprecated, OldDeprecated, OverrideOrImpl) ||
2415 !versionsMatch(Obsoleted, OldObsoleted, OverrideOrImpl) ||
2416 !(OldIsUnavailable == IsUnavailable ||
2417 (OverrideOrImpl && !OldIsUnavailable && IsUnavailable))) {
2418 if (OverrideOrImpl) {
2419 int Which = -1;
2420 VersionTuple FirstVersion;
2421 VersionTuple SecondVersion;
2422 if (!versionsMatch(OldIntroduced, Introduced, OverrideOrImpl)) {
2423 Which = 0;
2424 FirstVersion = OldIntroduced;
2425 SecondVersion = Introduced;
2426 } else if (!versionsMatch(Deprecated, OldDeprecated, OverrideOrImpl)) {
2427 Which = 1;
2428 FirstVersion = Deprecated;
2429 SecondVersion = OldDeprecated;
2430 } else if (!versionsMatch(Obsoleted, OldObsoleted, OverrideOrImpl)) {
2431 Which = 2;
2432 FirstVersion = Obsoleted;
2433 SecondVersion = OldObsoleted;
2434 }
2435
2436 if (Which == -1) {
2437 Diag(OldAA->getLocation(),
2438 diag::warn_mismatched_availability_override_unavail)
2439 << AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(Platform->getName())
2440 << (AMK == AMK_Override);
2441 } else {
2442 Diag(OldAA->getLocation(),
2443 diag::warn_mismatched_availability_override)
2444 << Which
2445 << AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(Platform->getName())
2446 << FirstVersion.getAsString() << SecondVersion.getAsString()
2447 << (AMK == AMK_Override);
2448 }
2449 if (AMK == AMK_Override)
2450 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_overridden_method);
2451 else
2452 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_protocol_method);
2453 } else {
2454 Diag(OldAA->getLocation(), diag::warn_mismatched_availability);
2455 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
2456 }
2457
2458 Attrs.erase(Attrs.begin() + i);
2459 --e;
2460 continue;
2461 }
2462
2463 VersionTuple MergedIntroduced2 = MergedIntroduced;
2464 VersionTuple MergedDeprecated2 = MergedDeprecated;
2465 VersionTuple MergedObsoleted2 = MergedObsoleted;
2466
2467 if (MergedIntroduced2.empty())
2468 MergedIntroduced2 = OldIntroduced;
2469 if (MergedDeprecated2.empty())
2470 MergedDeprecated2 = OldDeprecated;
2471 if (MergedObsoleted2.empty())
2472 MergedObsoleted2 = OldObsoleted;
2473
2474 if (checkAvailabilityAttr(*this, OldAA->getRange(), Platform,
2475 MergedIntroduced2, MergedDeprecated2,
2476 MergedObsoleted2)) {
2477 Attrs.erase(Attrs.begin() + i);
2478 --e;
2479 continue;
2480 }
2481
2482 MergedIntroduced = MergedIntroduced2;
2483 MergedDeprecated = MergedDeprecated2;
2484 MergedObsoleted = MergedObsoleted2;
2485 ++i;
2486 }
2487 }
2488
2489 if (FoundAny &&
2490 MergedIntroduced == Introduced &&
2491 MergedDeprecated == Deprecated &&
2492 MergedObsoleted == Obsoleted)
2493 return nullptr;
2494
2495 // Only create a new attribute if !OverrideOrImpl, but we want to do
2496 // the checking.
2497 if (!checkAvailabilityAttr(*this, Range, Platform, MergedIntroduced,
2498 MergedDeprecated, MergedObsoleted) &&
2499 !OverrideOrImpl) {
2500 auto *Avail = ::new (Context)
2501 AvailabilityAttr(Range, Context, Platform, Introduced, Deprecated,
2502 Obsoleted, IsUnavailable, Message, IsStrict,
2503 Replacement, Priority, AttrSpellingListIndex);
2504 Avail->setImplicit(Implicit);
2505 return Avail;
2506 }
2507 return nullptr;
2508}
2509
2510static void handleAvailabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2511 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
2512 return;
2513 IdentifierLoc *Platform = AL.getArgAsIdent(0);
2514 unsigned Index = AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex();
2515
2516 IdentifierInfo *II = Platform->Ident;
2517 if (AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(II->getName()).empty())
2518 S.Diag(Platform->Loc, diag::warn_availability_unknown_platform)
2519 << Platform->Ident;
2520
2521 auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D);
2522 if (!ND) // We warned about this already, so just return.
2523 return;
2524
2525 AvailabilityChange Introduced = AL.getAvailabilityIntroduced();
2526 AvailabilityChange Deprecated = AL.getAvailabilityDeprecated();
2527 AvailabilityChange Obsoleted = AL.getAvailabilityObsoleted();
2528 bool IsUnavailable = AL.getUnavailableLoc().isValid();
2529 bool IsStrict = AL.getStrictLoc().isValid();
2530 StringRef Str;
2531 if (const auto *SE = dyn_cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(AL.getMessageExpr()))
2532 Str = SE->getString();
2533 StringRef Replacement;
2534 if (const auto *SE = dyn_cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(AL.getReplacementExpr()))
2535 Replacement = SE->getString();
2536
2537 if (II->isStr("swift")) {
2538 if (Introduced.isValid() || Obsoleted.isValid() ||
2539 (!IsUnavailable && !Deprecated.isValid())) {
2540 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
2541 diag::warn_availability_swift_unavailable_deprecated_only);
2542 return;
2543 }
2544 }
2545
2546 int PriorityModifier = AL.isPragmaClangAttribute()
2547 ? Sema::AP_PragmaClangAttribute
2548 : Sema::AP_Explicit;
2549 AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2550 ND, AL.getRange(), II, false /*Implicit*/, Introduced.Version,
2551 Deprecated.Version, Obsoleted.Version, IsUnavailable, Str, IsStrict,
2552 Replacement, Sema::AMK_None, PriorityModifier, Index);
2553 if (NewAttr)
2554 D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2555
2556 // Transcribe "ios" to "watchos" (and add a new attribute) if the versioning
2557 // matches before the start of the watchOS platform.
2558 if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isWatchOS()) {
2559 IdentifierInfo *NewII = nullptr;
2560 if (II->getName() == "ios")
2561 NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("watchos");
2562 else if (II->getName() == "ios_app_extension")
2563 NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("watchos_app_extension");
2564
2565 if (NewII) {
2566 auto adjustWatchOSVersion = [](VersionTuple Version) -> VersionTuple {
2567 if (Version.empty())
2568 return Version;
2569 auto Major = Version.getMajor();
2570 auto NewMajor = Major >= 9 ? Major - 7 : 0;
2571 if (NewMajor >= 2) {
2572 if (Version.getMinor().hasValue()) {
2573 if (Version.getSubminor().hasValue())
2574 return VersionTuple(NewMajor, Version.getMinor().getValue(),
2575 Version.getSubminor().getValue());
2576 else
2577 return VersionTuple(NewMajor, Version.getMinor().getValue());
2578 }
2579 return VersionTuple(NewMajor);
2580 }
2581
2582 return VersionTuple(2, 0);
2583 };
2584
2585 auto NewIntroduced = adjustWatchOSVersion(Introduced.Version);
2586 auto NewDeprecated = adjustWatchOSVersion(Deprecated.Version);
2587 auto NewObsoleted = adjustWatchOSVersion(Obsoleted.Version);
2588
2589 AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2590 ND, AL.getRange(), NewII, true /*Implicit*/, NewIntroduced,
2591 NewDeprecated, NewObsoleted, IsUnavailable, Str, IsStrict,
2592 Replacement, Sema::AMK_None,
2593 PriorityModifier + Sema::AP_InferredFromOtherPlatform, Index);
2594 if (NewAttr)
2595 D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2596 }
2597 } else if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isTvOS()) {
2598 // Transcribe "ios" to "tvos" (and add a new attribute) if the versioning
2599 // matches before the start of the tvOS platform.
2600 IdentifierInfo *NewII = nullptr;
2601 if (II->getName() == "ios")
2602 NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("tvos");
2603 else if (II->getName() == "ios_app_extension")
2604 NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("tvos_app_extension");
2605
2606 if (NewII) {
2607 AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2608 ND, AL.getRange(), NewII, true /*Implicit*/, Introduced.Version,
2609 Deprecated.Version, Obsoleted.Version, IsUnavailable, Str, IsStrict,
2610 Replacement, Sema::AMK_None,
2611 PriorityModifier + Sema::AP_InferredFromOtherPlatform, Index);
2612 if (NewAttr)
2613 D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2614 }
2615 }
2616}
2617
2618static void handleExternalSourceSymbolAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
2619 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2620 if (!checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
2621 return;
2622 assert(checkAttributeAtMostNumArgs(S, AL, 3) &&
2623 "Invalid number of arguments in an external_source_symbol attribute");
2624
2625 StringRef Language;
2626 if (const auto *SE = dyn_cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(AL.getArgAsExpr(0)))
2627 Language = SE->getString();
2628 StringRef DefinedIn;
2629 if (const auto *SE = dyn_cast_or_null<StringLiteral>(AL.getArgAsExpr(1)))
2630 DefinedIn = SE->getString();
2631 bool IsGeneratedDeclaration = AL.getArgAsIdent(2) != nullptr;
2632
2633 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ExternalSourceSymbolAttr(
2634 AL.getRange(), S.Context, Language, DefinedIn, IsGeneratedDeclaration,
2635 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2636}
2637
2638template <class T>
2639static T *mergeVisibilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, SourceRange range,
2640 typename T::VisibilityType value,
2641 unsigned attrSpellingListIndex) {
2642 T *existingAttr = D->getAttr<T>();
2643 if (existingAttr) {
2644 typename T::VisibilityType existingValue = existingAttr->getVisibility();
2645 if (existingValue == value)
2646 return nullptr;
2647 S.Diag(existingAttr->getLocation(), diag::err_mismatched_visibility);
2648 S.Diag(range.getBegin(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
2649 D->dropAttr<T>();
2650 }
2651 return ::new (S.Context) T(range, S.Context, value, attrSpellingListIndex);
2652}
2653
2654VisibilityAttr *Sema::mergeVisibilityAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
2655 VisibilityAttr::VisibilityType Vis,
2656 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
2657 return ::mergeVisibilityAttr<VisibilityAttr>(*this, D, Range, Vis,
2658 AttrSpellingListIndex);
2659}
2660
2661TypeVisibilityAttr *Sema::mergeTypeVisibilityAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
2662 TypeVisibilityAttr::VisibilityType Vis,
2663 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
2664 return ::mergeVisibilityAttr<TypeVisibilityAttr>(*this, D, Range, Vis,
2665 AttrSpellingListIndex);
2666}
2667
2668static void handleVisibilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
2669 bool isTypeVisibility) {
2670 // Visibility attributes don't mean anything on a typedef.
2671 if (isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
2672 S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << AL;
2673 return;
2674 }
2675
2676 // 'type_visibility' can only go on a type or namespace.
2677 if (isTypeVisibility &&
2678 !(isa<TagDecl>(D) ||
2679 isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D) ||
2680 isa<NamespaceDecl>(D))) {
2681 S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
2682 << AL << ExpectedTypeOrNamespace;
2683 return;
2684 }
2685
2686 // Check that the argument is a string literal.
2687 StringRef TypeStr;
2688 SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
2689 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, TypeStr, &LiteralLoc))
2690 return;
2691
2692 VisibilityAttr::VisibilityType type;
2693 if (!VisibilityAttr::ConvertStrToVisibilityType(TypeStr, type)) {
2694 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL
2695 << TypeStr;
2696 return;
2697 }
2698
2699 // Complain about attempts to use protected visibility on targets
2700 // (like Darwin) that don't support it.
2701 if (type == VisibilityAttr::Protected &&
2702 !S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasProtectedVisibility()) {
2703 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_protected_visibility);
2704 type = VisibilityAttr::Default;
2705 }
2706
2707 unsigned Index = AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex();
2708 Attr *newAttr;
2709 if (isTypeVisibility) {
2710 newAttr = S.mergeTypeVisibilityAttr(D, AL.getRange(),
2711 (TypeVisibilityAttr::VisibilityType) type,
2712 Index);
2713 } else {
2714 newAttr = S.mergeVisibilityAttr(D, AL.getRange(), type, Index);
2715 }
2716 if (newAttr)
2717 D->addAttr(newAttr);
2718}
2719
2720static void handleObjCMethodFamilyAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2721 const auto *M = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
2722 if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
2723 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
2724 << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
2725 return;
2726 }
2727
2728 IdentifierLoc *IL = AL.getArgAsIdent(0);
2729 ObjCMethodFamilyAttr::FamilyKind F;
2730 if (!ObjCMethodFamilyAttr::ConvertStrToFamilyKind(IL->Ident->getName(), F)) {
2731 S.Diag(IL->Loc, diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << IL->Ident;
2732 return;
2733 }
2734
2735 if (F == ObjCMethodFamilyAttr::OMF_init &&
2736 !M->getReturnType()->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
2737 S.Diag(M->getLocation(), diag::err_init_method_bad_return_type)
2738 << M->getReturnType();
2739 // Ignore the attribute.
2740 return;
2741 }
2742
2743 D->addAttr(new (S.Context) ObjCMethodFamilyAttr(
2744 AL.getRange(), S.Context, F, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2745}
2746
2747static void handleObjCNSObject(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2748 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
2749 QualType T = TD->getUnderlyingType();
2750 if (!T->isCARCBridgableType()) {
2751 S.Diag(TD->getLocation(), diag::err_nsobject_attribute);
2752 return;
2753 }
2754 }
2755 else if (const auto *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D)) {
2756 QualType T = PD->getType();
2757 if (!T->isCARCBridgableType()) {
2758 S.Diag(PD->getLocation(), diag::err_nsobject_attribute);
2759 return;
2760 }
2761 }
2762 else {
2763 // It is okay to include this attribute on properties, e.g.:
2764 //
2765 // @property (retain, nonatomic) struct Bork *Q __attribute__((NSObject));
2766 //
2767 // In this case it follows tradition and suppresses an error in the above
2768 // case.
2769 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_nsobject_attribute);
2770 }
2771 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2772 ObjCNSObjectAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
2773 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2774}
2775
2776static void handleObjCIndependentClass(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2777 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
2778 QualType T = TD->getUnderlyingType();
2779 if (!T->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
2780 S.Diag(TD->getLocation(), diag::warn_ptr_independentclass_attribute);
2781 return;
2782 }
2783 } else {
2784 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_independentclass_attribute);
2785 return;
2786 }
2787 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2788 ObjCIndependentClassAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
2789 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2790}

2792static void handleBlocksAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2793 if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
2794 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
2795 << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
2796 return;
2797 }
2798
2799 IdentifierInfo *II = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
2800 BlocksAttr::BlockType type;
2801 if (!BlocksAttr::ConvertStrToBlockType(II->getName(), type)) {
2802 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << II;
2803 return;
2804 }
2805
2806 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2807 BlocksAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, type,
2808 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2809}
2810
2811static void handleSentinelAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2812 unsigned sentinel = (unsigned)SentinelAttr::DefaultSentinel;
2813 if (AL.getNumArgs() > 0) {
2814 Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
2815 llvm::APSInt Idx(32);
2816 if (E->isTypeDependent() || E->isValueDependent() ||
2817 !E->isIntegerConstantExpr(Idx, S.Context)) {
2818 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
2819 << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << E->getSourceRange();
2820 return;
2821 }
2822
2823 if (Idx.isSigned() && Idx.isNegative()) {
2824 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_sentinel_less_than_zero)
2825 << E->getSourceRange();
2826 return;
2827 }
2828
2829 sentinel = Idx.getZExtValue();
2830 }
2831
2832 unsigned nullPos = (unsigned)SentinelAttr::DefaultNullPos;
2833 if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
2834 Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
2835 llvm::APSInt Idx(32);
2836 if (E->isTypeDependent() || E->isValueDependent() ||
2837 !E->isIntegerConstantExpr(Idx, S.Context)) {
2838 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
2839 << AL << 2 << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << E->getSourceRange();
2840 return;
2841 }
2842 nullPos = Idx.getZExtValue();
2843
2844 if ((Idx.isSigned() && Idx.isNegative()) || nullPos > 1) {
2845 // FIXME: This error message could be improved, it would be nice
2846 // to say what the bounds actually are.
2847 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_sentinel_not_zero_or_one)
2848 << E->getSourceRange();
2849 return;
2850 }
2851 }
2852
2853 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
2854 const FunctionType *FT = FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>();
2855 if (isa<FunctionNoProtoType>(FT)) {
2856 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_named_arguments);
2857 return;
2858 }
2859
2860 if (!cast<FunctionProtoType>(FT)->isVariadic()) {
2861 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << 0;
2862 return;
2863 }
2864 } else if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
2865 if (!MD->isVariadic()) {
2866 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << 0;
2867 return;
2868 }
2869 } else if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(D)) {
2870 if (!BD->isVariadic()) {
2871 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << 1;
2872 return;
2873 }
2874 } else if (const auto *V = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
2875 QualType Ty = V->getType();
2876 if (Ty->isBlockPointerType() || Ty->isFunctionPointerType()) {
2877 const FunctionType *FT = Ty->isFunctionPointerType()
2878 ? D->getFunctionType()
2879 : Ty->getAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType()->getAs<FunctionType>();
2880 if (!cast<FunctionProtoType>(FT)->isVariadic()) {
2881 int m = Ty->isFunctionPointerType() ? 0 : 1;
2882 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << m;
2883 return;
2884 }
2885 } else {
2886 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
2887 << AL << ExpectedFunctionMethodOrBlock;
2888 return;
2889 }
2890 } else {
2891 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
2892 << AL << ExpectedFunctionMethodOrBlock;
2893 return;
2894 }
2895 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2896 SentinelAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, sentinel, nullPos,
2897 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2898}
2899
2900static void handleWarnUnusedResult(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2901 if (D->getFunctionType() &&
2902 D->getFunctionType()->getReturnType()->isVoidType()) {
2903 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_void_function_method) << AL << 0;
2904 return;
2905 }
2906 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
2907 if (MD->getReturnType()->isVoidType()) {
2908 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_void_function_method) << AL << 1;
2909 return;
2910 }
2911
2912 // If this is spelled as the standard C++17 attribute, but not in C++17, warn
2913 // about using it as an extension.
2914 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 && AL.isCXX11Attribute() &&
2915 !AL.getScopeName())
2916 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_cxx17_attr) << AL;
2917
2918 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2919 WarnUnusedResultAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
2920 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2921}
2922
2923static void handleWeakImportAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2924 // weak_import only applies to variable & function declarations.
2925 bool isDef = false;
2926 if (!D->canBeWeakImported(isDef)) {
2927 if (isDef)
2928 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_invalid_on_definition)
2929 << "weak_import";
2930 else if (isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) ||
2931 (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSDarwin() &&
2932 (isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D) || isa<EnumDecl>(D)))) {
2933 // Nothing to warn about here.
2934 } else
2935 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
2936 << AL << ExpectedVariableOrFunction;
2937
2938 return;
2939 }
2940
2941 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2942 WeakImportAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
2943 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2944}
2945
2946// Handles reqd_work_group_size and work_group_size_hint.
2947template <typename WorkGroupAttr>
2948static void handleWorkGroupSize(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2949 uint32_t WGSize[3];
2950 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
2951 const Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(i);
2952 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, WGSize[i], i,
2953 /*StrictlyUnsigned=*/true))
2954 return;
2955 if (WGSize[i] == 0) {
2956 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_is_zero)
2957 << AL << E->getSourceRange();
2958 return;
2959 }
2960 }
2961
2962 WorkGroupAttr *Existing = D->getAttr<WorkGroupAttr>();
2963 if (Existing && !(Existing->getXDim() == WGSize[0] &&
2964 Existing->getYDim() == WGSize[1] &&
2965 Existing->getZDim() == WGSize[2]))
2966 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
2967
2968 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) WorkGroupAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
2969 WGSize[0], WGSize[1], WGSize[2],
2970 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2971}
2972
2973// Handles intel_reqd_sub_group_size.
2974static void handleSubGroupSize(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2975 uint32_t SGSize;
2976 const Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
2977 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, SGSize))
2978 return;
2979 if (SGSize == 0) {
2980 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_is_zero)
2981 << AL << E->getSourceRange();
2982 return;
2983 }
2984
2985 OpenCLIntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr *Existing =
2986 D->getAttr<OpenCLIntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>();
2987 if (Existing && Existing->getSubGroupSize() != SGSize)
2988 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
2989
2990 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) OpenCLIntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr(
2991 AL.getRange(), S.Context, SGSize,
2992 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
2993}
2994
2995static void handleVecTypeHint(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2996 if (!AL.hasParsedType()) {
2997 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << AL << 1;
2998 return;
2999 }
3000
3001 TypeSourceInfo *ParmTSI = nullptr;
3002 QualType ParmType = S.GetTypeFromParser(AL.getTypeArg(), &ParmTSI);
3003 assert(ParmTSI && "no type source info for attribute argument");
3004
3005 if (!ParmType->isExtVectorType() && !ParmType->isFloatingType() &&
3006 (ParmType->isBooleanType() ||
3007 !ParmType->isIntegralType(S.getASTContext()))) {
3008 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_vec_type_hint)
3009 << ParmType;
3010 return;
3011 }
3012
3013 if (VecTypeHintAttr *A = D->getAttr<VecTypeHintAttr>()) {
3014 if (!S.Context.hasSameType(A->getTypeHint(), ParmType)) {
3015 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
3016 return;
3017 }
3018 }
3019
3020 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) VecTypeHintAttr(AL.getLoc(), S.Context,
3021 ParmTSI,
3022 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3023}
3024
3025SectionAttr *Sema::mergeSectionAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
3026 StringRef Name,
3027 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
3028 // Explicit or partial specializations do not inherit
3029 // the section attribute from the primary template.
3030 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
3031 if (AttrSpellingListIndex == SectionAttr::Declspec_allocate &&
3032 FD->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization())
3033 return nullptr;
3034 }
3035 if (SectionAttr *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>()) {
3036 if (ExistingAttr->getName() == Name)
3037 return nullptr;
3038 Diag(ExistingAttr->getLocation(), diag::warn_mismatched_section)
3039 << 1 /*section*/;
3040 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3041 return nullptr;
3042 }
3043 return ::new (Context) SectionAttr(Range, Context, Name,
3044 AttrSpellingListIndex);
3045}
3046
3047bool Sema::checkSectionName(SourceLocation LiteralLoc, StringRef SecName) {
3048 std::string Error = Context.getTargetInfo().isValidSectionSpecifier(SecName);
3049 if (!Error.empty()) {
3050 Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_section_invalid_for_target) << Error
3051 << 1 /*'section'*/;
3052 return false;
3053 }
3054 return true;
3055}
3056
3057static void handleSectionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3058 // Make sure that there is a string literal as the sections's single
3059 // argument.
3060 StringRef Str;
3061 SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
3062 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc))
3063 return;
3064
3065 if (!S.checkSectionName(LiteralLoc, Str))
3066 return;
3067
3068 // If the target wants to validate the section specifier, make it happen.
3069 std::string Error = S.Context.getTargetInfo().isValidSectionSpecifier(Str);
3070 if (!Error.empty()) {
3071 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_section_invalid_for_target)
3072 << Error;
3073 return;
3074 }
3075
3076 unsigned Index = AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex();
3077 SectionAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeSectionAttr(D, AL.getRange(), Str, Index);
3078 if (NewAttr)
3079 D->addAttr(NewAttr);
3080}
3081
3082static bool checkCodeSegName(Sema&S, SourceLocation LiteralLoc, StringRef CodeSegName) {
3083 std::string Error = S.Context.getTargetInfo().isValidSectionSpecifier(CodeSegName);
3084 if (!Error.empty()) {
3085 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_section_invalid_for_target) << Error
3086 << 0 /*'code-seg'*/;
3087 return false;
3088 }
3089 return true;
3090}
3091
3092CodeSegAttr *Sema::mergeCodeSegAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
3093 StringRef Name,
3094 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
3095 // Explicit or partial specializations do not inherit
3096 // the code_seg attribute from the primary template.
3097 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
3098 if (FD->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization())
3099 return nullptr;
3100 }
3101 if (const auto *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>()) {
3102 if (ExistingAttr->getName() == Name)
3103 return nullptr;
3104 Diag(ExistingAttr->getLocation(), diag::warn_mismatched_section)
3105 << 0 /*codeseg*/;
3106 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3107 return nullptr;
3108 }
3109 return ::new (Context) CodeSegAttr(Range, Context, Name,
3110 AttrSpellingListIndex);
3111}
3112
3113static void handleCodeSegAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3114 StringRef Str;
3115 SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
3116 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc))
3117 return;
3118 if (!checkCodeSegName(S, LiteralLoc, Str))
3119 return;
3120 if (const auto *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>()) {
3121 if (!ExistingAttr->isImplicit()) {
3122 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
3123 ExistingAttr->getName() == Str
3124 ? diag::warn_duplicate_codeseg_attribute
3125 : diag::err_conflicting_codeseg_attribute);
3126 return;
3127 }
3128 D->dropAttr<CodeSegAttr>();
3129 }
3130 if (CodeSegAttr *CSA = S.mergeCodeSegAttr(D, AL.getRange(), Str,
3131 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()))
3132 D->addAttr(CSA);
3133}
3134
3135// Check for things we'd like to warn about. Multiversioning issues are
3136// handled later in the process, once we know how many exist.
3137bool Sema::checkTargetAttr(SourceLocation LiteralLoc, StringRef AttrStr) {
3138 enum FirstParam { Unsupported, Duplicate };
3139 enum SecondParam { None, Architecture };
3140 for (auto Str : {"tune=", "fpmath="})
3141 if (AttrStr.find(Str) != StringRef::npos)
3142 return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
3143 << Unsupported << None << Str;
3144
3145 TargetAttr::ParsedTargetAttr ParsedAttrs = TargetAttr::parse(AttrStr);
3146
3147 if (!ParsedAttrs.Architecture.empty() &&
3148 !Context.getTargetInfo().isValidCPUName(ParsedAttrs.Architecture))
3149 return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
3150 << Unsupported << Architecture << ParsedAttrs.Architecture;
3151
3152 if (ParsedAttrs.DuplicateArchitecture)
3153 return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
3154 << Duplicate << None << "arch=";
3155
3156 for (const auto &Feature : ParsedAttrs.Features) {
3157 auto CurFeature = StringRef(Feature).drop_front(); // remove + or -.
3158 if (!Context.getTargetInfo().isValidFeatureName(CurFeature))
3159 return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
3160 << Unsupported << None << CurFeature;
3161 }
3162
3163 return false;
3164}
3165
3166static void handleTargetAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3167 StringRef Str;
3168 SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
3169 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc) ||
3170 S.checkTargetAttr(LiteralLoc, Str))
3171 return;
3172
3173 unsigned Index = AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex();
3174 TargetAttr *NewAttr =
3175 ::new (S.Context) TargetAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Str, Index);
3176 D->addAttr(NewAttr);
3177}
3178
3179static void handleMinVectorWidthAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3180 Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
3181 uint32_t VecWidth;
3182 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, VecWidth)) {
3183 AL.setInvalid();
3184 return;
3185 }
3186
3187 MinVectorWidthAttr *Existing = D->getAttr<MinVectorWidthAttr>();
3188 if (Existing && Existing->getVectorWidth() != VecWidth) {
3189 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
3190 return;
3191 }
3192
3193 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
3194 MinVectorWidthAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, VecWidth,
3195 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3196}
3197
3198static void handleCleanupAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3199 Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
3200 SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
3201 FunctionDecl *FD = nullptr;
3202 DeclarationNameInfo NI;
3203
3204 // gcc only allows for simple identifiers. Since we support more than gcc, we
3205 // will warn the user.
3206 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
3207 if (DRE->hasQualifier())
3208 S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_cleanup_ext);
3209 FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
3210 NI = DRE->getNameInfo();
3211 if (!FD) {
3212 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_arg_not_function) << 1
3213 << NI.getName();
3214 return;
3215 }
3216 } else if (auto *ULE = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E)) {
3217 if (ULE->hasExplicitTemplateArgs())
3218 S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_cleanup_ext);
3219 FD = S.ResolveSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(ULE, true);
3220 NI = ULE->getNameInfo();
3221 if (!FD) {
3222 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_arg_not_function) << 2
3223 << NI.getName();
3224 if (ULE->getType() == S.Context.OverloadTy)
3225 S.NoteAllOverloadCandidates(ULE);
3226 return;
3227 }
3228 } else {
3229 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_arg_not_function) << 0;
3230 return;
3231 }
3232
3233 if (FD->getNumParams() != 1) {
3234 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_func_must_take_one_arg)
3235 << NI.getName();
3236 return;
3237 }
3238
3239 // We're currently more strict than GCC about what function types we accept.
3240 // If this ever proves to be a problem it should be easy to fix.
3241 QualType Ty = S.Context.getPointerType(cast<VarDecl>(D)->getType());
3242 QualType ParamTy = FD->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
3243 if (S.CheckAssignmentConstraints(FD->getParamDecl(0)->getLocation(),
3244 ParamTy, Ty) != Sema::Compatible) {
3245 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_func_arg_incompatible_type)
3246 << NI.getName() << ParamTy << Ty;
3247 return;
3248 }
3249
3250 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
3251 CleanupAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, FD,
3252 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3253}
3254
3255static void handleEnumExtensibilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
3256 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3257 if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
3258 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
3259 << AL << 0 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
3260 return;
3261 }
3262
3263 EnumExtensibilityAttr::Kind ExtensibilityKind;
3264 IdentifierInfo *II = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
3265 if (!EnumExtensibilityAttr::ConvertStrToKind(II->getName(),
3266 ExtensibilityKind)) {
3267 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << II;
3268 return;
3269 }
3270
3271 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) EnumExtensibilityAttr(
3272 AL.getRange(), S.Context, ExtensibilityKind,
3273 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3274}
3275
3276/// Handle __attribute__((format_arg((idx)))) attribute based on
3277/// http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Function-Attributes.html
3278static void handleFormatArgAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3279 Expr *IdxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
3280 ParamIdx Idx;
3281 if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 1, IdxExpr, Idx))
3282 return;
3283
3284 // Make sure the format string is really a string.
3285 QualType Ty = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, Idx.getASTIndex());
3286
3287 bool NotNSStringTy = !isNSStringType(Ty, S.Context);
3288 if (NotNSStringTy &&
3289 !isCFStringType(Ty, S.Context) &&
3290 (!Ty->isPointerType() ||
3291 !Ty->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->isCharType())) {
3292 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_not)
3293 << "a string type" << IdxExpr->getSourceRange()
3294 << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 0);
3295 return;
3296 }
3297 Ty = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
3298 if (!isNSStringType(Ty, S.Context) &&
3299 !isCFStringType(Ty, S.Context) &&
3300 (!Ty->isPointerType() ||
3301 !Ty->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->isCharType())) {
3302 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_result_not)
3303 << (NotNSStringTy ? "string type" : "NSString")
3304 << IdxExpr->getSourceRange() << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 0);
3305 return;
3306 }
3307
3308 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) FormatArgAttr(
3309 AL.getRange(), S.Context, Idx, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3310}
3311
3312enum FormatAttrKind {
3313 CFStringFormat,
3314 NSStringFormat,
3315 StrftimeFormat,
3316 SupportedFormat,
3317 IgnoredFormat,
3318 InvalidFormat
3319};
3320
3321/// getFormatAttrKind - Map from format attribute names to supported format
3322/// types.
3323static FormatAttrKind getFormatAttrKind(StringRef Format) {
3324 return llvm::StringSwitch<FormatAttrKind>(Format)
3325 // Check for formats that get handled specially.
3326 .Case("NSString", NSStringFormat)
3327 .Case("CFString", CFStringFormat)
3328 .Case("strftime", StrftimeFormat)
3329
3330 // Otherwise, check for supported formats.
3331 .Cases("scanf", "printf", "printf0", "strfmon", SupportedFormat)
3332 .Cases("cmn_err", "vcmn_err", "zcmn_err", SupportedFormat)
3333 .Case("kprintf", SupportedFormat) // OpenBSD.
3334 .Case("freebsd_kprintf", SupportedFormat) // FreeBSD.
3335 .Case("os_trace", SupportedFormat)
3336 .Case("os_log", SupportedFormat)
3337
3338 .Cases("gcc_diag", "gcc_cdiag", "gcc_cxxdiag", "gcc_tdiag", IgnoredFormat)
3339 .Default(InvalidFormat);
3340}
3341
3342/// Handle __attribute__((init_priority(priority))) attributes based on
3343/// http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/C_002b_002b-Attributes.html
3344static void handleInitPriorityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3345 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
3346 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << AL;
3347 return;
3348 }
3349
3350 if (S.getCurFunctionOrMethodDecl()) {
3351 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_init_priority_object_attr);
3352 AL.setInvalid();
3353 return;
3354 }
3355 QualType T = cast<VarDecl>(D)->getType();
3356 if (S.Context.getAsArrayType(T))
3357 T = S.Context.getBaseElementType(T);
3358 if (!T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
3359 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_init_priority_object_attr);
3360 AL.setInvalid();
3361 return;
3362 }
3363
3364 Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
3365 uint32_t prioritynum;
3366 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, prioritynum)) {
3367 AL.setInvalid();
3368 return;
3369 }
3370
3371 if (prioritynum < 101 || prioritynum > 65535) {
3372 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_range)
3373 << E->getSourceRange() << AL << 101 << 65535;
3374 AL.setInvalid();
3375 return;
3376 }
3377 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
3378 InitPriorityAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, prioritynum,
3379 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3380}
3381
3382FormatAttr *Sema::mergeFormatAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
3383 IdentifierInfo *Format, int FormatIdx,
3384 int FirstArg,
3385 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
3386 // Check whether we already have an equivalent format attribute.
3387 for (auto *F : D->specific_attrs<FormatAttr>()) {
3388 if (F->getType() == Format &&
3389 F->getFormatIdx() == FormatIdx &&
3390 F->getFirstArg() == FirstArg) {
3391 // If we don't have a valid location for this attribute, adopt the
3392 // location.
3393 if (F->getLocation().isInvalid())
3394 F->setRange(Range);
3395 return nullptr;
3396 }
3397 }
3398
3399 return ::new (Context) FormatAttr(Range, Context, Format, FormatIdx,
3400 FirstArg, AttrSpellingListIndex);
3401}
3402
3403/// Handle __attribute__((format(type,idx,firstarg))) attributes based on
3404/// http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Function-Attributes.html
3405static void handleFormatAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3406 if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
3407 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
3408 << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
3409 return;
3410 }
3411
3412 // In C++ the implicit 'this' function parameter also counts, and they are
3413 // counted from one.
3414 bool HasImplicitThisParam = isInstanceMethod(D);
3415 unsigned NumArgs = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) + HasImplicitThisParam;
3416
3417 IdentifierInfo *II = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
3418 StringRef Format = II->getName();
3419
3420 if (normalizeName(Format)) {
3421 // If we've modified the string name, we need a new identifier for it.
3422 II = &S.Context.Idents.get(Format);
3423 }
3424
3425 // Check for supported formats.
3426 FormatAttrKind Kind = getFormatAttrKind(Format);
3427
3428 if (Kind == IgnoredFormat)
3429 return;
3430
3431 if (Kind == InvalidFormat) {
3432 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
3433 << AL << II->getName();
3434 return;
3435 }
3436
3437 // checks for the 2nd argument
3438 Expr *IdxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
3439 uint32_t Idx;
3440 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, IdxExpr, Idx, 2))
3441 return;
3442
3443 if (Idx < 1 || Idx > NumArgs) {
3444 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
3445 << AL << 2 << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
3446 return;
3447 }
3448
3449 // FIXME: Do we need to bounds check?
3450 unsigned ArgIdx = Idx - 1;
3451
3452 if (HasImplicitThisParam) {
3453 if (ArgIdx == 0) {
3454 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
3455 diag::err_format_attribute_implicit_this_format_string)
3456 << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
3457 return;
3458 }
3459 ArgIdx--;
3460 }
3461
3462 // make sure the format string is really a string
3463 QualType Ty = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, ArgIdx);
3464
3465 if (Kind == CFStringFormat) {
3466 if (!isCFStringType(Ty, S.Context)) {
3467 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_not)
3468 << "a CFString" << IdxExpr->getSourceRange()
3469 << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, ArgIdx);
3470 return;
3471 }
3472 } else if (Kind == NSStringFormat) {
3473 // FIXME: do we need to check if the type is NSString*? What are the
3474 // semantics?
3475 if (!isNSStringType(Ty, S.Context)) {
3476 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_not)
3477 << "an NSString" << IdxExpr->getSourceRange()
3478 << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, ArgIdx);
3479 return;
3480 }
3481 } else if (!Ty->isPointerType() ||
3482 !Ty->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->isCharType()) {
3483 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_not)
3484 << "a string type" << IdxExpr->getSourceRange()
3485 << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, ArgIdx);
3486 return;
3487 }
3488
3489 // check the 3rd argument
3490 Expr *FirstArgExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(2);
3491 uint32_t FirstArg;
3492 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, FirstArgExpr, FirstArg, 3))
3493 return;
3494
3495 // check if the function is variadic if the 3rd argument non-zero
3496 if (FirstArg != 0) {
3497 if (isFunctionOrMethodVariadic(D)) {
3498 ++NumArgs; // +1 for ...
3499 } else {
3500 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_format_attribute_requires_variadic);
3501 return;
3502 }
3503 }
3504
3505 // strftime requires FirstArg to be 0 because it doesn't read from any
3506 // variable the input is just the current time + the format string.
3507 if (Kind == StrftimeFormat) {
3508 if (FirstArg != 0) {
3509 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_strftime_third_parameter)
3510 << FirstArgExpr->getSourceRange();
3511 return;
3512 }
3513 // if 0 it disables parameter checking (to use with e.g. va_list)
3514 } else if (FirstArg != 0 && FirstArg != NumArgs) {
3515 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
3516 << AL << 3 << FirstArgExpr->getSourceRange();
3517 return;
3518 }
3519
3520 FormatAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeFormatAttr(D, AL.getRange(), II,
3521 Idx, FirstArg,
3522 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
3523 if (NewAttr)
3524 D->addAttr(NewAttr);
3525}
3526
3527/// Handle __attribute__((callback(CalleeIdx, PayloadIdx0, ...))) attributes.
3528static void handleCallbackAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3529 // The index that identifies the callback callee is mandatory.
3530 if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0) {
3531 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_no_callee)
3532 << AL.getRange();
3533 return;
3534 }
3535
3536 bool HasImplicitThisParam = isInstanceMethod(D);
3537 int32_t NumArgs = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D);
3538
3539 FunctionDecl *FD = D->getAsFunction();
3540 assert(FD && "Expected a function declaration!");
3541
3542 llvm::StringMap<int> NameIdxMapping;
3543 NameIdxMapping["__"] = -1;
3544
3545 NameIdxMapping["this"] = 0;
3546
3547 int Idx = 1;
3548 for (const ParmVarDecl *PVD : FD->parameters())
3549 NameIdxMapping[PVD->getName()] = Idx++;
3550
3551 auto UnknownName = NameIdxMapping.end();
3552
3553 SmallVector<int, 8> EncodingIndices;
3554 for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I < E; ++I) {
3555 SourceRange SR;
3556 int32_t ArgIdx;
3557
3558 if (AL.isArgIdent(I)) {
3559 IdentifierLoc *IdLoc = AL.getArgAsIdent(I);
3560 auto It = NameIdxMapping.find(IdLoc->Ident->getName());
3561 if (It == UnknownName) {
3562 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_argument_unknown)
3563 << IdLoc->Ident << IdLoc->Loc;
3564 return;
3565 }
3566
3567 SR = SourceRange(IdLoc->Loc);
3568 ArgIdx = It->second;
3569 } else if (AL.isArgExpr(I)) {
3570 Expr *IdxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(I);
3571
3572 // If the expression is not parseable as an int32_t we have a problem.
3573 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, IdxExpr, (uint32_t &)ArgIdx, I + 1,
3574 false)) {
3575 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
3576 << AL << (I + 1) << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
3577 return;
3578 }
3579
3580 // Check oob, excluding the special values, 0 and -1.
3581 if (ArgIdx < -1 || ArgIdx > NumArgs) {
3582 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
3583 << AL << (I + 1) << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
3584 return;
3585 }
3586
3587 SR = IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
3588 } else {
3589 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected ParsedAttr argument type!");
3590 }
3591
3592 if (ArgIdx == 0 && !HasImplicitThisParam) {
3593 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_implicit_this_not_available)
3594 << (I + 1) << SR;
3595 return;
3596 }
3597
3598 // Adjust for the case we do not have an implicit "this" parameter. In this
3599 // case we decrease all positive values by 1 to get LLVM argument indices.
3600 if (!HasImplicitThisParam && ArgIdx > 0)
3601 ArgIdx -= 1;
3602
3603 EncodingIndices.push_back(ArgIdx);
3604 }
3605
3606 int CalleeIdx = EncodingIndices.front();
3607 // Check if the callee index is proper, thus not "this" and not "unknown".
3608 // This means the "CalleeIdx" has to be non-negative if "HasImplicitThisParam"
3609 // is false and positive if "HasImplicitThisParam" is true.
3610 if (CalleeIdx < (int)HasImplicitThisParam) {
3611 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_invalid_callee)
3612 << AL.getRange();
3613 return;
3614 }
3615
3616 // Get the callee type, note the index adjustment as the AST doesn't contain
3617 // the this type (which the callee cannot reference anyway!).
3618 const Type *CalleeType =
3619 getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, CalleeIdx - HasImplicitThisParam)
3620 .getTypePtr();
3621 if (!CalleeType || !CalleeType->isFunctionPointerType()) {
3622 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_callee_no_function_type)
3623 << AL.getRange();
3624 return;
3625 }
3626
3627 const Type *CalleeFnType =
3628 CalleeType->getPointeeType()->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
3629
3630 // TODO: Check the type of the callee arguments.
3631
3632 const auto *CalleeFnProtoType = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(CalleeFnType);
3633 if (!CalleeFnProtoType) {
3634 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_callee_no_function_type)
3635 << AL.getRange();
3636 return;
3637 }
3638
3639 if (CalleeFnProtoType->getNumParams() > EncodingIndices.size() - 1) {
3640 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
3641 << AL << (unsigned)(EncodingIndices.size() - 1);
3642 return;
3643 }
3644
3645 if (CalleeFnProtoType->getNumParams() < EncodingIndices.size() - 1) {
3646 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
3647 << AL << (unsigned)(EncodingIndices.size() - 1);
3648 return;
3649 }
3650
3651 if (CalleeFnProtoType->isVariadic()) {
3652 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_callee_is_variadic) << AL.getRange();
3653 return;
3654 }
3655
3656 // Do not allow multiple callback attributes.
3657 if (D->hasAttr<CallbackAttr>()) {
3658 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_multiple) << AL.getRange();
3659 return;
3660 }
3661
3662 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CallbackAttr(
3663 AL.getRange(), S.Context, EncodingIndices.data(), EncodingIndices.size(),
3664 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3665}
3666
3667static void handleTransparentUnionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3668 // Try to find the underlying union declaration.
3669 RecordDecl *RD = nullptr;
3670 const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D);
3671 if (TD && TD->getUnderlyingType()->isUnionType())
3672 RD = TD->getUnderlyingType()->getAsUnionType()->getDecl();
3673 else
3674 RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(D);
3675
3676 if (!RD || !RD->isUnion()) {
3677 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type) << AL
3678 << ExpectedUnion;
3679 return;
3680 }
3681
3682 if (!RD->isCompleteDefinition()) {
3683 if (!RD->isBeingDefined())
3684 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
3685 diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_not_definition);
3686 return;
3687 }
3688
3689 RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = RD->field_begin(),
3690 FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
3691 if (Field == FieldEnd) {
3692 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_zero_fields);
3693 return;
3694 }
3695
3696 FieldDecl *FirstField = *Field;
3697 QualType FirstType = FirstField->getType();
3698 if (FirstType->hasFloatingRepresentation() || FirstType->isVectorType()) {
3699 S.Diag(FirstField->getLocation(),
3700 diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_floating)
3701 << FirstType->isVectorType() << FirstType;
3702 return;
3703 }
3704
3705 if (FirstType->isIncompleteType())
3706 return;
3707 uint64_t FirstSize = S.Context.getTypeSize(FirstType);
3708 uint64_t FirstAlign = S.Context.getTypeAlign(FirstType);
3709 for (; Field != FieldEnd; ++Field) {
3710 QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
3711 if (FieldType->isIncompleteType())
3712 return;
3713 // FIXME: this isn't fully correct; we also need to test whether the
3714 // members of the union would all have the same calling convention as the
3715 // first member of the union. Checking just the size and alignment isn't
3716 // sufficient (consider structs passed on the stack instead of in registers
3717 // as an example).
3718 if (S.Context.getTypeSize(FieldType) != FirstSize ||
3719 S.Context.getTypeAlign(FieldType) > FirstAlign) {
3720 // Warn if we drop the attribute.
3721 bool isSize = S.Context.getTypeSize(FieldType) != FirstSize;
3722 unsigned FieldBits = isSize? S.Context.getTypeSize(FieldType)
3723 : S.Context.getTypeAlign(FieldType);
3724 S.Diag(Field->getLocation(),
3725 diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_field_size_align)
3726 << isSize << Field->getDeclName() << FieldBits;
3727 unsigned FirstBits = isSize? FirstSize : FirstAlign;
3728 S.Diag(FirstField->getLocation(),
3729 diag::note_transparent_union_first_field_size_align)
3730 << isSize << FirstBits;
3731 return;
3732 }
3733 }
3734
3735 RD->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
3736 TransparentUnionAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
3737 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3738}
3739
3740static void handleAnnotateAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3741 // Make sure that there is a string literal as the annotation's single
3742 // argument.
3743 StringRef Str;
3744 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
3745 return;
3746
3747 // Don't duplicate annotations that are already set.
3748 for (const auto *I : D->specific_attrs<AnnotateAttr>()) {
3749 if (I->getAnnotation() == Str)
3750 return;
3751 }
3752
3753 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
3754 AnnotateAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Str,
3755 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3756}
3757
3758static void handleAlignValueAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3759 S.AddAlignValueAttr(AL.getRange(), D, AL.getArgAsExpr(0),
3760 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
3761}
3762
3763void Sema::AddAlignValueAttr(SourceRange AttrRange, Decl *D, Expr *E,
3764 unsigned SpellingListIndex) {
3765 AlignValueAttr TmpAttr(AttrRange, Context, E, SpellingListIndex);
3766 SourceLocation AttrLoc = AttrRange.getBegin();
3767
3768 QualType T;
3769 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D))
3770 T = TD->getUnderlyingType();
3771 else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D))
3772 T = VD->getType();
3773 else
3774 llvm_unreachable("Unknown decl type for align_value");
3775
3776 if (!T->isDependentType() && !T->isAnyPointerType() &&
3777 !T->isReferenceType() && !T->isMemberPointerType()) {
3778 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_attribute_pointer_or_reference_only)
3779 << &TmpAttr /*TmpAttr.getName()*/ << T << D->getSourceRange();
3780 return;
3781 }
3782
3783 if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
3784 llvm::APSInt Alignment;
3785 ExprResult ICE
3786 = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &Alignment,
3787 diag::err_align_value_attribute_argument_not_int,
3788 /*AllowFold*/ false);
3789 if (ICE.isInvalid())
3790 return;
3791
3792 if (!Alignment.isPowerOf2()) {
3793 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_not_power_of_two)
3794 << E->getSourceRange();
3795 return;
3796 }
3797
3798 D->addAttr(::new (Context)
3799 AlignValueAttr(AttrRange, Context, ICE.get(),
3800 SpellingListIndex));
3801 return;
3802 }
3803
3804 // Save dependent expressions in the AST to be instantiated.
3805 D->addAttr(::new (Context) AlignValueAttr(TmpAttr));
3806}
3807
3808static void handleAlignedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3809 // check the attribute arguments.
3810 if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
3811 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << AL << 1;
3812 return;
3813 }
3814
3815 if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0) {
3816 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AlignedAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
3817 true, nullptr, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
3818 return;
3819 }
3820
3821 Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
3822 if (AL.isPackExpansion() && !E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
3823 S.Diag(AL.getEllipsisLoc(),
3824 diag::err_pack_expansion_without_parameter_packs);
3825 return;
3826 }
3827
3828 if (!AL.isPackExpansion() && S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(E))
3829 return;
3830
3831 S.AddAlignedAttr(AL.getRange(), D, E, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex(),
3832 AL.isPackExpansion());
3833}
3834
3835void Sema::AddAlignedAttr(SourceRange AttrRange, Decl *D, Expr *E,
3836 unsigned SpellingListIndex, bool IsPackExpansion) {
3837 AlignedAttr TmpAttr(AttrRange, Context, true, E, SpellingListIndex);
3838 SourceLocation AttrLoc = AttrRange.getBegin();
3839
3840 // C++11 alignas(...) and C11 _Alignas(...) have additional requirements.
3841 if (TmpAttr.isAlignas()) {
3842 // C++11 [dcl.align]p1:
3843 // An alignment-specifier may be applied to a variable or to a class
3844 // data member, but it shall not be applied to a bit-field, a function
3845 // parameter, the formal parameter of a catch clause, or a variable
3846 // declared with the register storage class specifier. An
3847 // alignment-specifier may also be applied to the declaration of a class
3848 // or enumeration type.
3849 // C11 6.7.5/2:
3850 // An alignment attribute shall not be specified in a declaration of
3851 // a typedef, or a bit-field, or a function, or a parameter, or an
3852 // object declared with the register storage-class specifier.
3853 int DiagKind = -1;
3854 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
3855 DiagKind = 0;
3856 } else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
3857 if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register)
3858 DiagKind = 1;
3859 if (VD->isExceptionVariable())
3860 DiagKind = 2;
3861 } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D)) {
3862 if (FD->isBitField())
3863 DiagKind = 3;
3864 } else if (!isa<TagDecl>(D)) {
3865 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type) << &TmpAttr
3866 << (TmpAttr.isC11() ? ExpectedVariableOrField
3867 : ExpectedVariableFieldOrTag);
3868 return;
3869 }
3870 if (DiagKind != -1) {
3871 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignas_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
3872 << &TmpAttr << DiagKind;
3873 return;
3874 }
3875 }
3876
3877 if (E->isValueDependent()) {
3878 // We can't support a dependent alignment on a non-dependent type,
3879 // because we have no way to model that a type is "alignment-dependent"
3880 // but not dependent in any other way.
3881 if (const auto *TND = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
3882 if (!TND->getUnderlyingType()->isDependentType()) {
3883 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_dependent_typedef_name)
3884 << E->getSourceRange();
3885 return;
3886 }
3887 }
3888
3889 // Save dependent expressions in the AST to be instantiated.
3890 AlignedAttr *AA = ::new (Context) AlignedAttr(TmpAttr);
3891 AA->setPackExpansion(IsPackExpansion);
3892 D->addAttr(AA);
3893 return;
3894 }
3895
3896 // FIXME: Cache the number on the AL object?
3897 llvm::APSInt Alignment;
3898 ExprResult ICE
3899 = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &Alignment,
3900 diag::err_aligned_attribute_argument_not_int,
3901 /*AllowFold*/ false);
3902 if (ICE.isInvalid())
3903 return;
3904
3905 uint64_t AlignVal = Alignment.getZExtValue();
3906
3907 // C++11 [dcl.align]p2:
3908 // -- if the constant expression evaluates to zero, the alignment
3909 // specifier shall have no effect
3910 // C11 6.7.5p6:
3911 // An alignment specification of zero has no effect.
3912 if (!(TmpAttr.isAlignas() && !Alignment)) {
3913 if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_64(AlignVal)) {
3914 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_not_power_of_two)
3915 << E->getSourceRange();
3916 return;
3917 }
3918 }
3919
3920 // Alignment calculations can wrap around if it's greater than 2**28.
3921 unsigned MaxValidAlignment =
3922 Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF() ? 8192
3923 : 268435456;
3924 if (AlignVal > MaxValidAlignment) {
3925 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_aligned_too_great) << MaxValidAlignment
3926 << E->getSourceRange();
3927 return;
3928 }
3929
3930 if (Context.getTargetInfo().isTLSSupported()) {
3931 unsigned MaxTLSAlign =
3932 Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Context.getTargetInfo().getMaxTLSAlign())
3933 .getQuantity();
3934 const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
3935 if (MaxTLSAlign && AlignVal > MaxTLSAlign && VD &&
3936 VD->getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None) {
3937 Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::err_tls_var_aligned_over_maximum)
3938 << (unsigned)AlignVal << VD << MaxTLSAlign;
3939 return;
3940 }
3941 }
3942
3943 AlignedAttr *AA = ::new (Context) AlignedAttr(AttrRange, Context, true,
3944 ICE.get(), SpellingListIndex);
3945 AA->setPackExpansion(IsPackExpansion);
3946 D->addAttr(AA);
3947}
3948
3949void Sema::AddAlignedAttr(SourceRange AttrRange, Decl *D, TypeSourceInfo *TS,
3950 unsigned SpellingListIndex, bool IsPackExpansion) {
3951 // FIXME: Cache the number on the AL object if non-dependent?
3952 // FIXME: Perform checking of type validity
3953 AlignedAttr *AA = ::new (Context) AlignedAttr(AttrRange, Context, false, TS,
3954 SpellingListIndex);
3955 AA->setPackExpansion(IsPackExpansion);
3956 D->addAttr(AA);
3957}
3958
3959void Sema::CheckAlignasUnderalignment(Decl *D) {
3960 assert(D->hasAttrs() && "no attributes on decl");
3961
3962 QualType UnderlyingTy, DiagTy;
3963 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D))
3964 UnderlyingTy = DiagTy = VD->getType();
3965 else if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefDecl>(D))
3966 UnderlyingTy = DiagTy = Context.getTypeDeclType(TD);
3967 else {
3968 UnderlyingTy = DiagTy = Context.getTagDeclType(cast<TagDecl>(D));
3969 if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D))
3970 UnderlyingTy = ED->getIntegerType();
3971 }
3972 if (DiagTy->isDependentType() || DiagTy->isIncompleteType())
3973 return;
3974
3975 // C++11 [dcl.align]p5, C11 6.7.5/4:
3976 // The combined effect of all alignment attributes in a declaration shall
3977 // not specify an alignment that is less strict than the alignment that
3978 // would otherwise be required for the entity being declared.
3979 AlignedAttr *AlignasAttr = nullptr;
3980 unsigned Align = 0;
3981 // A decl has an alignment override if it has an aligned or packed attribute
3982 bool hasAlignOverride = D->hasAttr<PackedAttr>();
3983 for (auto *I : D->specific_attrs<AlignedAttr>()) {
3984 if (I->isAlignmentDependent())
3985 return;
3986 if (I->isAlignas())
3987 AlignasAttr = I;
3988 Align = std::max(Align, I->getAlignment(Context));
3989 hasAlignOverride = true;
3990 }
3991 // If this target supports capabilities, then warn if we're requesting
3992 // less-than-capability alignment for a type containing capabilities.
3993 // Only looking at the align attribute value will not give the correct
3994 // result since __attribute__((__aligned())) only increases the alignment
3995 // when applied to record declarations. However, when it is applied to a
3996 // typedef type it sets it instead. According to comments in
3997 // ASTContext::getTypeInfoImpl() this is due to GCC compatibility...
3998 bool ShouldDiagnoseCheriAlign =
3999 Context.getTargetInfo().SupportsCapabilities();
4000 if (ShouldDiagnoseCheriAlign && (isa<RecordDecl>(D) || isa<FieldDecl>(D))) {
4001 // If the attribute is applied to a record declaration declaration we only
4002 // need to warn if it also has the packed attribute
4003 ShouldDiagnoseCheriAlign = D->hasAttr<PackedAttr>();
4004 // Allow using the annotate attribute instead of a pragma warning silence
4005 if (auto *AA = D->getAttr<AnnotateAttr>()) {
4006 if (AA->getAnnotation() == "underaligned_capability")
4007 ShouldDiagnoseCheriAlign = false;
4008 }
4009 }
4010 if (hasAlignOverride && ShouldDiagnoseCheriAlign) {
4011 CharUnits CapAlign = Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(
4012 Context.getTargetInfo().getCHERICapabilityAlign());
4013 CharUnits MinAlign =
4014 Align ? Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Align) : CharUnits::One();
4015 if (const auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D)) {
4016 // Context.getDeclAlign() requires a full definition so for fields we
4017 // can usually only look at the aligned attribute
4018 if (Field->getParent()->getDefinition())
4019 MinAlign = Context.getDeclAlign(D);
4020 } else {
4021 // Not a field -> we have the full definition and can use it
4022 MinAlign = Context.getDeclAlign(D);
4023 }
4024 if ((MinAlign < CapAlign) && Context.containsCapabilities(UnderlyingTy)) {
4025 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_cheri_underalign)
4026 << (unsigned)MinAlign.getQuantity() << DiagTy
4027 << (unsigned)CapAlign.getQuantity();
4028 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::note_cheri_underalign_annotate_fixit);
4029 }
4030 }
4031
4032 if (AlignasAttr && Align) {
4033 CharUnits RequestedAlign = Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Align);
4034 CharUnits NaturalAlign = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(UnderlyingTy);
4035 if (NaturalAlign > RequestedAlign)
4036 Diag(AlignasAttr->getLocation(), diag::err_alignas_underaligned)
4037 << DiagTy << (unsigned)NaturalAlign.getQuantity();
4038 }
4039}
4040
4041bool Sema::checkMSInheritanceAttrOnDefinition(
4042 CXXRecordDecl *RD, SourceRange Range, bool BestCase,
4043 MSInheritanceAttr::Spelling SemanticSpelling) {
4044 assert(RD->hasDefinition() && "RD has no definition!");
4045
4046 // We may not have seen base specifiers or any virtual methods yet. We will
4047 // have to wait until the record is defined to catch any mismatches.
4048 if (!RD->getDefinition()->isCompleteDefinition())
4049 return false;
4050
4051 // The unspecified model never matches what a definition could need.
4052 if (SemanticSpelling == MSInheritanceAttr::Keyword_unspecified_inheritance)
4053 return false;
4054
4055 if (BestCase) {
4056 if (RD->calculateInheritanceModel() == SemanticSpelling)
4057 return false;
4058 } else {
4059 if (RD->calculateInheritanceModel() <= SemanticSpelling)
4060 return false;
4061 }
4062
4063 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::err_mismatched_ms_inheritance)
4064 << 0 /*definition*/;
4065 Diag(RD->getDefinition()->getLocation(), diag::note_defined_here)
4066 << RD->getNameAsString();
4067 return true;
4068}
4069
4070/// parseModeAttrArg - Parses attribute mode string and returns parsed type
4071/// attribute.
4072static void parseModeAttrArg(Sema &S, StringRef Str, unsigned &DestWidth,
4073 bool &IntegerMode, bool &ComplexMode) {
4074 IntegerMode = true;
4075 ComplexMode = false;
4076 switch (Str.size()) {
4077 case 2:
4078 switch (Str[0]) {
4079 case 'Q':
4080 DestWidth = 8;
4081 break;
4082 case 'H':
4083 DestWidth = 16;
4084 break;
4085 case 'S':
4086 DestWidth = 32;
4087 break;
4088 case 'D':
4089 DestWidth = 64;
4090 break;
4091 case 'X':
4092 DestWidth = 96;
4093 break;
4094 case 'T':
4095 DestWidth = 128;
4096 break;
4097 }
4098 if (Str[1] == 'F') {
4099 IntegerMode = false;
4100 } else if (Str[1] == 'C') {
4101 IntegerMode = false;
4102 ComplexMode = true;
4103 } else if (Str[1] != 'I') {
4104 DestWidth = 0;
4105 }
4106 break;
4107 case 4:
4108 // FIXME: glibc uses 'word' to define register_t; this is narrower than a
4109 // pointer on PIC16 and other embedded platforms.
4110 if (Str == "word")
4111 DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getRegisterWidth();
4112 else if (Str == "byte")
4113 DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getCharWidth();
4114 break;
4115 case 7:
4116 if (Str == "pointer")
4117 DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0);
4118 break;
4119 case 11:
4120 if (Str == "unwind_word")
4121 DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getUnwindWordWidth();
4122 break;
4123 }
4124}
4125
4126/// handleModeAttr - This attribute modifies the width of a decl with primitive
4127/// type.
4128///
4129/// Despite what would be logical, the mode attribute is a decl attribute, not a
4130/// type attribute: 'int ** __attribute((mode(HI))) *G;' tries to make 'G' be
4131/// HImode, not an intermediate pointer.
4132static void handleModeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4133 // This attribute isn't documented, but glibc uses it. It changes
4134 // the width of an int or unsigned int to the specified size.
4135 if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
4136 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
4137 << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
4138 return;
4139 }
4140
4141 IdentifierInfo *Name = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
4142
4143 S.AddModeAttr(AL.getRange(), D, Name, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
4144}
4145
4146void Sema::AddModeAttr(SourceRange AttrRange, Decl *D, IdentifierInfo *Name,
4147 unsigned SpellingListIndex, bool InInstantiation) {
4148 StringRef Str = Name->getName();
4149 normalizeName(Str);
4150 SourceLocation AttrLoc = AttrRange.getBegin();
4151
4152 unsigned DestWidth = 0;
4153 bool IntegerMode = true;
4154 bool ComplexMode = false;
4155 llvm::APInt VectorSize(64, 0);
4156 if (Str.size() >= 4 && Str[0] == 'V') {
4157 // Minimal length of vector mode is 4: 'V' + NUMBER(>=1) + TYPE(>=2).
4158 size_t StrSize = Str.size();
4159 size_t VectorStringLength = 0;
4160 while ((VectorStringLength + 1) < StrSize &&
4161 isdigit(Str[VectorStringLength + 1]))
4162 ++VectorStringLength;
4163 if (VectorStringLength &&
4164 !Str.substr(1, VectorStringLength).getAsInteger(10, VectorSize) &&
4165 VectorSize.isPowerOf2()) {
4166 parseModeAttrArg(*this, Str.substr(VectorStringLength + 1), DestWidth,
4167 IntegerMode, ComplexMode);
4168 // Avoid duplicate warning from template instantiation.
4169 if (!InInstantiation)
4170 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_vector_mode_deprecated);
4171 } else {
4172 VectorSize = 0;
4173 }
4174 }
4175
4176 if (!VectorSize)
4177 parseModeAttrArg(*this, Str, DestWidth, IntegerMode, ComplexMode);
4178
4179 // FIXME: Sync this with InitializePredefinedMacros; we need to match int8_t
4180 // and friends, at least with glibc.
4181 // FIXME: Make sure floating-point mappings are accurate
4182 // FIXME: Support XF and TF types
4183 if (!DestWidth) {
4184 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_machine_mode) << 0 /*Unknown*/ << Name;
4185 return;
4186 }
4187
4188 QualType OldTy;
4189 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D))
4190 OldTy = TD->getUnderlyingType();
4191 else if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
4192 // Something like 'typedef enum { X } __attribute__((mode(XX))) T;'.
4193 // Try to get type from enum declaration, default to int.
4194 OldTy = ED->getIntegerType();
4195 if (OldTy.isNull())
4196 OldTy = Context.IntTy;
4197 } else
4198 OldTy = cast<ValueDecl>(D)->getType();
4199
4200 if (OldTy->isDependentType()) {
4201 D->addAttr(::new (Context)
4202 ModeAttr(AttrRange, Context, Name, SpellingListIndex));
4203 return;
4204 }
4205
4206 // Base type can also be a vector type (see PR17453).
4207 // Distinguish between base type and base element type.
4208 QualType OldElemTy = OldTy;
4209 if (const auto *VT = OldTy->getAs<VectorType>())
4210 OldElemTy = VT->getElementType();
4211
4212 // GCC allows 'mode' attribute on enumeration types (even incomplete), except
4213 // for vector modes. So, 'enum X __attribute__((mode(QI)));' forms a complete
4214 // type, 'enum { A } __attribute__((mode(V4SI)))' is rejected.
4215 if ((isa<EnumDecl>(D) || OldElemTy->getAs<EnumType>()) &&
4216 VectorSize.getBoolValue()) {
4217 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_enum_mode_vector_type) << Name << AttrRange;
4218 return;
4219 }
4220 bool IntegralOrAnyEnumType =
4221 OldElemTy->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() || OldElemTy->getAs<EnumType>();
4222
4223 if (!OldElemTy->getAs<BuiltinType>() && !OldElemTy->isComplexType() &&
4224 !IntegralOrAnyEnumType)
4225 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_not_primitive);
4226 else if (IntegerMode) {
4227 if (!IntegralOrAnyEnumType)
4228 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
4229 } else if (ComplexMode) {
4230 if (!OldElemTy->isComplexType())
4231 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
4232 } else {
4233 if (!OldElemTy->isFloatingType())
4234 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
4235 }
4236
4237 QualType NewElemTy;
4238
4239 if (IntegerMode)
4240 NewElemTy = Context.getIntTypeForBitwidth(DestWidth,
4241 OldElemTy->isSignedIntegerType());
4242 else
4243 NewElemTy = Context.getRealTypeForBitwidth(DestWidth);
4244
4245 if (NewElemTy.isNull()) {
4246 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_machine_mode) << 1 /*Unsupported*/ << Name;
4247 return;
4248 }
4249
4250 if (ComplexMode) {
4251 NewElemTy = Context.getComplexType(NewElemTy);
4252 }
4253
4254 QualType NewTy = NewElemTy;
4255 if (VectorSize.getBoolValue()) {
4256 NewTy = Context.getVectorType(NewTy, VectorSize.getZExtValue(),
4257 VectorType::GenericVector);
4258 } else if (const auto *OldVT = OldTy->getAs<VectorType>()) {
4259 // Complex machine mode does not support base vector types.
4260 if (ComplexMode) {
4261 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_complex_mode_vector_type);
4262 return;
4263 }
4264 unsigned NumElements = Context.getTypeSize(OldElemTy) *
4265 OldVT->getNumElements() /
4266 Context.getTypeSize(NewElemTy);
4267 NewTy =
4268 Context.getVectorType(NewElemTy, NumElements, OldVT->getVectorKind());
4269 }
4270
4271 if (NewTy.isNull()) {
4272 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
4273 return;
4274 }
4275
4276 // Install the new type.
4277 if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D))
4278 TD->setModedTypeSourceInfo(TD->getTypeSourceInfo(), NewTy);
4279 else if (auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D))
4280 ED->setIntegerType(NewTy);
4281 else
4282 cast<ValueDecl>(D)->setType(NewTy);
4283
4284 D->addAttr(::new (Context)
4285 ModeAttr(AttrRange, Context, Name, SpellingListIndex));
4286}
4287
4288static void handleNoDebugAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4289 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4290 NoDebugAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4291 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4292}

4294AlwaysInlineAttr *Sema::mergeAlwaysInlineAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
4295 IdentifierInfo *Ident,
4296 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
4297 if (OptimizeNoneAttr *Optnone = D->getAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>()) {
4298 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << Ident;
4299 Diag(Optnone->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4300 return nullptr;
4301 }
4302
4303 if (D->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>())
4304 return nullptr;
4305
4306 return ::new (Context) AlwaysInlineAttr(Range, Context,
4307 AttrSpellingListIndex);
4308}

4310CommonAttr *Sema::mergeCommonAttr(Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4311 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<InternalLinkageAttr>(*this, D, AL))
4312 return nullptr;
4313
4314 return ::new (Context)
4315 CommonAttr(AL.getRange(), Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
4316}
4317
4318CommonAttr *Sema::mergeCommonAttr(Decl *D, const CommonAttr &AL) {
4319 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<InternalLinkageAttr>(*this, D, AL))
4320 return nullptr;
4321
4322 return ::new (Context)
4323 CommonAttr(AL.getRange(), Context, AL.getSpellingListIndex());
4324}
4325
4326InternalLinkageAttr *Sema::mergeInternalLinkageAttr(Decl *D,
4327 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4328 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
4329 // Attribute applies to Var but not any subclass of it (like ParmVar,
4330 // ImplicitParm or VarTemplateSpecialization).
4331 if (VD->getKind() != Decl::Var) {
4332 Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
4333 << AL << (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ? ExpectedFunctionVariableOrClass
4334 : ExpectedVariableOrFunction);
4335 return nullptr;
4336 }
4337 // Attribute does not apply to non-static local variables.
4338 if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
4339 Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::warn_internal_linkage_local_storage);
4340 return nullptr;
4341 }
4342 }
4343
4344 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<CommonAttr>(*this, D, AL))
4345 return nullptr;
4346
4347 return ::new (Context) InternalLinkageAttr(
4348 AL.getRange(), Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
4349}
4350InternalLinkageAttr *
4351Sema::mergeInternalLinkageAttr(Decl *D, const InternalLinkageAttr &AL) {
4352 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
4353 // Attribute applies to Var but not any subclass of it (like ParmVar,
4354 // ImplicitParm or VarTemplateSpecialization).
4355 if (VD->getKind() != Decl::Var) {
4356 Diag(AL.getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
4357 << &AL << (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ? ExpectedFunctionVariableOrClass
4358 : ExpectedVariableOrFunction);
4359 return nullptr;
4360 }
4361 // Attribute does not apply to non-static local variables.
4362 if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
4363 Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::warn_internal_linkage_local_storage);
4364 return nullptr;
4365 }
4366 }
4367
4368 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<CommonAttr>(*this, D, AL))
4369 return nullptr;
4370
4371 return ::new (Context)
4372 InternalLinkageAttr(AL.getRange(), Context, AL.getSpellingListIndex());
4373}
4374
4375MinSizeAttr *Sema::mergeMinSizeAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
4376 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
4377 if (OptimizeNoneAttr *Optnone = D->getAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>()) {
4378 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << "'minsize'";
4379 Diag(Optnone->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4380 return nullptr;
4381 }
4382
4383 if (D->hasAttr<MinSizeAttr>())
4384 return nullptr;
4385
4386 return ::new (Context) MinSizeAttr(Range, Context, AttrSpellingListIndex);
4387}

4389NoSpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr *Sema::mergeNoSpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr(
4390 Decl *D, const NoSpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr &AL) {
4391 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<SpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr>(*this, D, AL))
4392 return nullptr;
4393
4394 return ::new (Context) NoSpeculativeLoadHardeningAttr(
4395 AL.getRange(), Context, AL.getSpellingListIndex());
4396}
4397
4398OptimizeNoneAttr *Sema::mergeOptimizeNoneAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
4399 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
4400 if (AlwaysInlineAttr *Inline = D->getAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>()) {
4401 Diag(Inline->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << Inline;
4402 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4403 D->dropAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>();
4404 }
4405 if (MinSizeAttr *MinSize = D->getAttr<MinSizeAttr>()) {
4406 Diag(MinSize->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << MinSize;
4407 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4408 D->dropAttr<MinSizeAttr>();
4409 }
4410
4411 if (D->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>())
4412 return nullptr;
4413
4414 return ::new (Context) OptimizeNoneAttr(Range, Context,
4415 AttrSpellingListIndex);
4416}

4421 return nullptr;

4427static void handleAlwaysInlineAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4428 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<NotTailCalledAttr>(S, D, AL))
4429 return;
4430
4431 if (AlwaysInlineAttr *Inline = S.mergeAlwaysInlineAttr(
4432 D, AL.getRange(), AL.getName(),
4433 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()))
4434 D->addAttr(Inline);
4435}

4438 if (MinSizeAttr *MinSize = S.mergeMinSizeAttr(
4439 D, AL.getRange(), AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()))
4440 D->addAttr(MinSize);
4441}
