4444 if (OptimizeNoneAttr *Optnone = S.mergeOptimizeNoneAttr(
4445 D, AL.getRange(), AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()))
4446 D->addAttr(Optnone);
4447}
4448
4449static void handleConstantAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4450 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<CUDASharedAttr>(S, D, AL))
4451 return;
4452 const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
4453 if (!VD->hasGlobalStorage()) {
4454 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_nonglobal_constant);
4455 return;
4456 }
4457 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CUDAConstantAttr(
4458 AL.getRange(), S.Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4459}
4460
4461static void handleSharedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4462 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<CUDAConstantAttr>(S, D, AL))
4463 return;
4464 const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
4465 // extern __shared__ is only allowed on arrays with no length (e.g.
4466 // "int x[]").
4467 if (!S.getLangOpts().GPURelocatableDeviceCode && VD->hasExternalStorage() &&
4468 !isa<IncompleteArrayType>(VD->getType())) {
4469 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_extern_shared) << VD;
4470 return;
4471 }
4472 if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA && VD->hasLocalStorage() &&
4473 S.CUDADiagIfHostCode(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_host_shared)
4474 << S.CurrentCUDATarget())
4475 return;
4476 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CUDASharedAttr(
4477 AL.getRange(), S.Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4478}
4479
4480static void handleGlobalAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4481 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<CUDADeviceAttr>(S, D, AL) ||
4482 checkAttrMutualExclusion<CUDAHostAttr>(S, D, AL)) {
4483 return;
4484 }
4485 const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
4486 if (!FD->getReturnType()->isVoidType()) {
4487 SourceRange RTRange = FD->getReturnTypeSourceRange();
4488 S.Diag(FD->getTypeSpecStartLoc(), diag::err_kern_type_not_void_return)
4489 << FD->getType()
4490 << (RTRange.isValid() ? FixItHint::CreateReplacement(RTRange, "void")
4491 : FixItHint());
4492 return;
4493 }
4494 if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
4495 if (Method->isInstance()) {
4496 S.Diag(Method->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_kern_is_nonstatic_method)
4497 << Method;
4498 return;
4499 }
4500 S.Diag(Method->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_kern_is_method) << Method;
4501 }
4502 // Only warn for "inline" when compiling for host, to cut down on noise.
4503 if (FD->isInlineSpecified() && !S.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
4504 S.Diag(FD->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_kern_is_inline) << FD;
4505
4506 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4507 CUDAGlobalAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4508 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4509}
4510
4511static void handleSensitiveAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &Attr) {
4512 // check the attribute arguments.
4513 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(S, Attr, 0))
4514 return;
4515
4516
4517 if (!isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4518 S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
4519 << Attr.getName() << ExpectedFunction;
4520 return;
4521 }
4522
4523 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SensitiveAttr(Attr.getRange(), S.Context,
4524 Attr.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4525}
4526
4527static void handleGNUInlineAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4528 const auto *Fn = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
4529 if (!Fn->isInlineSpecified()) {
4530 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_gnu_inline_attribute_requires_inline);
4531 return;
4532 }
4533
4534 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4535 GNUInlineAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4536 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4537}
4538
4539static void handleCallConvAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4540 if (hasDeclarator(D)) return;
4541
4542 // Diagnostic is emitted elsewhere: here we store the (valid) AL
4543 // in the Decl node for syntactic reasoning, e.g., pretty-printing.
4544 CallingConv CC;
4545 if (S.CheckCallingConvAttr(AL, CC, /*FD*/nullptr))
4546 return;
4547
4548 if (!isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
4549 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
4550 << AL << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
4551 return;
4552 }
4553
4554 switch (AL.getKind()) {
4555 case ParsedAttr::AT_FastCall:
4556 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4557 FastCallAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4558 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4559 return;
4560 case ParsedAttr::AT_StdCall:
4561 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4562 StdCallAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4563 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4564 return;
4565 case ParsedAttr::AT_ThisCall:
4566 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4567 ThisCallAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4568 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4569 return;
4570 case ParsedAttr::AT_CDecl:
4571 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4572 CDeclAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4573 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4574 return;
4575 case ParsedAttr::AT_Pascal:
4576 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4577 PascalAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4578 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4579 return;
4580 case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftCall:
4581 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4582 SwiftCallAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4583 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4584 return;
4585 case ParsedAttr::AT_VectorCall:
4586 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4587 VectorCallAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4588 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4589 return;
4590 case ParsedAttr::AT_MSABI:
4591 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4592 MSABIAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4593 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4594 return;
4595 case ParsedAttr::AT_SysVABI:
4596 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4597 SysVABIAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4598 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4599 return;
4600 case ParsedAttr::AT_RegCall:
4601 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) RegCallAttr(
4602 AL.getRange(), S.Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4603 return;
4604 case ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs: {
4605 PcsAttr::PCSType PCS;
4606 switch (CC) {
4607 case CC_AAPCS:
4608 PCS = PcsAttr::AAPCS;
4609 break;
4610 case CC_AAPCS_VFP:
4611 PCS = PcsAttr::AAPCS_VFP;
4612 break;
4613 default:
4614 llvm_unreachable("unexpected calling convention in pcs attribute");
4615 }
4616
4617 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4618 PcsAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, PCS,
4619 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4620 return;
4621 }
4622 case ParsedAttr::AT_CHERICCall:
4623 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4624 CHERICCallAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4625 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4626 return;
4627 case ParsedAttr::AT_CHERICCallee:
4628 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4629 CHERICCalleeAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4630 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4631 return;
4632 case ParsedAttr::AT_CHERICCallback:
4633 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4634 CHERICCallbackAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4635 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4636 return;
4637 case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64VectorPcs:
4638 D->addAttr(::new(S.Context)
4639 AArch64VectorPcsAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4640 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4641 return;
4642 case ParsedAttr::AT_IntelOclBicc:
4643 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
4644 IntelOclBiccAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
4645 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4646 return;
4647 case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveMost:
4648 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PreserveMostAttr(
4649 AL.getRange(), S.Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4650 return;
4651 case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveAll:
4652 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PreserveAllAttr(
4653 AL.getRange(), S.Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4654 return;
4655 default:
4656 llvm_unreachable("unexpected attribute kind");
4657 }
4658}
4659
4660static void handleSuppressAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4661 if (!checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
4662 return;
4663
4664 std::vector<StringRef> DiagnosticIdentifiers;
4665 for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
4666 StringRef RuleName;
4667
4668 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, RuleName, nullptr))
4669 return;
4670
4671 // FIXME: Warn if the rule name is unknown. This is tricky because only
4672 // clang-tidy knows about available rules.
4673 DiagnosticIdentifiers.push_back(RuleName);
4674 }
4675 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SuppressAttr(
4676 AL.getRange(), S.Context, DiagnosticIdentifiers.data(),
4677 DiagnosticIdentifiers.size(), AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
4678}
4679
4680bool Sema::CheckCallingConvAttr(const ParsedAttr &Attrs, CallingConv &CC,
4681 const FunctionDecl *FD) {
4682 if (Attrs.isInvalid())
4683 return true;
4684
4685 if (Attrs.hasProcessingCache()) {
4686 CC = (CallingConv) Attrs.getProcessingCache();
4687 return false;
4688 }
4689
4690 unsigned ReqArgs = Attrs.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs ? 1 : 0;
4691 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(*this, Attrs, ReqArgs)) {
4692 Attrs.setInvalid();
4693 return true;
4694 }
4695
4696 // TODO: diagnose uses of these conventions on the wrong target.
4697 switch (Attrs.getKind()) {
4698 case ParsedAttr::AT_CDecl:
4699 CC = CC_C;
4700 break;
4701 case ParsedAttr::AT_FastCall:
4702 CC = CC_X86FastCall;
4703 break;
4704 case ParsedAttr::AT_StdCall:
4705 CC = CC_X86StdCall;
4706 break;
4707 case ParsedAttr::AT_ThisCall:
4708 CC = CC_X86ThisCall;
4709 break;
4710 case ParsedAttr::AT_Pascal:
4711 CC = CC_X86Pascal;
4712 break;
4713 case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftCall:
4714 CC = CC_Swift;
4715 break;
4716 case ParsedAttr::AT_VectorCall:
4717 CC = CC_X86VectorCall;
4718 break;
4719 case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64VectorPcs:
4720 CC = CC_AArch64VectorCall;
4721 break;
4722 case ParsedAttr::AT_RegCall:
4723 CC = CC_X86RegCall;
4724 break;
4725 case ParsedAttr::AT_MSABI:
4726 CC = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSWindows() ? CC_C :
4727 CC_Win64;
4728 break;
4729 case ParsedAttr::AT_SysVABI:
4730 CC = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSWindows() ? CC_X86_64SysV :
4731 CC_C;
4732 break;
4733 case ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs: {
4734 StringRef StrRef;
4735 if (!checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(Attrs, 0, StrRef)) {
4736 Attrs.setInvalid();
4737 return true;
4738 }
4739 if (StrRef == "aapcs") {
4740 CC = CC_AAPCS;
4741 break;
4742 } else if (StrRef == "aapcs-vfp") {
4743 CC = CC_AAPCS_VFP;
4744 break;
4745 }
4746
4747 Attrs.setInvalid();
4748 Diag(Attrs.getLoc(), diag::err_invalid_pcs);
4749 return true;
4750 }
4751 case ParsedAttr::AT_CHERICCall:
4752 CC = CC_CHERICCall;
4753 break;
4754 case ParsedAttr::AT_CHERICCallee:
4755 CC = CC_CHERICCallee;
4756 break;
4757 case ParsedAttr::AT_CHERICCallback:
4758 CC = CC_CHERICCallback;
4759 break;
4760 case ParsedAttr::AT_IntelOclBicc:
4761 CC = CC_IntelOclBicc;
4762 break;
4763 case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveMost:
4764 CC = CC_PreserveMost;
4765 break;
4766 case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveAll:
4767 CC = CC_PreserveAll;
4768 break;
4769 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected attribute kind");
4770 }
4771
4772 TargetInfo::CallingConvCheckResult A = TargetInfo::CCCR_OK;
4773 const TargetInfo &TI = Context.getTargetInfo();
4774 // CUDA functions may have host and/or device attributes which indicate
4775 // their targeted execution environment, therefore the calling convention
4776 // of functions in CUDA should be checked against the target deduced based
4777 // on their host/device attributes.
4778 if (LangOpts.CUDA) {
4779 auto *Aux = Context.getAuxTargetInfo();
4780 auto CudaTarget = IdentifyCUDATarget(FD);
4781 bool CheckHost = false, CheckDevice = false;
4782 switch (CudaTarget) {
4783 case CFT_HostDevice:
4784 CheckHost = true;
4785 CheckDevice = true;
4786 break;
4787 case CFT_Host:
4788 CheckHost = true;
4789 break;
4790 case CFT_Device:
4791 case CFT_Global:
4792 CheckDevice = true;
4793 break;
4794 case CFT_InvalidTarget:
4795 llvm_unreachable("unexpected cuda target");
4796 }
4797 auto *HostTI = LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice ? Aux : &TI;
4798 auto *DeviceTI = LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice ? &TI : Aux;
4799 if (CheckHost && HostTI)
4800 A = HostTI->checkCallingConvention(CC);
4801 if (A == TargetInfo::CCCR_OK && CheckDevice && DeviceTI)
4802 A = DeviceTI->checkCallingConvention(CC);
4803 } else {
4804 A = TI.checkCallingConvention(CC);
4805 }
4806 if (A != TargetInfo::CCCR_OK) {
4807 if (A == TargetInfo::CCCR_Warning)
4808 Diag(Attrs.getLoc(), diag::warn_cconv_ignored)
4809 << Attrs << (int)CallingConventionIgnoredReason::ForThisTarget;
4810
4811 // This convention is not valid for the target. Use the default function or
4812 // method calling convention.
4813 bool IsCXXMethod = false, IsVariadic = false;
4814 if (FD) {
4815 IsCXXMethod = FD->isCXXInstanceMember();
4816 IsVariadic = FD->isVariadic();
4817 }
4818 CC = Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(IsVariadic, IsCXXMethod);
4819 }
4820
4821 Attrs.setProcessingCache((unsigned) CC);
4822 return false;
4823}
4824
4825/// Pointer-like types in the default address space.
4826static bool isValidSwiftContextType(QualType Ty) {
4827 if (!Ty->hasPointerRepresentation())
4828 return Ty->isDependentType();
4829 return Ty->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() == LangAS::Default;
4830}
4831
4832/// Pointers and references in the default address space.
4833static bool isValidSwiftIndirectResultType(QualType Ty) {
4834 if (const auto *PtrType = Ty->getAs<PointerType>()) {
4835 Ty = PtrType->getPointeeType();
4836 } else if (const auto *RefType = Ty->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
4837 Ty = RefType->getPointeeType();
4838 } else {
4839 return Ty->isDependentType();
4840 }
4841 return Ty.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::Default;
4842}
4843
4844/// Pointers and references to pointers in the default address space.
4845static bool isValidSwiftErrorResultType(QualType Ty) {
4846 if (const auto *PtrType = Ty->getAs<PointerType>()) {
4847 Ty = PtrType->getPointeeType();
4848 } else if (const auto *RefType = Ty->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
4849 Ty = RefType->getPointeeType();
4850 } else {
4851 return Ty->isDependentType();
4852 }
4853 if (!Ty.getQualifiers().empty())
4854 return false;
4855 return isValidSwiftContextType(Ty);
4856}
4857
4858static void handleParameterABIAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &Attrs,
4859 ParameterABI Abi) {
4860 S.AddParameterABIAttr(Attrs.getRange(), D, Abi,
4861 Attrs.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
4862}
4863
4864void Sema::AddParameterABIAttr(SourceRange range, Decl *D, ParameterABI abi,
4865 unsigned spellingIndex) {
4866
4867 QualType type = cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)->getType();
4868
4869 if (auto existingAttr = D->getAttr<ParameterABIAttr>()) {
4870 if (existingAttr->getABI() != abi) {
4871 Diag(range.getBegin(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
4872 << getParameterABISpelling(abi) << existingAttr;
4873 Diag(existingAttr->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4874 return;
4875 }
4876 }
4877
4878 switch (abi) {
4879 case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
4880 llvm_unreachable("explicit attribute for ordinary parameter ABI?");
4881
4882 case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
4883 if (!isValidSwiftContextType(type)) {
4884 Diag(range.getBegin(), diag::err_swift_abi_parameter_wrong_type)
4885 << getParameterABISpelling(abi)
4886 << /*pointer to pointer */ 0 << type;
4887 }
4888 D->addAttr(::new (Context)
4889 SwiftContextAttr(range, Context, spellingIndex));
4890 return;
4891
4892 case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
4893 if (!isValidSwiftErrorResultType(type)) {
4894 Diag(range.getBegin(), diag::err_swift_abi_parameter_wrong_type)
4895 << getParameterABISpelling(abi)
4896 << /*pointer to pointer */ 1 << type;
4897 }
4898 D->addAttr(::new (Context)
4899 SwiftErrorResultAttr(range, Context, spellingIndex));
4900 return;
4901
4902 case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult:
4903 if (!isValidSwiftIndirectResultType(type)) {
4904 Diag(range.getBegin(), diag::err_swift_abi_parameter_wrong_type)
4905 << getParameterABISpelling(abi)
4906 << /*pointer*/ 0 << type;
4907 }
4908 D->addAttr(::new (Context)
4909 SwiftIndirectResultAttr(range, Context, spellingIndex));
4910 return;
4911 }
4912 llvm_unreachable("bad parameter ABI attribute");
4913}
4914
4915/// Checks a regparm attribute, returning true if it is ill-formed and
4916/// otherwise setting numParams to the appropriate value.
4917bool Sema::CheckRegparmAttr(const ParsedAttr &AL, unsigned &numParams) {
4918 if (AL.isInvalid())
4919 return true;
4920
4921 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(*this, AL, 1)) {
4922 AL.setInvalid();
4923 return true;
4924 }
4925
4926 uint32_t NP;
4927 Expr *NumParamsExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
4928 if (!checkUInt32Argument(*this, AL, NumParamsExpr, NP)) {
4929 AL.setInvalid();
4930 return true;
4931 }
4932
4933 if (Context.getTargetInfo().getRegParmMax() == 0) {
4934 Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_regparm_wrong_platform)
4935 << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
4936 AL.setInvalid();
4937 return true;
4938 }
4939
4940 numParams = NP;
4941 if (numParams > Context.getTargetInfo().getRegParmMax()) {
4942 Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_regparm_invalid_number)
4943 << Context.getTargetInfo().getRegParmMax() << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
4944 AL.setInvalid();
4945 return true;
4946 }
4947
4948 return false;
4949}
4950
4951// Checks whether an argument of launch_bounds attribute is
4952// acceptable, performs implicit conversion to Rvalue, and returns
4953// non-nullptr Expr result on success. Otherwise, it returns nullptr
4954// and may output an error.
4955static Expr *makeLaunchBoundsArgExpr(Sema &S, Expr *E,
4956 const CUDALaunchBoundsAttr &AL,
4957 const unsigned Idx) {
4958 if (S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(E))
4959 return nullptr;
4960
4961 // Accept template arguments for now as they depend on something else.
4962 // We'll get to check them when they eventually get instantiated.
4963 if (E->isValueDependent())
4964 return E;
4965
4966 llvm::APSInt I(64);
4967 if (!E->isIntegerConstantExpr(I, S.Context)) {
4968 S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
4969 << &AL << Idx << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << E->getSourceRange();
4970 return nullptr;
4971 }
4972 // Make sure we can fit it in 32 bits.
4973 if (!I.isIntN(32)) {
4974 S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_ice_too_large) << I.toString(10, false)
4975 << 32 << /* Unsigned */ 1;
4976 return nullptr;
4977 }
4978 if (I < 0)
4979 S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_argument_n_negative)
4980 << &AL << Idx << E->getSourceRange();
4981
4982 // We may need to perform implicit conversion of the argument.
4983 InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
4984 S.Context, S.Context.getConstType(S.Context.IntTy), /*consume*/ false);
4985 ExprResult ValArg = S.PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), E);
4986 assert(!ValArg.isInvalid() &&
4987 "Unexpected PerformCopyInitialization() failure.");
4988
4989 return ValArg.getAs<Expr>();
4990}
4991
4992void Sema::AddLaunchBoundsAttr(SourceRange AttrRange, Decl *D, Expr *MaxThreads,
4993 Expr *MinBlocks, unsigned SpellingListIndex) {
4994 CUDALaunchBoundsAttr TmpAttr(AttrRange, Context, MaxThreads, MinBlocks,
4995 SpellingListIndex);
4996 MaxThreads = makeLaunchBoundsArgExpr(*this, MaxThreads, TmpAttr, 0);
4997 if (MaxThreads == nullptr)
4998 return;
4999
5000 if (MinBlocks) {
5001 MinBlocks = makeLaunchBoundsArgExpr(*this, MinBlocks, TmpAttr, 1);
5002 if (MinBlocks == nullptr)
5003 return;
5004 }
5005
5006 D->addAttr(::new (Context) CUDALaunchBoundsAttr(
5007 AttrRange, Context, MaxThreads, MinBlocks, SpellingListIndex));
5008}
5009
5010static void handleLaunchBoundsAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5011 if (!checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, 1) ||
5012 !checkAttributeAtMostNumArgs(S, AL, 2))
5013 return;
5014
5015 S.AddLaunchBoundsAttr(AL.getRange(), D, AL.getArgAsExpr(0),
5016 AL.getNumArgs() > 1 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(1) : nullptr,
5017 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
5018}
5019
5020static void handleArgumentWithTypeTagAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5021 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5022 if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
5023 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
5024 << AL << /* arg num = */ 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
5025 return;
5026 }
5027
5028 ParamIdx ArgumentIdx;
5029 if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 2, AL.getArgAsExpr(1),
5030 ArgumentIdx))
5031 return;
5032
5033 ParamIdx TypeTagIdx;
5034 if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 3, AL.getArgAsExpr(2),
5035 TypeTagIdx))
5036 return;
5037
5038 bool IsPointer = AL.getName()->getName() == "pointer_with_type_tag";
5039 if (IsPointer) {
5040 // Ensure that buffer has a pointer type.
5041 unsigned ArgumentIdxAST = ArgumentIdx.getASTIndex();
5042 if (ArgumentIdxAST >= getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) ||
5043 !getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, ArgumentIdxAST)->isPointerType())
5044 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_pointers_only) << AL << 0;
5045 }
5046
5047 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ArgumentWithTypeTagAttr(
5048 AL.getRange(), S.Context, AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident, ArgumentIdx,
5049 TypeTagIdx, IsPointer, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5050}
5051
5052static void handleTypeTagForDatatypeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5053 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5054 if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
5055 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
5056 << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
5057 return;
5058 }
5059
5060 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
5061 return;
5062
5063 if (!isa<VarDecl>(D)) {
5064 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5065 << AL << ExpectedVariable;
5066 return;
5067 }
5068
5069 IdentifierInfo *PointerKind = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
5070 TypeSourceInfo *MatchingCTypeLoc = nullptr;
5071 S.GetTypeFromParser(AL.getMatchingCType(), &MatchingCTypeLoc);
5072 assert(MatchingCTypeLoc && "no type source info for attribute argument");
5073
5074 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5075 TypeTagForDatatypeAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, PointerKind,
5076 MatchingCTypeLoc,
5077 AL.getLayoutCompatible(),
5078 AL.getMustBeNull(),
5079 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5080}
5081
5082static void handleXRayLogArgsAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5083 ParamIdx ArgCount;
5084
5085 if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 1, AL.getArgAsExpr(0),
5086 ArgCount,
5087 true /* CanIndexImplicitThis */))
5088 return;
5089
5090 // ArgCount isn't a parameter index [0;n), it's a count [1;n]
5091 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) XRayLogArgsAttr(
5092 AL.getRange(), S.Context, ArgCount.getSourceIndex(),
5093 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5094}

5096//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5097// Checker-specific attribute handlers.
5098//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5099static bool isValidSubjectOfNSReturnsRetainedAttribute(QualType QT) {
5100 return QT->isDependentType() || QT->isObjCRetainableType();
5101}
5102
5103static bool isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(QualType QT) {
5104 return QT->isDependentType() || QT->isObjCObjectPointerType() ||
5105 QT->isObjCNSObjectType();
5106}
5107
5108static bool isValidSubjectOfCFAttribute(QualType QT) {
5109 return QT->isDependentType() || QT->isPointerType() ||
5110 isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(QT);
5111}
5112
5113static bool isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(QualType QT) {
5114 if (QT->isDependentType())
5115 return true;
5116 QualType PT = QT->getPointeeType();
5117 return !PT.isNull() && PT->getAsCXXRecordDecl() != nullptr;
5118}
5119
5120void Sema::AddXConsumedAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange SR, unsigned SpellingIndex,
5121 RetainOwnershipKind K,
5122 bool IsTemplateInstantiation) {
5123 ValueDecl *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D);
5124 switch (K) {
5125 case RetainOwnershipKind::OS:
5126 handleSimpleAttributeOrDiagnose<OSConsumedAttr>(
5127 *this, VD, SR, SpellingIndex, isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(VD->getType()),
5128 diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type,
5129 /*ExtraArgs=*/SR, "os_consumed", /*pointers*/ 1);
5130 return;
5131 case RetainOwnershipKind::NS:
5132 handleSimpleAttributeOrDiagnose<NSConsumedAttr>(
5133 *this, VD, SR, SpellingIndex, isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(VD->getType()),
5134
5135 // These attributes are normally just advisory, but in ARC, ns_consumed
5136 // is significant. Allow non-dependent code to contain inappropriate
5137 // attributes even in ARC, but require template instantiations to be
5138 // set up correctly.
5139 ((IsTemplateInstantiation && getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
5140 ? diag::err_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type
5141 : diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type),
5142 /*ExtraArgs=*/SR, "ns_consumed", /*objc pointers*/ 0);
5143 return;
5144 case RetainOwnershipKind::CF:
5145 handleSimpleAttributeOrDiagnose<CFConsumedAttr>(
5146 *this, VD, SR, SpellingIndex,
5147 isValidSubjectOfCFAttribute(VD->getType()),
5148 diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type,
5149 /*ExtraArgs=*/SR, "cf_consumed", /*pointers*/1);
5150 return;
5151 }
5152}
5153
5154static Sema::RetainOwnershipKind
5155parsedAttrToRetainOwnershipKind(const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5156 switch (AL.getKind()) {
5157 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFConsumed:
5158 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
5159 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
5160 return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::CF;
5161 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSConsumesThis:
5162 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSConsumed:
5163 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
5164 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
5165 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetainedOnZero:
5166 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetainedOnNonZero:
5167 return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::OS;
5168 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSConsumesSelf:
5169 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSConsumed:
5170 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
5171 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
5172 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
5173 return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::NS;
5174 default:
5175 llvm_unreachable("Wrong argument supplied");
5176 }
5177}
5178
5179bool Sema::checkNSReturnsRetainedReturnType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType QT) {
5180 if (isValidSubjectOfNSReturnsRetainedAttribute(QT))
5181 return false;
5182
5183 Diag(Loc, diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type)
5184 << "'ns_returns_retained'" << 0 << 0;
5185 return true;
5186}
5187
5188/// \return whether the parameter is a pointer to OSObject pointer.
5189static bool isValidOSObjectOutParameter(const Decl *D) {
5190 const auto *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(D);
5191 if (!PVD)
5192 return false;
5193 QualType QT = PVD->getType();
5194 QualType PT = QT->getPointeeType();
5195 return !PT.isNull() && isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(PT);
5196}
5197
5198static void handleXReturnsXRetainedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5199 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5200 QualType ReturnType;
5201 Sema::RetainOwnershipKind K = parsedAttrToRetainOwnershipKind(AL);
5202
5203 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
5204 ReturnType = MD->getReturnType();
5205 } else if (S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && hasDeclarator(D) &&
5206 (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained)) {
5207 return; // ignore: was handled as a type attribute
5208 } else if (const auto *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D)) {
5209 ReturnType = PD->getType();
5210 } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
5211 ReturnType = FD->getReturnType();
5212 } else if (const auto *Param = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
5213 // Attributes on parameters are used for out-parameters,
5214 // passed as pointers-to-pointers.
5215 unsigned DiagID = K == Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::CF
5216 ? /*pointer-to-CF-pointer*/2
5217 : /*pointer-to-OSObject-pointer*/3;
5218 ReturnType = Param->getType()->getPointeeType();
5219 if (ReturnType.isNull()) {
5220 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type)
5221 << AL << DiagID << AL.getRange();
5222 return;
5223 }
5224 } else if (AL.isUsedAsTypeAttr()) {
5225 return;
5226 } else {
5227 AttributeDeclKind ExpectedDeclKind;
5228 switch (AL.getKind()) {
5229 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid ownership attribute");
5230 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
5231 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
5232 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
5233 ExpectedDeclKind = ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
5234 break;
5235
5236 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
5237 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
5238 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
5239 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
5240 ExpectedDeclKind = ExpectedFunctionMethodOrParameter;
5241 break;
5242 }
5243 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5244 << AL.getRange() << AL << ExpectedDeclKind;
5245 return;
5246 }
5247
5248 bool TypeOK;
5249 bool Cf;
5250 unsigned ParmDiagID = 2; // Pointer-to-CF-pointer
5251 switch (AL.getKind()) {
5252 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid ownership attribute");
5253 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
5254 TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfNSReturnsRetainedAttribute(ReturnType);
5255 Cf = false;
5256 break;
5257
5258 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
5259 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
5260 TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(ReturnType);
5261 Cf = false;
5262 break;
5263
5264 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
5265 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
5266 TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfCFAttribute(ReturnType);
5267 Cf = true;
5268 break;
5269
5270 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
5271 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
5272 TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(ReturnType);
5273 Cf = true;
5274 ParmDiagID = 3; // Pointer-to-OSObject-pointer
5275 break;
5276 }
5277
5278 if (!TypeOK) {
5279 if (AL.isUsedAsTypeAttr())
5280 return;
5281
5282 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
5283 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type)
5284 << AL << ParmDiagID << AL.getRange();
5285 } else {
5286 // Needs to be kept in sync with warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type.
5287 enum : unsigned {
5288 Function,
5289 Method,
5290 Property
5291 } SubjectKind = Function;
5292 if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
5293 SubjectKind = Method;
5294 else if (isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D))
5295 SubjectKind = Property;
5296 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type)
5297 << AL << SubjectKind << Cf << AL.getRange();
5298 }
5299 return;
5300 }
5301
5302 switch (AL.getKind()) {
5303 default:
5304 llvm_unreachable("invalid ownership attribute");
5305 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
5306 handleSimpleAttribute<NSReturnsAutoreleasedAttr>(S, D, AL);
5307 return;
5308 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
5309 handleSimpleAttribute<CFReturnsNotRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
5310 return;
5311 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
5312 handleSimpleAttribute<NSReturnsNotRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
5313 return;
5314 case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
5315 handleSimpleAttribute<CFReturnsRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
5316 return;
5317 case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
5318 handleSimpleAttribute<NSReturnsRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
5319 return;
5320 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
5321 handleSimpleAttribute<OSReturnsRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
5322 return;
5323 case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
5324 handleSimpleAttribute<OSReturnsNotRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
5325 return;
5326 };
5327}
5328
5329static void handleObjCReturnsInnerPointerAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5330 const ParsedAttr &Attrs) {
5331 const int EP_ObjCMethod = 1;
5332 const int EP_ObjCProperty = 2;
5333
5334 SourceLocation loc = Attrs.getLoc();
5335 QualType resultType;
5336 if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
5337 resultType = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)->getReturnType();
5338 else
5339 resultType = cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D)->getType();
5340
5341 if (!resultType->isReferenceType() &&
5342 (!resultType->isPointerType() || resultType->isObjCRetainableType())) {
5343 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type)
5344 << SourceRange(loc) << Attrs
5345 << (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) ? EP_ObjCMethod : EP_ObjCProperty)
5346 << /*non-retainable pointer*/ 2;
5347
5348 // Drop the attribute.
5349 return;
5350 }
5351
5352 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCReturnsInnerPointerAttr(
5353 Attrs.getRange(), S.Context, Attrs.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5354}
5355
5356static void handleObjCRequiresSuperAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5357 const ParsedAttr &Attrs) {
5358 const auto *Method = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
5359
5360 const DeclContext *DC = Method->getDeclContext();
5361 if (const auto *PDecl = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCProtocolDecl>(DC)) {
5362 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_objc_requires_super_protocol) << Attrs
5363 << 0;
5364 S.Diag(PDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_protocol_decl);
5365 return;
5366 }
5367 if (Method->getMethodFamily() == OMF_dealloc) {
5368 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_objc_requires_super_protocol) << Attrs
5369 << 1;
5370 return;
5371 }
5372
5373 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCRequiresSuperAttr(
5374 Attrs.getRange(), S.Context, Attrs.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5375}
5376
5377static void handleObjCBridgeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5378 IdentifierLoc *Parm = AL.isArgIdent(0) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(0) : nullptr;
5379
5380 if (!Parm) {
5381 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_not_id) << AL << 0;
5382 return;
5383 }
5384
5385 // Typedefs only allow objc_bridge(id) and have some additional checking.
5386 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
5387 if (!Parm->Ident->isStr("id")) {
5388 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_typedef_not_id) << AL;
5389 return;
5390 }
5391
5392 // Only allow 'cv void *'.
5393 QualType T = TD->getUnderlyingType();
5394 if (!T->isVoidPointerType()) {
5395 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_typedef_not_void_pointer);
5396 return;
5397 }
5398 }
5399
5400 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5401 ObjCBridgeAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Parm->Ident,
5402 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5403}
5404
5405static void handleObjCBridgeMutableAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5406 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5407 IdentifierLoc *Parm = AL.isArgIdent(0) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(0) : nullptr;
5408
5409 if (!Parm) {
5410 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_not_id) << AL << 0;
5411 return;
5412 }
5413
5414 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5415 ObjCBridgeMutableAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Parm->Ident,
5416 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5417}
5418
5419static void handleObjCBridgeRelatedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5420 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5421 IdentifierInfo *RelatedClass =
5422 AL.isArgIdent(0) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident : nullptr;
5423 if (!RelatedClass) {
5424 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_not_id) << AL << 0;
5425 return;
5426 }
5427 IdentifierInfo *ClassMethod =
5428 AL.getArgAsIdent(1) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(1)->Ident : nullptr;
5429 IdentifierInfo *InstanceMethod =
5430 AL.getArgAsIdent(2) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(2)->Ident : nullptr;
5431 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5432 ObjCBridgeRelatedAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, RelatedClass,
5433 ClassMethod, InstanceMethod,
5434 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5435}
5436
5437static void handleObjCDesignatedInitializer(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5438 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5439 DeclContext *Ctx = D->getDeclContext();
5440
5441 // This attribute can only be applied to methods in interfaces or class
5442 // extensions.
5443 if (!isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(Ctx) &&
5444 !(isa<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx) &&
5445 cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx)->IsClassExtension())) {
5446 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_designated_init_attr_non_init);
5447 return;
5448 }
5449
5450 ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFace;
5451 if (auto *CatDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx))
5452 IFace = CatDecl->getClassInterface();
5453 else
5454 IFace = cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(Ctx);
5455
5456 if (!IFace)
5457 return;
5458
5459 IFace->setHasDesignatedInitializers();
5460 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5461 ObjCDesignatedInitializerAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
5462 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5463}
5464
5465static void handleObjCRuntimeName(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5466 StringRef MetaDataName;
5467 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, MetaDataName))
5468 return;
5469 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5470 ObjCRuntimeNameAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
5471 MetaDataName,
5472 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5473}
5474
5475// When a user wants to use objc_boxable with a union or struct
5476// but they don't have access to the declaration (legacy/third-party code)
5477// then they can 'enable' this feature with a typedef:
5478// typedef struct __attribute((objc_boxable)) legacy_struct legacy_struct;
5479static void handleObjCBoxable(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5480 bool notify = false;
5481
5482 auto *RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(D);
5483 if (RD && RD->getDefinition()) {
5484 RD = RD->getDefinition();
5485 notify = true;
5486 }
5487
5488 if (RD) {
5489 ObjCBoxableAttr *BoxableAttr = ::new (S.Context)
5490 ObjCBoxableAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
5491 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
5492 RD->addAttr(BoxableAttr);
5493 if (notify) {
5494 // we need to notify ASTReader/ASTWriter about
5495 // modification of existing declaration
5496 if (ASTMutationListener *L = S.getASTMutationListener())
5497 L->AddedAttributeToRecord(BoxableAttr, RD);
5498 }
5499 }
5500}
5501
5502static void handleObjCOwnershipAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5503 if (hasDeclarator(D)) return;
5504
5505 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5506 << AL.getRange() << AL << ExpectedVariable;
5507}
5508
5509static void handleObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5510 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5511 const auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D);
5512 QualType QT = VD->getType();
5513
5514 if (!QT->isDependentType() &&
5515 !QT->isObjCLifetimeType()) {
5516 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_objc_precise_lifetime_bad_type)
5517 << QT;
5518 return;
5519 }
5520
5521 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime = QT.getObjCLifetime();
5522
5523 // If we have no lifetime yet, check the lifetime we're presumably
5524 // going to infer.
5525 if (Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_None && !QT->isDependentType())
5526 Lifetime = QT->getObjCARCImplicitLifetime();
5527
5528 switch (Lifetime) {
5529 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
5530 assert(QT->isDependentType() &&
5531 "didn't infer lifetime for non-dependent type?");
5532 break;
5533
5534 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak: // meaningful
5535 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong: // meaningful
5536 break;
5537
5538 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
5539 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
5540 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_objc_precise_lifetime_meaningless)
5541 << (Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing);
5542 break;
5543 }
5544
5545 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5546 ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
5547 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5548}
5549
5550//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5551// Microsoft specific attribute handlers.
5552//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5553
5554UuidAttr *Sema::mergeUuidAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
5555 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex, StringRef Uuid) {
5556 if (const auto *UA = D->getAttr<UuidAttr>()) {
5557 if (UA->getGuid().equals_lower(Uuid))
5558 return nullptr;
5559 Diag(UA->getLocation(), diag::err_mismatched_uuid);
5560 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_previous_uuid);
5561 D->dropAttr<UuidAttr>();
5562 }
5563
5564 return ::new (Context) UuidAttr(Range, Context, Uuid, AttrSpellingListIndex);
5565}
5566
5567static void handleUuidAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5568 if (!S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus) {
5569 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_supported_in_lang)
5570 << AL << AttributeLangSupport::C;
5571 return;
5572 }
5573
5574 StringRef StrRef;
5575 SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
5576 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, StrRef, &LiteralLoc))
5577 return;
5578
5579 // GUID format is "XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX" or
5580 // "{XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX}", normalize to the former.
5581 if (StrRef.size() == 38 && StrRef.front() == '{' && StrRef.back() == '}')
5582 StrRef = StrRef.drop_front().drop_back();
5583
5584 // Validate GUID length.
5585 if (StrRef.size() != 36) {
5586 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
5587 return;
5588 }
5589
5590 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; ++i) {
5591 if (i == 8 || i == 13 || i == 18 || i == 23) {
5592 if (StrRef[i] != '-') {
5593 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
5594 return;
5595 }
5596 } else if (!isHexDigit(StrRef[i])) {
5597 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
5598 return;
5599 }
5600 }
5601
5602 // FIXME: It'd be nice to also emit a fixit removing uuid(...) (and, if it's
5603 // the only thing in the [] list, the [] too), and add an insertion of
5604 // __declspec(uuid(...)). But sadly, neither the SourceLocs of the commas
5605 // separating attributes nor of the [ and the ] are in the AST.
5606 // Cf "SourceLocations of attribute list delimiters - [[ ... , ... ]] etc"
5607 // on cfe-dev.
5608 if (AL.isMicrosoftAttribute()) // Check for [uuid(...)] spelling.
5609 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_atl_uuid_deprecated);
5610
5611 UuidAttr *UA = S.mergeUuidAttr(D, AL.getRange(),
5612 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex(), StrRef);
5613 if (UA)
5614 D->addAttr(UA);
5615}
5616
5617static void handleMSInheritanceAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5618 if (!S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus) {
5619 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_supported_in_lang)
5620 << AL << AttributeLangSupport::C;
5621 return;
5622 }
5623 MSInheritanceAttr *IA = S.mergeMSInheritanceAttr(
5624 D, AL.getRange(), /*BestCase=*/true,
5625 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex(),
5626 (MSInheritanceAttr::Spelling)AL.getSemanticSpelling());
5627 if (IA) {
5628 D->addAttr(IA);
5629 S.Consumer.AssignInheritanceModel(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D));
5630 }
5631}
5632
5633static void handleDeclspecThreadAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5634 const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
5635 if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().isTLSSupported()) {
5636 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_thread_unsupported);
5637 return;
5638 }
5639 if (VD->getTSCSpec() != TSCS_unspecified) {
5640 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_declspec_thread_on_thread_variable);
5641 return;
5642 }
5643 if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
5644 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_thread_non_global) << "__declspec(thread)";
5645 return;
5646 }
5647 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ThreadAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
5648 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5649}
5650
5651static void handleAbiTagAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5652 SmallVector<StringRef, 4> Tags;
5653 for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
5654 StringRef Tag;
5655 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, Tag))
5656 return;
5657 Tags.push_back(Tag);
5658 }
5659
5660 if (const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(D)) {
5661 if (!NS->isInline()) {
5662 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attr_abi_tag_namespace) << 0;
5663 return;
5664 }
5665 if (NS->isAnonymousNamespace()) {
5666 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attr_abi_tag_namespace) << 1;
5667 return;
5668 }
5669 if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
5670 Tags.push_back(NS->getName());
5671 } else if (!checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
5672 return;
5673
5674 // Store tags sorted and without duplicates.
5675 llvm::sort(Tags);
5676 Tags.erase(std::unique(Tags.begin(), Tags.end()), Tags.end());
5677
5678 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5679 AbiTagAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Tags.data(), Tags.size(),
5680 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5681}
5682
5683static void handleARMInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5684 // Check the attribute arguments.
5685 if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
5686 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_too_many_arguments) << AL << 1;
5687 return;
5688 }
5689
5690 StringRef Str;
5691 SourceLocation ArgLoc;
5692
5693 if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
5694 Str = "";
5695 else if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))
5696 return;
5697
5698 ARMInterruptAttr::InterruptType Kind;
5699 if (!ARMInterruptAttr::ConvertStrToInterruptType(Str, Kind)) {
5700 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << Str
5701 << ArgLoc;
5702 return;
5703 }
5704
5705 unsigned Index = AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex();
5706 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5707 ARMInterruptAttr(AL.getLoc(), S.Context, Kind, Index));
5708}
5709
5710static void handleMSP430InterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5711 // MSP430 'interrupt' attribute is applied to
5712 // a function with no parameters and void return type.
5713 if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {
5714 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5715 << "'interrupt'" << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
5716 return;
5717 }
5718
5719 if (hasFunctionProto(D) && getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) != 0) {
5720 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
5721 << /*MSP430*/ 1 << 0;
5722 return;
5723 }
5724
5725 if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
5726 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
5727 << /*MSP430*/ 1 << 1;
5728 return;
5729 }
5730
5731 // The attribute takes one integer argument.
5732 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
5733 return;
5734
5735 if (!AL.isArgExpr(0)) {
5736 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
5737 << AL << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant;
5738 return;
5739 }
5740
5741 Expr *NumParamsExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
5742 llvm::APSInt NumParams(32);
5743 if (!NumParamsExpr->isIntegerConstantExpr(NumParams, S.Context)) {
5744 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
5745 << AL << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
5746 << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
5747 return;
5748 }
5749 // The argument should be in range 0..63.
5750 unsigned Num = NumParams.getLimitedValue(255);
5751 if (Num > 63) {
5752 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
5753 << AL << (int)NumParams.getSExtValue()
5754 << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
5755 return;
5756 }
5757
5758 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5759 MSP430InterruptAttr(AL.getLoc(), S.Context, Num,
5760 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5761 D->addAttr(UsedAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context));
5762}
5763
5764static void handleMipsInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5765 // Only one optional argument permitted.
5766 if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
5767 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_too_many_arguments) << AL << 1;
5768 return;
5769 }
5770
5771 StringRef Str;
5772 SourceLocation ArgLoc;
5773
5774 if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
5775 Str = "";
5776 else if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))
5777 return;
5778
5779 // Semantic checks for a function with the 'interrupt' attribute for MIPS:
5780 // a) Must be a function.
5781 // b) Must have no parameters.
5782 // c) Must have the 'void' return type.
5783 // d) Cannot have the 'mips16' attribute, as that instruction set
5784 // lacks the 'eret' instruction.
5785 // e) The attribute itself must either have no argument or one of the
5786 // valid interrupt types, see [MipsInterruptDocs].
5787
5788 if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {
5789 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5790 << "'interrupt'" << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
5791 return;
5792 }
5793
5794 if (hasFunctionProto(D) && getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) != 0) {
5795 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
5796 << /*MIPS*/ 0 << 0;
5797 return;
5798 }
5799
5800 if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
5801 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
5802 << /*MIPS*/ 0 << 1;
5803 return;
5804 }
5805
5806 if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<Mips16Attr>(S, D, AL))
5807 return;
5808
5809 MipsInterruptAttr::InterruptType Kind;
5810 if (!MipsInterruptAttr::ConvertStrToInterruptType(Str, Kind)) {
5811 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
5812 << AL << "'" + std::string(Str) + "'";
5813 return;
5814 }
5815
5816 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) MipsInterruptAttr(
5817 AL.getLoc(), S.Context, Kind, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5818}
5819
5820static void handleAnyX86InterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5821 // Semantic checks for a function with the 'interrupt' attribute.
5822 // a) Must be a function.
5823 // b) Must have the 'void' return type.
5824 // c) Must take 1 or 2 arguments.
5825 // d) The 1st argument must be a pointer.
5826 // e) The 2nd argument (if any) must be an unsigned integer.
5827 if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D) || !hasFunctionProto(D) || isInstanceMethod(D) ||
5828 CXXMethodDecl::isStaticOverloadedOperator(
5829 cast<NamedDecl>(D)->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator())) {
5830 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5831 << AL << ExpectedFunctionWithProtoType;
5832 return;
5833 }
5834 // Interrupt handler must have void return type.
5835 if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
5836 S.Diag(getFunctionOrMethodResultSourceRange(D).getBegin(),
5837 diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
5838 << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
5839 ? 0
5840 : 1)
5841 << 0;
5842 return;
5843 }
5844 // Interrupt handler must have 1 or 2 parameters.
5845 unsigned NumParams = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D);
5846 if (NumParams < 1 || NumParams > 2) {
5847 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
5848 << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
5849 ? 0
5850 : 1)
5851 << 1;
5852 return;
5853 }
5854 // The first argument must be a pointer.
5855 if (!getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, 0)->isPointerType()) {
5856 S.Diag(getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 0).getBegin(),
5857 diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
5858 << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
5859 ? 0
5860 : 1)
5861 << 2;
5862 return;
5863 }
5864 // The second argument, if present, must be an unsigned integer.
5865 unsigned TypeSize =
5866 S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86_64
5867 ? 64
5868 : 32;
5869 if (NumParams == 2 &&
5870 (!getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, 1)->isUnsignedIntegerType() ||
5871 S.Context.getTypeSize(getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, 1)) != TypeSize)) {
5872 S.Diag(getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 1).getBegin(),
5873 diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
5874 << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
5875 ? 0
5876 : 1)
5877 << 3 << S.Context.getIntTypeForBitwidth(TypeSize, /*Signed=*/false);
5878 return;
5879 }
5880 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AnyX86InterruptAttr(
5881 AL.getLoc(), S.Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
5882 D->addAttr(UsedAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context));
5883}
5884
5885static void handleAVRInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5886 if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {
5887 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5888 << "'interrupt'" << ExpectedFunction;
5889 return;
5890 }
5891
5892 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(S, AL, 0))
5893 return;
5894
5895 handleSimpleAttribute<AVRInterruptAttr>(S, D, AL);
5896}

5901 << "'signal'" << ExpectedFunction;
5902 return;

5906 return;

5911static void handleWebAssemblyImportModuleAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5912 if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {

5915 return;

5919 if (FD->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {

5921 return;

5925 SourceLocation ArgLoc;

5927 return;

5931 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));

5934static void handleWebAssemblyImportNameAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5935 if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {
5936 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5937 << "'import_name'" << ExpectedFunction;
5938 return;
5939 }
5940
5941 auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
5942 if (FD->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {
5943 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_alias_is_definition) << FD << 0;
5944 return;
5945 }
5946

5948 SourceLocation ArgLoc;
5949 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))

5956
5957static void handleRISCVInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5958 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5959 // Warn about repeated attributes.
5960 if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<RISCVInterruptAttr>()) {
5961 S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(),
5962 diag::warn_riscv_repeated_interrupt_attribute);
5963 S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::note_riscv_repeated_interrupt_attribute);
5964 return;
5965 }
5966
5967 // Check the attribute argument. Argument is optional.
5968 if (!checkAttributeAtMostNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
5969 return;
5970
5971 StringRef Str;
5972 SourceLocation ArgLoc;
5973
5974 // 'machine'is the default interrupt mode.
5975 if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
5976 Str = "machine";
5977 else if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))
5978 return;
5979
5980 // Semantic checks for a function with the 'interrupt' attribute:
5981 // - Must be a function.
5982 // - Must have no parameters.
5983 // - Must have the 'void' return type.
5984 // - The attribute itself must either have no argument or one of the
5985 // valid interrupt types, see [RISCVInterruptDocs].
5986
5987 if (D->getFunctionType() == nullptr) {
5988 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5989 << "'interrupt'" << ExpectedFunction;
5990 return;
5991 }
5992
5993 if (hasFunctionProto(D) && getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) != 0) {
5994 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
5995 << /*RISC-V*/ 2 << 0;
5996 return;
5997 }
5998
5999 if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
6000 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
6001 << /*RISC-V*/ 2 << 1;
6002 return;
6003 }
6004
6005 RISCVInterruptAttr::InterruptType Kind;
6006 if (!RISCVInterruptAttr::ConvertStrToInterruptType(Str, Kind)) {
6007 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << Str
6008 << ArgLoc;
6009 return;
6010 }
6011
6012 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) RISCVInterruptAttr(
6013 AL.getLoc(), S.Context, Kind, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6014}
6015
6016static void handleInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6017 // Dispatch the interrupt attribute based on the current target.
6018 switch (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch()) {
6019 case llvm::Triple::msp430:
6020 handleMSP430InterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
6021 break;
6022 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
6023 case llvm::Triple::mips:
6024 handleMipsInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
6025 break;
6026 case llvm::Triple::x86:
6027 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
6028 handleAnyX86InterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
6029 break;
6030 case llvm::Triple::avr:
6031 handleAVRInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
6032 break;
6033 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
6034 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
6035 handleRISCVInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
6036 break;
6037 default:
6038 handleARMInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
6039 break;
6040 }
6041}
6042
6043static bool
6044checkAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeArguments(Sema &S, Expr *MinExpr, Expr *MaxExpr,
6045 const AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr &Attr) {
6046 // Accept template arguments for now as they depend on something else.
6047 // We'll get to check them when they eventually get instantiated.
6048 if (MinExpr->isValueDependent() || MaxExpr->isValueDependent())
6049 return false;
6050
6051 uint32_t Min = 0;
6052 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MinExpr, Min, 0))
6053 return true;
6054
6055 uint32_t Max = 0;
6056 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MaxExpr, Max, 1))
6057 return true;
6058
6059 if (Min == 0 && Max != 0) {
6060 S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
6061 << &Attr << 0;
6062 return true;
6063 }
6064 if (Min > Max) {
6065 S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
6066 << &Attr << 1;
6067 return true;
6068 }
6069
6070 return false;
6071}
6072
6073void Sema::addAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(SourceRange AttrRange, Decl *D,
6074 Expr *MinExpr, Expr *MaxExpr,
6075 unsigned SpellingListIndex) {
6076 AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr TmpAttr(AttrRange, Context, MinExpr, MaxExpr,
6077 SpellingListIndex);
6078
6079 if (checkAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeArguments(*this, MinExpr, MaxExpr, TmpAttr))
6080 return;
6081
6082 D->addAttr(::new (Context) AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(
6083 AttrRange, Context, MinExpr, MaxExpr, SpellingListIndex));
6084}
6085
6086static void handleAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6087 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6088 Expr *MinExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
6089 Expr *MaxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
6090
6091 S.addAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(AL.getRange(), D, MinExpr, MaxExpr,
6092 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
6093}
6094
6095static bool checkAMDGPUWavesPerEUArguments(Sema &S, Expr *MinExpr,
6096 Expr *MaxExpr,
6097 const AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr &Attr) {
6098 if (S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(MinExpr) ||
6099 (MaxExpr && S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(MaxExpr)))
6100 return true;
6101
6102 // Accept template arguments for now as they depend on something else.
6103 // We'll get to check them when they eventually get instantiated.
6104 if (MinExpr->isValueDependent() || (MaxExpr && MaxExpr->isValueDependent()))
6105 return false;
6106
6107 uint32_t Min = 0;
6108 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MinExpr, Min, 0))
6109 return true;
6110
6111 uint32_t Max = 0;
6112 if (MaxExpr && !checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MaxExpr, Max, 1))
6113 return true;
6114
6115 if (Min == 0 && Max != 0) {
6116 S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
6117 << &Attr << 0;
6118 return true;
6119 }
6120 if (Max != 0 && Min > Max) {
6121 S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
6122 << &Attr << 1;
6123 return true;
6124 }
6125
6126 return false;
6127}
6128
6129void Sema::addAMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(SourceRange AttrRange, Decl *D,
6130 Expr *MinExpr, Expr *MaxExpr,
6131 unsigned SpellingListIndex) {
6132 AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr TmpAttr(AttrRange, Context, MinExpr, MaxExpr,
6133 SpellingListIndex);
6134
6135 if (checkAMDGPUWavesPerEUArguments(*this, MinExpr, MaxExpr, TmpAttr))
6136 return;
6137
6138 D->addAttr(::new (Context) AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(AttrRange, Context, MinExpr,
6139 MaxExpr, SpellingListIndex));
6140}
6141
6142static void handleAMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6143 if (!checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, 1) ||
6144 !checkAttributeAtMostNumArgs(S, AL, 2))
6145 return;
6146
6147 Expr *MinExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
6148 Expr *MaxExpr = (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) ? AL.getArgAsExpr(1) : nullptr;
6149
6150 S.addAMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(AL.getRange(), D, MinExpr, MaxExpr,
6151 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
6152}
