6165static void handleAMDGPUNumVGPRAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6166 uint32_t NumVGPR = 0;
6167 Expr *NumVGPRExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
6168 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, NumVGPRExpr, NumVGPR))
6169 return;
6170
6171 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
6172 AMDGPUNumVGPRAttr(AL.getLoc(), S.Context, NumVGPR,
6173 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6174}
6175
6176static void handleX86ForceAlignArgPointerAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6177 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6178 // If we try to apply it to a function pointer, don't warn, but don't
6179 // do anything, either. It doesn't matter anyway, because there's nothing
6180 // special about calling a force_align_arg_pointer function.
6181 const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D);
6182 if (VD && VD->getType()->isFunctionPointerType())
6183 return;
6184 // Also don't warn on function pointer typedefs.
6185 const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D);
6186 if (TD && (TD->getUnderlyingType()->isFunctionPointerType() ||
6187 TD->getUnderlyingType()->isFunctionType()))
6188 return;
6189 // Attribute can only be applied to function types.
6190 if (!isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
6191 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6192 << AL << ExpectedFunction;
6193 return;
6194 }
6195
6196 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
6197 X86ForceAlignArgPointerAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
6198 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6199}
6200
6201static void handleLayoutVersion(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6202 uint32_t Version;
6203 Expr *VersionExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
6204 if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), Version))
6205 return;
6206
6207 // TODO: Investigate what happens with the next major version of MSVC.
6208 if (Version != LangOptions::MSVC2015 / 100) {
6209 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
6210 << AL << Version << VersionExpr->getSourceRange();
6211 return;
6212 }
6213
6214 // The attribute expects a "major" version number like 19, but new versions of
6215 // MSVC have moved to updating the "minor", or less significant numbers, so we
6216 // have to multiply by 100 now.
6217 Version *= 100;
6218
6219 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
6220 LayoutVersionAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Version,
6221 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6222}
6223
6224DLLImportAttr *Sema::mergeDLLImportAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
6225 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
6226 if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) {
6227 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << "'dllimport'";
6228 return nullptr;
6229 }
6230
6231 if (D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
6232 return nullptr;
6233
6234 return ::new (Context) DLLImportAttr(Range, Context, AttrSpellingListIndex);
6235}
6236
6237DLLExportAttr *Sema::mergeDLLExportAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range,
6238 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex) {
6239 if (DLLImportAttr *Import = D->getAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
6240 Diag(Import->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << Import;
6241 D->dropAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
6242 }
6243
6244 if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
6245 return nullptr;
6246
6247 return ::new (Context) DLLExportAttr(Range, Context, AttrSpellingListIndex);
6248}
6249
6250static void handleDLLAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &A) {
6251 if (isa<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(D) &&
6252 S.Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
6253 S.Diag(A.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << A;
6254 return;
6255 }
6256
6257 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
6258 if (FD->isInlined() && A.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_DLLImport &&
6259 !S.Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
6260 // MinGW doesn't allow dllimport on inline functions.
6261 S.Diag(A.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored_on_inline)
6262 << A;
6263 return;
6264 }
6265 }
6266
6267 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
6268 if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
6269 MD->getParent()->isLambda()) {
6270 S.Diag(A.getRange().getBegin(), diag::err_attribute_dll_lambda) << A;
6271 return;
6272 }
6273 }
6274
6275 unsigned Index = A.getAttributeSpellingListIndex();
6276 Attr *NewAttr = A.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_DLLExport
6277 ? (Attr *)S.mergeDLLExportAttr(D, A.getRange(), Index)
6278 : (Attr *)S.mergeDLLImportAttr(D, A.getRange(), Index);
6279 if (NewAttr)
6280 D->addAttr(NewAttr);
6281}
6282
6283MSInheritanceAttr *
6284Sema::mergeMSInheritanceAttr(Decl *D, SourceRange Range, bool BestCase,
6285 unsigned AttrSpellingListIndex,
6286 MSInheritanceAttr::Spelling SemanticSpelling) {
6287 if (MSInheritanceAttr *IA = D->getAttr<MSInheritanceAttr>()) {
6288 if (IA->getSemanticSpelling() == SemanticSpelling)
6289 return nullptr;
6290 Diag(IA->getLocation(), diag::err_mismatched_ms_inheritance)
6291 << 1 /*previous declaration*/;
6292 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_previous_ms_inheritance);
6293 D->dropAttr<MSInheritanceAttr>();
6294 }
6295
6296 auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
6297 if (RD->hasDefinition()) {
6298 if (checkMSInheritanceAttrOnDefinition(RD, Range, BestCase,
6299 SemanticSpelling)) {
6300 return nullptr;
6301 }
6302 } else {
6303 if (isa<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
6304 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_ignored_ms_inheritance)
6305 << 1 /*partial specialization*/;
6306 return nullptr;
6307 }
6308 if (RD->getDescribedClassTemplate()) {
6309 Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_ignored_ms_inheritance)
6310 << 0 /*primary template*/;
6311 return nullptr;
6312 }
6313 }
6314
6315 return ::new (Context)
6316 MSInheritanceAttr(Range, Context, BestCase, AttrSpellingListIndex);
6317}
6318
6319static void handleCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6320 // The capability attributes take a single string parameter for the name of
6321 // the capability they represent. The lockable attribute does not take any
6322 // parameters. However, semantically, both attributes represent the same
6323 // concept, and so they use the same semantic attribute. Eventually, the
6324 // lockable attribute will be removed.
6325 //
6326 // For backward compatibility, any capability which has no specified string
6327 // literal will be considered a "mutex."
6328 StringRef N("mutex");
6329 SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
6330 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_Capability &&
6331 !S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, N, &LiteralLoc))
6332 return;
6333
6334 // Currently, there are only two names allowed for a capability: role and
6335 // mutex (case insensitive). Diagnose other capability names.
6336 if (!N.equals_lower("mutex") && !N.equals_lower("role"))
6337 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_invalid_capability_name) << N;
6338
6339 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CapabilityAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, N,
6340 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6341}
6342
6343static void handleAssertCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6344 SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
6345 if (!checkLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
6346 return;
6347
6348 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AssertCapabilityAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context,
6349 Args.data(), Args.size(),
6350 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6351}
6352
6353static void handleAcquireCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6354 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6355 SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
6356 if (!checkLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
6357 return;
6358
6359 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AcquireCapabilityAttr(AL.getRange(),
6360 S.Context,
6361 Args.data(), Args.size(),
6362 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6363}
6364
6365static void handleTryAcquireCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6366 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6367 SmallVector<Expr*, 2> Args;
6368 if (!checkTryLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
6369 return;
6370
6371 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) TryAcquireCapabilityAttr(AL.getRange(),
6372 S.Context,
6373 AL.getArgAsExpr(0),
6374 Args.data(),
6375 Args.size(),
6376 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6377}
6378
6379static void handleReleaseCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6380 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6381 // Check that all arguments are lockable objects.
6382 SmallVector<Expr *, 1> Args;
6383 checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args, 0, true);
6384
6385 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ReleaseCapabilityAttr(
6386 AL.getRange(), S.Context, Args.data(), Args.size(),
6387 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6388}
6389
6390static void handleRequiresCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6391 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6392 if (!checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
6393 return;
6394
6395 // check that all arguments are lockable objects
6396 SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
6397 checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args);
6398 if (Args.empty())
6399 return;
6400
6401 RequiresCapabilityAttr *RCA = ::new (S.Context)
6402 RequiresCapabilityAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Args.data(),
6403 Args.size(), AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
6404
6405 D->addAttr(RCA);
6406}
6407
6408static void handleDeprecatedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6409 if (const auto *NSD = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(D)) {
6410 if (NSD->isAnonymousNamespace()) {
6411 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_deprecated_anonymous_namespace);
6412 // Do not want to attach the attribute to the namespace because that will
6413 // cause confusing diagnostic reports for uses of declarations within the
6414 // namespace.
6415 return;
6416 }
6417 }
6418
6419 // Handle the cases where the attribute has a text message.
6420 StringRef Str, Replacement;
6421 if (AL.isArgExpr(0) && AL.getArgAsExpr(0) &&
6422 !S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
6423 return;
6424
6425 // Only support a single optional message for Declspec and CXX11.
6426 if (AL.isDeclspecAttribute() || AL.isCXX11Attribute())
6427 checkAttributeAtMostNumArgs(S, AL, 1);
6428 else if (AL.isArgExpr(1) && AL.getArgAsExpr(1) &&
6429 !S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 1, Replacement))
6430 return;
6431
6432 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 && AL.isCXX11Attribute() && !AL.isGNUScope())
6433 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_cxx14_attr) << AL;
6434
6435 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
6436 DeprecatedAttr(AL.getRange(), S.Context, Str, Replacement,
6437 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6438}
6439
6440static bool isGlobalVar(const Decl *D) {
6441 if (const auto *S = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
6442 return S->hasGlobalStorage();
6443 return false;
6444}
6445
6446static void handleNoSanitizeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6447 if (!checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, 1))
6448 return;
6449
6450 std::vector<StringRef> Sanitizers;
6451
6452 for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
6453 StringRef SanitizerName;
6454 SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
6455
6456 if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, SanitizerName, &LiteralLoc))
6457 return;
6458
6459 if (parseSanitizerValue(SanitizerName, /*AllowGroups=*/true) ==
6460 SanitizerMask())
6461 S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unknown_sanitizer_ignored) << SanitizerName;
6462 else if (isGlobalVar(D) && SanitizerName != "address")
6463 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6464 << AL << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
6465 Sanitizers.push_back(SanitizerName);
6466 }
6467
6468 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NoSanitizeAttr(
6469 AL.getRange(), S.Context, Sanitizers.data(), Sanitizers.size(),
6470 AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6471}
6472
6473static void handleNoSanitizeSpecificAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6474 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6475 StringRef AttrName = AL.getName()->getName();
6476 normalizeName(AttrName);
6477 StringRef SanitizerName = llvm::StringSwitch<StringRef>(AttrName)
6478 .Case("no_address_safety_analysis", "address")
6479 .Case("no_sanitize_address", "address")
6480 .Case("no_sanitize_thread", "thread")
6481 .Case("no_sanitize_memory", "memory");
6482 if (isGlobalVar(D) && SanitizerName != "address")
6483 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6484 << AL << ExpectedFunction;
6485
6486 // FIXME: Rather than create a NoSanitizeSpecificAttr, this creates a
6487 // NoSanitizeAttr object; but we need to calculate the correct spelling list
6488 // index rather than incorrectly assume the index for NoSanitizeSpecificAttr
6489 // has the same spellings as the index for NoSanitizeAttr. We don't have a
6490 // general way to "translate" between the two, so this hack attempts to work
6491 // around the issue with hard-coded indicies. This is critical for calling
6492 // getSpelling() or prettyPrint() on the resulting semantic attribute object
6493 // without failing assertions.
6494 unsigned TranslatedSpellingIndex = 0;
6495 if (AL.isC2xAttribute() || AL.isCXX11Attribute())
6496 TranslatedSpellingIndex = 1;
6497
6498 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NoSanitizeAttr(
6499 AL.getRange(), S.Context, &SanitizerName, 1, TranslatedSpellingIndex));
6500}
6501
6502static void handleInternalLinkageAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6503 if (InternalLinkageAttr *Internal = S.mergeInternalLinkageAttr(D, AL))
6504 D->addAttr(Internal);
6505}
6506
6507static void handleOpenCLNoSVMAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6508 if (S.LangOpts.OpenCLVersion != 200)
6509 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_opencl_version)
6510 << AL << "2.0" << 0;
6511 else
6512 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_opencl_attr_deprecated_ignored) << AL
6513 << "2.0";
6514}
6515
6516/// Handles semantic checking for features that are common to all attributes,
6517/// such as checking whether a parameter was properly specified, or the correct
6518/// number of arguments were passed, etc.
6519static bool handleCommonAttributeFeatures(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6520 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6521 // Several attributes carry different semantics than the parsing requires, so
6522 // those are opted out of the common argument checks.
6523 //
6524 // We also bail on unknown and ignored attributes because those are handled
6525 // as part of the target-specific handling logic.
6526 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::UnknownAttribute)
6527 return false;
6528 // Check whether the attribute requires specific language extensions to be
6529 // enabled.
6530 if (!AL.diagnoseLangOpts(S))
6531 return true;
6532 // Check whether the attribute appertains to the given subject.
6533 if (!AL.diagnoseAppertainsTo(S, D))
6534 return true;
6535 if (AL.hasCustomParsing())
6536 return false;
6537
6538 if (AL.getMinArgs() == AL.getMaxArgs()) {
6539 // If there are no optional arguments, then checking for the argument count
6540 // is trivial.
6541 if (!checkAttributeNumArgs(S, AL, AL.getMinArgs()))
6542 return true;
6543 } else {
6544 // There are optional arguments, so checking is slightly more involved.
6545 if (AL.getMinArgs() &&
6546 !checkAttributeAtLeastNumArgs(S, AL, AL.getMinArgs()))
6547 return true;
6548 else if (!AL.hasVariadicArg() && AL.getMaxArgs() &&
6549 !checkAttributeAtMostNumArgs(S, AL, AL.getMaxArgs()))
6550 return true;
6551 }
6552
6553 if (S.CheckAttrTarget(AL))
6554 return true;
6555
6556 return false;
6557}
6558
6559static void handleOpenCLAccessAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6560 if (D->isInvalidDecl())
6561 return;
6562
6563 // Check if there is only one access qualifier.
6564 if (D->hasAttr<OpenCLAccessAttr>()) {
6565 if (D->getAttr<OpenCLAccessAttr>()->getSemanticSpelling() ==
6566 AL.getSemanticSpelling()) {
6567 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_declspec)
6568 << AL.getName()->getName() << AL.getRange();
6569 } else {
6570 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_opencl_multiple_access_qualifiers)
6571 << D->getSourceRange();
6572 D->setInvalidDecl(true);
6573 return;
6574 }
6575 }
6576
6577 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.6 - read_write can be used for image types to specify that an
6578 // image object can be read and written.
6579 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.6 - A kernel cannot read from and write to the same pipe
6580 // object. Using the read_write (or __read_write) qualifier with the pipe
6581 // qualifier is a compilation error.
6582 if (const auto *PDecl = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
6583 const Type *DeclTy = PDecl->getType().getCanonicalType().getTypePtr();
6584 if (AL.getName()->getName().find("read_write") != StringRef::npos) {
6585 if ((!S.getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus &&
6586 S.getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion < 200) ||
6587 DeclTy->isPipeType()) {
6588 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_read_write)
6589 << AL << PDecl->getType() << DeclTy->isImageType();
6590 D->setInvalidDecl(true);
6591 return;
6592 }
6593 }
6594 }
6595
6596 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) OpenCLAccessAttr(
6597 AL.getRange(), S.Context, AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()));
6598}
6599
6600static void handleDestroyAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &A) {
6601 if (!cast<VarDecl>(D)->hasGlobalStorage()) {
6602 S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_destroy_attr_on_non_static_var)
6603 << (A.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AlwaysDestroy);
6604 return;
6605 }
6606
6607 if (A.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AlwaysDestroy)
6608 handleSimpleAttributeWithExclusions<AlwaysDestroyAttr, NoDestroyAttr>(S, D, A);
6609 else
6610 handleSimpleAttributeWithExclusions<NoDestroyAttr, AlwaysDestroyAttr>(S, D, A);
6611}
6612
6613static void handleUninitializedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6614 assert(cast<VarDecl>(D)->getStorageDuration() == SD_Automatic &&
6615 "uninitialized is only valid on automatic duration variables");
6616 unsigned Index = AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex();
6617 D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
6618 UninitializedAttr(AL.getLoc(), S.Context, Index));
6619}
6620
6621static bool tryMakeVariablePseudoStrong(Sema &S, VarDecl *VD,
6622 bool DiagnoseFailure) {
6623 QualType Ty = VD->getType();
6624 if (!Ty->isObjCRetainableType()) {
6625 if (DiagnoseFailure) {
6626 S.Diag(VD->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ignored_objc_externally_retained)
6627 << 0;
6628 }
6629 return false;
6630 }
6631
6632 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime LifetimeQual = Ty.getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime();
6633
6634 // Sema::inferObjCARCLifetime must run after processing decl attributes
6635 // (because __block lowers to an attribute), so if the lifetime hasn't been
6636 // explicitly specified, infer it locally now.
6637 if (LifetimeQual == Qualifiers::OCL_None)
6638 LifetimeQual = Ty->getObjCARCImplicitLifetime();
6639
6640 // The attributes only really makes sense for __strong variables; ignore any
6641 // attempts to annotate a parameter with any other lifetime qualifier.
6642 if (LifetimeQual != Qualifiers::OCL_Strong) {
6643 if (DiagnoseFailure) {
6644 S.Diag(VD->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ignored_objc_externally_retained)
6645 << 1;
6646 }
6647 return false;
6648 }
6649
6650 // Tampering with the type of a VarDecl here is a bit of a hack, but we need
6651 // to ensure that the variable is 'const' so that we can error on
6652 // modification, which can otherwise over-release.
6653 VD->setType(Ty.withConst());
6654 VD->setARCPseudoStrong(true);
6655 return true;
6656}
6657
6658static void handleObjCExternallyRetainedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6659 const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6660 if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
6661 assert(!isa<ParmVarDecl>(VD) && "should be diagnosed automatically");
6662 if (!VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
6663 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ignored_objc_externally_retained)
6664 << 0;
6665 return;
6666 }
6667
6668 if (!tryMakeVariablePseudoStrong(S, VD, /*DiagnoseFailure=*/true))
6669 return;
6670
6671 handleSimpleAttribute<ObjCExternallyRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
6672 return;
6673 }
6674
6675 // If D is a function-like declaration (method, block, or function), then we
6676 // make every parameter psuedo-strong.
6677 for (unsigned I = 0, E = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D); I != E; ++I) {
6678 auto *PVD = const_cast<ParmVarDecl *>(getFunctionOrMethodParam(D, I));
6679 QualType Ty = PVD->getType();
6680
6681 // If a user wrote a parameter with __strong explicitly, then assume they
6682 // want "real" strong semantics for that parameter. This works because if
6683 // the parameter was written with __strong, then the strong qualifier will
6684 // be non-local.
6685 if (Ty.getLocalUnqualifiedType().getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime() ==
6686 Qualifiers::OCL_Strong)
6687 continue;
6688
6689 tryMakeVariablePseudoStrong(S, PVD, /*DiagnoseFailure=*/false);
6690 }
6691 handleSimpleAttribute<ObjCExternallyRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
6692}
6693
6694static void handleMIGServerRoutineAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6695 // Check that the return type is a `typedef int kern_return_t` or a typedef
6696 // around it, because otherwise MIG convention checks make no sense.
6697 // BlockDecl doesn't store a return type, so it's annoying to check,
6698 // so let's skip it for now.
6699 if (!isa<BlockDecl>(D)) {
6700 QualType T = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
6701 bool IsKernReturnT = false;
6702 while (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
6703 IsKernReturnT = (TT->getDecl()->getName() == "kern_return_t");
6704 T = TT->desugar();
6705 }
6706 if (!IsKernReturnT || T.getCanonicalType() != S.getASTContext().IntTy) {
6707 S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(),
6708 diag::warn_mig_server_routine_does_not_return_kern_return_t);
6709 return;
6710 }
6711 }
6712
6713 handleSimpleAttribute<MIGServerRoutineAttr>(S, D, AL);
6714}
6715
6716static void handleMSAllocatorAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6717 // Warn if the return type is not a pointer or reference type.
6718 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
6719 QualType RetTy = FD->getReturnType();
6720 if (!RetTy->isPointerType() && !RetTy->isReferenceType()) {
6721 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_declspec_allocator_nonpointer)
6722 << AL.getRange() << RetTy;
6723 return;
6724 }
6725 }
6726
6727 handleSimpleAttribute<MSAllocatorAttr>(S, D, AL);
6728}
6729
6730//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6731// Top Level Sema Entry Points
6732//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6733
6734/// ProcessDeclAttribute - Apply the specific attribute to the specified decl if
6735/// the attribute applies to decls. If the attribute is a type attribute, just
6736/// silently ignore it if a GNU attribute.
6737static void ProcessDeclAttribute(Sema &S, Scope *scope, Decl *D,
6738 const ParsedAttr &AL,
6739 bool IncludeCXX11Attributes) {
6740 if (AL.isInvalid() || AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::IgnoredAttribute)
6741 return;
6742
6743 // Ignore C++11 attributes on declarator chunks: they appertain to the type
6744 // instead.
6745 if (AL.isCXX11Attribute() && !IncludeCXX11Attributes)
6746 return;
6747
6748 // Unknown attributes are automatically warned on. Target-specific attributes
6749 // which do not apply to the current target architecture are treated as
6750 // though they were unknown attributes.
6751 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::UnknownAttribute ||
6752 !AL.existsInTarget(S.Context.getTargetInfo())) {
6753 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
6754 AL.isDeclspecAttribute()
6755 ? (unsigned)diag::warn_unhandled_ms_attribute_ignored
6756 : (unsigned)diag::warn_unknown_attribute_ignored)
6757 << AL;
6758 return;
6759 }

6762 return;

7375 break;
7376 case ParsedAttr::AT_PtGuardedBy:
7377 handlePtGuardedByAttr(S, D, AL);
7378 break;
7379 case ParsedAttr::AT_ExclusiveTrylockFunction:
7380 handleExclusiveTrylockFunctionAttr(S, D, AL);
7381 break;
7382 case ParsedAttr::AT_LockReturned:
7383 handleLockReturnedAttr(S, D, AL);
7384 break;
7385 case ParsedAttr::AT_LocksExcluded:
7386 handleLocksExcludedAttr(S, D, AL);
7387 break;
7388 case ParsedAttr::AT_SharedTrylockFunction:
7389 handleSharedTrylockFunctionAttr(S, D, AL);
7390 break;
7391 case ParsedAttr::AT_AcquiredBefore:
7392 handleAcquiredBeforeAttr(S, D, AL);
7393 break;
7394 case ParsedAttr::AT_AcquiredAfter:
7395 handleAcquiredAfterAttr(S, D, AL);
7396 break;
7397
7398 // Capability analysis attributes.
7399 case ParsedAttr::AT_Capability:
7400 case ParsedAttr::AT_Lockable:
7401 handleCapabilityAttr(S, D, AL);
7402 break;
7403 case ParsedAttr::AT_RequiresCapability:
7404 handleRequiresCapabilityAttr(S, D, AL);
7405 break;
7406
7407 case ParsedAttr::AT_AssertCapability:
7408 handleAssertCapabilityAttr(S, D, AL);
7409 break;
7410 case ParsedAttr::AT_AcquireCapability:
7411 handleAcquireCapabilityAttr(S, D, AL);
7412 break;
7413 case ParsedAttr::AT_ReleaseCapability:
7414 handleReleaseCapabilityAttr(S, D, AL);
7415 break;
7416 case ParsedAttr::AT_TryAcquireCapability:
7417 handleTryAcquireCapabilityAttr(S, D, AL);
7418 break;
7419
7420 // Consumed analysis attributes.
7421 case ParsedAttr::AT_Consumable:
7422 handleConsumableAttr(S, D, AL);
7423 break;
7424 case ParsedAttr::AT_ConsumableAutoCast:
7425 handleSimpleAttribute<ConsumableAutoCastAttr>(S, D, AL);
7426 break;
7427 case ParsedAttr::AT_ConsumableSetOnRead:
7428 handleSimpleAttribute<ConsumableSetOnReadAttr>(S, D, AL);
7429 break;
7430 case ParsedAttr::AT_CallableWhen:
7431 handleCallableWhenAttr(S, D, AL);
7432 break;
7433 case ParsedAttr::AT_ParamTypestate:
7434 handleParamTypestateAttr(S, D, AL);
7435 break;
7436 case ParsedAttr::AT_ReturnTypestate:
7437 handleReturnTypestateAttr(S, D, AL);
7438 break;
7439 case ParsedAttr::AT_SetTypestate:
7440 handleSetTypestateAttr(S, D, AL);
7441 break;
7442 case ParsedAttr::AT_TestTypestate:
7443 handleTestTypestateAttr(S, D, AL);
7444 break;
7445
7446 // Type safety attributes.
7447 case ParsedAttr::AT_ArgumentWithTypeTag:
7448 handleArgumentWithTypeTagAttr(S, D, AL);
7449 break;
7450 case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeTagForDatatype:
7451 handleTypeTagForDatatypeAttr(S, D, AL);
7452 break;
7453 case ParsedAttr::AT_AnyX86NoCallerSavedRegisters:
7454 handleSimpleAttribute<AnyX86NoCallerSavedRegistersAttr>(S, D, AL);
7455 break;
7456 case ParsedAttr::AT_RenderScriptKernel:
7457 handleSimpleAttribute<RenderScriptKernelAttr>(S, D, AL);
7458 break;
7459 // XRay attributes.
7460 case ParsedAttr::AT_XRayInstrument:
7461 handleSimpleAttribute<XRayInstrumentAttr>(S, D, AL);
7462 break;
7463 case ParsedAttr::AT_XRayLogArgs:
7464 handleXRayLogArgsAttr(S, D, AL);
7465 break;
7466
7467 // Move semantics attribute.
7468 case ParsedAttr::AT_Reinitializes:
7469 handleSimpleAttribute<ReinitializesAttr>(S, D, AL);
7470 break;
7471
7472 case ParsedAttr::AT_AlwaysDestroy:
7473 case ParsedAttr::AT_NoDestroy:
7474 handleDestroyAttr(S, D, AL);
7475 break;
7476
7477 case ParsedAttr::AT_Uninitialized:
7478 handleUninitializedAttr(S, D, AL);
7479 break;
7480
7481 case ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCExternallyRetained:
7482 handleObjCExternallyRetainedAttr(S, D, AL);
7483 break;
7484
7485 case ParsedAttr::AT_MIGServerRoutine:
7486 handleMIGServerRoutineAttr(S, D, AL);
7487 break;
7488
7489 case ParsedAttr::AT_MSAllocator:
7490 handleMSAllocatorAttr(S, D, AL);
7491 break;
7492 }
7493}
7494
7495/// ProcessDeclAttributeList - Apply all the decl attributes in the specified
7496/// attribute list to the specified decl, ignoring any type attributes.
7497void Sema::ProcessDeclAttributeList(Scope *S, Decl *D,
7498 const ParsedAttributesView &AttrList,
7499 bool IncludeCXX11Attributes) {
7500 if (AttrList.empty())
7501 return;
7502
7503 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : AttrList)
7504 ProcessDeclAttribute(*this, S, D, AL, IncludeCXX11Attributes);
7505
7506 // FIXME: We should be able to handle these cases in TableGen.
7507 // GCC accepts
7508 // static int a9 __attribute__((weakref));
7509 // but that looks really pointless. We reject it.
7510 if (D->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>() && !D->hasAttr<AliasAttr>()) {
7511 Diag(AttrList.begin()->getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_weakref_without_alias)
7512 << cast<NamedDecl>(D);
7513 D->dropAttr<WeakRefAttr>();
7514 return;
7515 }
7516
7517 // FIXME: We should be able to handle this in TableGen as well. It would be
7518 // good to have a way to specify "these attributes must appear as a group",
7519 // for these. Additionally, it would be good to have a way to specify "these
7520 // attribute must never appear as a group" for attributes like cold and hot.
7521 if (!D->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>()) {
7522 // These attributes cannot be applied to a non-kernel function.
7523 if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
7524 // FIXME: This emits a different error message than
7525 // diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type + ExpectedKernelFunction.
7526 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_opencl_kernel_attr) << A;
7527 D->setInvalidDecl();
7528 } else if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<WorkGroupSizeHintAttr>()) {
7529 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_opencl_kernel_attr) << A;
7530 D->setInvalidDecl();
7531 } else if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<VecTypeHintAttr>()) {
7532 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_opencl_kernel_attr) << A;
7533 D->setInvalidDecl();
7534 } else if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<OpenCLIntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
7535 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_opencl_kernel_attr) << A;
7536 D->setInvalidDecl();
7537 } else if (!D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) {
7538 if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
7539 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
7540 << A << ExpectedKernelFunction;
7541 D->setInvalidDecl();
7542 } else if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr>()) {
7543 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
7544 << A << ExpectedKernelFunction;
7545 D->setInvalidDecl();
7546 } else if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<AMDGPUNumSGPRAttr>()) {
7547 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
7548 << A << ExpectedKernelFunction;
7549 D->setInvalidDecl();
7550 } else if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<AMDGPUNumVGPRAttr>()) {
7551 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
7552 << A << ExpectedKernelFunction;
7553 D->setInvalidDecl();
7554 }
7555 }
7556 }
7557
7558 // Do this check after processing D's attributes because the attribute
7559 // objc_method_family can change whether the given method is in the init
7560 // family, and it can be applied after objc_designated_initializer. This is a
7561 // bit of a hack, but we need it to be compatible with versions of clang that
7562 // processed the attribute list in the wrong order.
7563 if (D->hasAttr<ObjCDesignatedInitializerAttr>() &&
7564 cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)->getMethodFamily() != OMF_init) {
7565 Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_designated_init_attr_non_init);
7566 D->dropAttr<ObjCDesignatedInitializerAttr>();
7567 }
7568}
7569
7570// Helper for delayed processing TransparentUnion attribute.
7571void Sema::ProcessDeclAttributeDelayed(Decl *D,
7572 const ParsedAttributesView &AttrList) {
7573 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : AttrList)
7574 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TransparentUnion) {
7575 handleTransparentUnionAttr(*this, D, AL);
7576 break;
7577 }
7578}
7579
7580// Annotation attributes are the only attributes allowed after an access
7581// specifier.
7582bool Sema::ProcessAccessDeclAttributeList(
7583 AccessSpecDecl *ASDecl, const ParsedAttributesView &AttrList) {
7584 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : AttrList) {
7585 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_Annotate) {
7586 ProcessDeclAttribute(*this, nullptr, ASDecl, AL, AL.isCXX11Attribute());
7587 } else {
7588 Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_only_annotate_after_access_spec);
7589 return true;
7590 }
7591 }
7592 return false;
7593}
7594
7595/// checkUnusedDeclAttributes - Check a list of attributes to see if it
7596/// contains any decl attributes that we should warn about.
7597static void checkUnusedDeclAttributes(Sema &S, const ParsedAttributesView &A) {
7598 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : A) {
7599 // Only warn if the attribute is an unignored, non-type attribute.
7600 if (AL.isUsedAsTypeAttr() || AL.isInvalid())
7601 continue;
7602 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::IgnoredAttribute)
7603 continue;
7604
7605 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::UnknownAttribute) {
7606 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_unknown_attribute_ignored)
7607 << AL << AL.getRange();
7608 } else {
7609 S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_not_on_decl) << AL
7610 << AL.getRange();
7611 }
7612 }
7613}
7614
7615/// checkUnusedDeclAttributes - Given a declarator which is not being
7616/// used to build a declaration, complain about any decl attributes
7617/// which might be lying around on it.
7618void Sema::checkUnusedDeclAttributes(Declarator &D) {
7619 ::checkUnusedDeclAttributes(*this, D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes());
7620 ::checkUnusedDeclAttributes(*this, D.getAttributes());
7621 for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i)
7622 ::checkUnusedDeclAttributes(*this, D.getTypeObject(i).getAttrs());
7623}
7624
7625/// DeclClonePragmaWeak - clone existing decl (maybe definition),
7626/// \#pragma weak needs a non-definition decl and source may not have one.
7627NamedDecl * Sema::DeclClonePragmaWeak(NamedDecl *ND, IdentifierInfo *II,
7628 SourceLocation Loc) {
7629 assert(isa<FunctionDecl>(ND) || isa<VarDecl>(ND));
7630 NamedDecl *NewD = nullptr;
7631 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND)) {
7632 FunctionDecl *NewFD;
7633 // FIXME: Missing call to CheckFunctionDeclaration().
7634 // FIXME: Mangling?
7635 // FIXME: Is the qualifier info correct?
7636 // FIXME: Is the DeclContext correct?
7637 NewFD = FunctionDecl::Create(FD->getASTContext(), FD->getDeclContext(),
7638 Loc, Loc, DeclarationName(II),
7639 FD->getType(), FD->getTypeSourceInfo(),
7640 SC_None, false/*isInlineSpecified*/,
7641 FD->hasPrototype(),
7642 false/*isConstexprSpecified*/);
7643 NewD = NewFD;
7644
7645 if (FD->getQualifier())
7646 NewFD->setQualifierInfo(FD->getQualifierLoc());
7647
7648 // Fake up parameter variables; they are declared as if this were
7649 // a typedef.
7650 QualType FDTy = FD->getType();
7651 if (const auto *FT = FDTy->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
7652 SmallVector<ParmVarDecl*, 16> Params;
7653 for (const auto &AI : FT->param_types()) {
7654 ParmVarDecl *Param = BuildParmVarDeclForTypedef(NewFD, Loc, AI);
7655 Param->setScopeInfo(0, Params.size());
7656 Params.push_back(Param);
7657 }
7658 NewFD->setParams(Params);
7659 }
7660 } else if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(ND)) {
7661 NewD = VarDecl::Create(VD->getASTContext(), VD->getDeclContext(),
7662 VD->getInnerLocStart(), VD->getLocation(), II,
7663 VD->getType(), VD->getTypeSourceInfo(),
7664 VD->getStorageClass());
7665 if (VD->getQualifier())
7666 cast<VarDecl>(NewD)->setQualifierInfo(VD->getQualifierLoc());
7667 }
7668 return NewD;
7669}
7670
7671/// DeclApplyPragmaWeak - A declaration (maybe definition) needs \#pragma weak
7672/// applied to it, possibly with an alias.
7673void Sema::DeclApplyPragmaWeak(Scope *S, NamedDecl *ND, WeakInfo &W) {
7674 if (W.getUsed()) return; // only do this once
7675 W.setUsed(true);
7676 if (W.getAlias()) { // clone decl, impersonate __attribute(weak,alias(...))
7677 IdentifierInfo *NDId = ND->getIdentifier();
7678 NamedDecl *NewD = DeclClonePragmaWeak(ND, W.getAlias(), W.getLocation());
7679 NewD->addAttr(AliasAttr::CreateImplicit(Context, NDId->getName(),
7680 W.getLocation()));
7681 NewD->addAttr(WeakAttr::CreateImplicit(Context, W.getLocation()));
7682 WeakTopLevelDecl.push_back(NewD);
7683 // FIXME: "hideous" code from Sema::LazilyCreateBuiltin
7684 // to insert Decl at TU scope, sorry.
7685 DeclContext *SavedContext = CurContext;
7686 CurContext = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
7687 NewD->setDeclContext(CurContext);
7688 NewD->setLexicalDeclContext(CurContext);
7689 PushOnScopeChains(NewD, S);
7690 CurContext = SavedContext;
7691 } else { // just add weak to existing
7692 ND->addAttr(WeakAttr::CreateImplicit(Context, W.getLocation()));
7693 }
7694}
7695
7696void Sema::ProcessPragmaWeak(Scope *S, Decl *D) {
7697 // It's valid to "forward-declare" #pragma weak, in which case we
7698 // have to do this.
7699 LoadExternalWeakUndeclaredIdentifiers();
7700 if (!WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.empty()) {
7701 NamedDecl *ND = nullptr;
7702 if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
7703 if (VD->isExternC())
7704 ND = VD;
7705 if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
7706 if (FD->isExternC())
7707 ND = FD;
7708 if (ND) {
7709 if (IdentifierInfo *Id = ND->getIdentifier()) {
7710 auto I = WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.find(Id);
7711 if (I != WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers.end()) {
7712 WeakInfo W = I->second;
7713 DeclApplyPragmaWeak(S, ND, W);
7714 WeakUndeclaredIdentifiers[Id] = W;
7715 }
7716 }
7717 }
7718 }
7719}
7720
7721/// ProcessDeclAttributes - Given a declarator (PD) with attributes indicated in
7722/// it, apply them to D. This is a bit tricky because PD can have attributes
7723/// specified in many different places, and we need to find and apply them all.
7724void Sema::ProcessDeclAttributes(Scope *S, Decl *D, const Declarator &PD) {
7725 // Apply decl attributes from the DeclSpec if present.
7726 if (!PD.getDeclSpec().getAttributes().empty())
7727 ProcessDeclAttributeList(S, D, PD.getDeclSpec().getAttributes());
7728
7729 // Walk the declarator structure, applying decl attributes that were in a type
7730 // position to the decl itself. This handles cases like:
7731 // int *__attr__(x)** D;
7732 // when X is a decl attribute.
7733 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PD.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i)
7734 ProcessDeclAttributeList(S, D, PD.getTypeObject(i).getAttrs(),
7735 /*IncludeCXX11Attributes=*/false);
7736
7737 // Finally, apply any attributes on the decl itself.
7738 ProcessDeclAttributeList(S, D, PD.getAttributes());
7739
7740 // Apply additional attributes specified by '#pragma clang attribute'.
7741 AddPragmaAttributes(S, D);
7742}
7743
7744/// Is the given declaration allowed to use a forbidden type?
7745/// If so, it'll still be annotated with an attribute that makes it
7746/// illegal to actually use.
7747static bool isForbiddenTypeAllowed(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7748 const DelayedDiagnostic &diag,
7749 UnavailableAttr::ImplicitReason &reason) {
7750 // Private ivars are always okay. Unfortunately, people don't
7751 // always properly make their ivars private, even in system headers.
7752 // Plus we need to make fields okay, too.
7753 if (!isa<FieldDecl>(D) && !isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D) &&
7754 !isa<FunctionDecl>(D))
7755 return false;
7756
7757 // Silently accept unsupported uses of __weak in both user and system
7758 // declarations when it's been disabled, for ease of integration with
7759 // -fno-objc-arc files. We do have to take some care against attempts
7760 // to define such things; for now, we've only done that for ivars
7761 // and properties.
7762 if ((isa<ObjCIvarDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D))) {
7763 if (diag.getForbiddenTypeDiagnostic() == diag::err_arc_weak_disabled ||
7764 diag.getForbiddenTypeDiagnostic() == diag::err_arc_weak_no_runtime) {
7765 reason = UnavailableAttr::IR_ForbiddenWeak;
7766 return true;
7767 }
7768 }
7769
7770 // Allow all sorts of things in system headers.
7771 if (S.Context.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(D->getLocation())) {
7772 // Currently, all the failures dealt with this way are due to ARC
7773 // restrictions.
7774 reason = UnavailableAttr::IR_ARCForbiddenType;
7775 return true;
7776 }
7777
7778 return false;
7779}
7780
7781/// Handle a delayed forbidden-type diagnostic.
7782static void handleDelayedForbiddenType(Sema &S, DelayedDiagnostic &DD,
7783 Decl *D) {
7784 auto Reason = UnavailableAttr::IR_None;
7785 if (D && isForbiddenTypeAllowed(S, D, DD, Reason)) {
7786 assert(Reason && "didn't set reason?");
7787 D->addAttr(UnavailableAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context, "", Reason, DD.Loc));
7788 return;
7789 }
7790 if (S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
7791 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
7792 // FIXME: we may want to suppress diagnostics for all
7793 // kind of forbidden type messages on unavailable functions.
7794 if (FD->hasAttr<UnavailableAttr>() &&
7795 DD.getForbiddenTypeDiagnostic() ==
7796 diag::err_arc_array_param_no_ownership) {
7797 DD.Triggered = true;
7798 return;
7799 }
7800 }
7801
7802 S.Diag(DD.Loc, DD.getForbiddenTypeDiagnostic())
7803 << DD.getForbiddenTypeOperand() << DD.getForbiddenTypeArgument();
7804 DD.Triggered = true;
7805}
7806
7807static const AvailabilityAttr *getAttrForPlatform(ASTContext &Context,
7808 const Decl *D) {
7809 // Check each AvailabilityAttr to find the one for this platform.
7810 for (const auto *A : D->attrs()) {
7811 if (const auto *Avail = dyn_cast<AvailabilityAttr>(A)) {
7812 // FIXME: this is copied from CheckAvailability. We should try to
7813 // de-duplicate.
7814
7815 // Check if this is an App Extension "platform", and if so chop off
7816 // the suffix for matching with the actual platform.
7817 StringRef ActualPlatform = Avail->getPlatform()->getName();
7818 StringRef RealizedPlatform = ActualPlatform;
7819 if (Context.getLangOpts().AppExt) {
7820 size_t suffix = RealizedPlatform.rfind("_app_extension");
7821 if (suffix != StringRef::npos)
7822 RealizedPlatform = RealizedPlatform.slice(0, suffix);
7823 }
7824
7825 StringRef TargetPlatform = Context.getTargetInfo().getPlatformName();
7826
7827 // Match the platform name.
7828 if (RealizedPlatform == TargetPlatform)
7829 return Avail;
7830 }
7831 }
7832 return nullptr;
7833}
7834
7835/// The diagnostic we should emit for \c D, and the declaration that
7836/// originated it, or \c AR_Available.
7837///
7838/// \param D The declaration to check.
7839/// \param Message If non-null, this will be populated with the message from
7840/// the availability attribute that is selected.
7841/// \param ClassReceiver If we're checking the the method of a class message
7842/// send, the class. Otherwise nullptr.
7843static std::pair<AvailabilityResult, const NamedDecl *>
7844ShouldDiagnoseAvailabilityOfDecl(Sema &S, const NamedDecl *D,
7845 std::string *Message,
7846 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ClassReceiver) {
7847 AvailabilityResult Result = D->getAvailability(Message);
7848
7849 // For typedefs, if the typedef declaration appears available look
7850 // to the underlying type to see if it is more restrictive.
7851 while (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
7852 if (Result == AR_Available) {
7853 if (const auto *TT = TD->getUnderlyingType()->getAs<TagType>()) {
7854 D = TT->getDecl();
7855 Result = D->getAvailability(Message);
7856 continue;
7857 }
7858 }
7859 break;
7860 }
7861
7862 // Forward class declarations get their attributes from their definition.
7863 if (const auto *IDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D)) {
7864 if (IDecl->getDefinition()) {
7865 D = IDecl->getDefinition();
7866 Result = D->getAvailability(Message);
7867 }
7868 }
7869
7870 if (const auto *ECD = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(D))
7871 if (Result == AR_Available) {
7872 const DeclContext *DC = ECD->getDeclContext();
7873 if (const auto *TheEnumDecl = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(DC)) {
7874 Result = TheEnumDecl->getAvailability(Message);
7875 D = TheEnumDecl;
7876 }
7877 }
7878
7879 // For +new, infer availability from -init.
7880 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
7881 if (S.NSAPIObj && ClassReceiver) {
7882 ObjCMethodDecl *Init = ClassReceiver->lookupInstanceMethod(
7883 S.NSAPIObj->getInitSelector());
7884 if (Init && Result == AR_Available && MD->isClassMethod() &&
7885 MD->getSelector() == S.NSAPIObj->getNewSelector() &&
7886 MD->definedInNSObject(S.getASTContext())) {
7887 Result = Init->getAvailability(Message);
7888 D = Init;
7889 }
7890 }
7891 }
7892
7893 return {Result, D};
7894}
7895
7896
7897/// whether we should emit a diagnostic for \c K and \c DeclVersion in
7898/// the context of \c Ctx. For example, we should emit an unavailable diagnostic
7899/// in a deprecated context, but not the other way around.
7900static bool
7901ShouldDiagnoseAvailabilityInContext(Sema &S, AvailabilityResult K,
7902 VersionTuple DeclVersion, Decl *Ctx,
7903 const NamedDecl *OffendingDecl) {
7904 assert(K != AR_Available && "Expected an unavailable declaration here!");
7905
7906 // Checks if we should emit the availability diagnostic in the context of C.
7907 auto CheckContext = [&](const Decl *C) {
7908 if (K == AR_NotYetIntroduced) {
7909 if (const AvailabilityAttr *AA = getAttrForPlatform(S.Context, C))
7910 if (AA->getIntroduced() >= DeclVersion)
7911 return true;
7912 } else if (K == AR_Deprecated) {
7913 if (C->isDeprecated())
7914 return true;
7915 } else if (K == AR_Unavailable) {
7916 // It is perfectly fine to refer to an 'unavailable' Objective-C method
7917 // when it is referenced from within the @implementation itself. In this
7918 // context, we interpret unavailable as a form of access control.
7919 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(OffendingDecl)) {
7920 if (const auto *Impl = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(C)) {
7921 if (MD->getClassInterface() == Impl->getClassInterface())
7922 return true;
7923 }
7924 }
7925 }
7926
7927 if (C->isUnavailable())
7928 return true;
7929 return false;
7930 };
7931
7932 do {
7933 if (CheckContext(Ctx))
7934 return false;
7935
7936 // An implementation implicitly has the availability of the interface.
7937 // Unless it is "+load" method.
7938 if (const auto *MethodD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(Ctx))
7939 if (MethodD->isClassMethod() &&
7940 MethodD->getSelector().getAsString() == "load")
7941 return true;
7942
7943 if (const auto *CatOrImpl = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(Ctx)) {
7944 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface = CatOrImpl->getClassInterface())
7945 if (CheckContext(Interface))
7946 return false;
7947 }
7948 // A category implicitly has the availability of the interface.
7949 else if (const auto *CatD = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx))
7950 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Interface = CatD->getClassInterface())
7951 if (CheckContext(Interface))
7952 return false;
7953 } while ((Ctx = cast_or_null<Decl>(Ctx->getDeclContext())));
7954
7955 return true;
7956}
7957
7958static bool
7959shouldDiagnoseAvailabilityByDefault(const ASTContext &Context,
7960 const VersionTuple &DeploymentVersion,
7961 const VersionTuple &DeclVersion) {
7962 const auto &Triple = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
7963 VersionTuple ForceAvailabilityFromVersion;
7964 switch (Triple.getOS()) {
7965 case llvm::Triple::IOS:
7966 case llvm::Triple::TvOS:
7967 ForceAvailabilityFromVersion = VersionTuple(/*Major=*/11);
7968 break;
7969 case llvm::Triple::WatchOS:
7970 ForceAvailabilityFromVersion = VersionTuple(/*Major=*/4);
7971 break;
7972 case llvm::Triple::Darwin:
7973 case llvm::Triple::MacOSX:
7974 ForceAvailabilityFromVersion = VersionTuple(/*Major=*/10, /*Minor=*/13);
7975 break;
7976 default:
7977 // New targets should always warn about availability.
7978 return Triple.getVendor() == llvm::Triple::Apple;
7979 }
7980 return DeploymentVersion >= ForceAvailabilityFromVersion ||
7981 DeclVersion >= ForceAvailabilityFromVersion;
7982}
7983
7984static NamedDecl *findEnclosingDeclToAnnotate(Decl *OrigCtx) {
7985 for (Decl *Ctx = OrigCtx; Ctx;
7986 Ctx = cast_or_null<Decl>(Ctx->getDeclContext())) {
7987 if (isa<TagDecl>(Ctx) || isa<FunctionDecl>(Ctx) || isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(Ctx))
7988 return cast<NamedDecl>(Ctx);
7989 if (auto *CD = dyn_cast<ObjCContainerDecl>(Ctx)) {
7990 if (auto *Imp = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(Ctx))
7991 return Imp->getClassInterface();
7992 return CD;
7993 }
7994 }
7995
7996 return dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(OrigCtx);
7997}

7999namespace {
8000
8001struct AttributeInsertion {
8002 StringRef Prefix;
8003 SourceLocation Loc;
8004 StringRef Suffix;
8005
8006 static AttributeInsertion createInsertionAfter(const NamedDecl *D) {
8007 return {" ", D->getEndLoc(), ""};
8008 }
8009 static AttributeInsertion createInsertionAfter(SourceLocation Loc) {
8010 return {" ", Loc, ""};
8011 }
8012 static AttributeInsertion createInsertionBefore(const NamedDecl *D) {
8013 return {"", D->getBeginLoc(), "\n"};
8014 }
8015};
8016
8017} // end anonymous namespace
8018
8019/// Tries to parse a string as ObjC method name.
8020///
8021/// \param Name The string to parse. Expected to originate from availability
8022/// attribute argument.
8023/// \param SlotNames The vector that will be populated with slot names. In case
8024/// of unsuccessful parsing can contain invalid data.
8025/// \returns A number of method parameters if parsing was successful, None
8026/// otherwise.
8027static Optional<unsigned>
8028tryParseObjCMethodName(StringRef Name, SmallVectorImpl<StringRef> &SlotNames,
8029 const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
8030 // Accept replacements starting with - or + as valid ObjC method names.
8031 if (!Name.empty() && (Name.front() == '-' || Name.front() == '+'))
8032 Name = Name.drop_front(1);
8033 if (Name.empty())
8034 return None;
8035 Name.split(SlotNames, ':');
8036 unsigned NumParams;
8037 if (Name.back() == ':') {
8038 // Remove an empty string at the end that doesn't represent any slot.
8039 SlotNames.pop_back();
8040 NumParams = SlotNames.size();
8041 } else {
8042 if (SlotNames.size() != 1)
8043 // Not a valid method name, just a colon-separated string.
8044 return None;
8045 NumParams = 0;
8046 }
8047 // Verify all slot names are valid.
8048 bool AllowDollar = LangOpts.DollarIdents;
8049 for (StringRef S : SlotNames) {
8050 if (S.empty())
8051 continue;
8052 if (!isValidIdentifier(S, AllowDollar))
8053 return None;
8054 }
8055 return NumParams;
8056}
8057
8058/// Returns a source location in which it's appropriate to insert a new
8059/// attribute for the given declaration \D.
8060static Optional<AttributeInsertion>
8061createAttributeInsertion(const NamedDecl *D, const SourceManager &SM,
8062 const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
8063 if (isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D))
8064 return AttributeInsertion::createInsertionAfter(D);
8065 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
8066 if (MD->hasBody())
8067 return None;
8068 return AttributeInsertion::createInsertionAfter(D);
8069 }
8070 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D)) {
8071 SourceLocation Loc =
8072 Lexer::getLocForEndOfToken(TD->getInnerLocStart(), 0, SM, LangOpts);
8073 if (Loc.isInvalid())
8074 return None;
8075 // Insert after the 'struct'/whatever keyword.
8076 return AttributeInsertion::createInsertionAfter(Loc);
8077 }
8078 return AttributeInsertion::createInsertionBefore(D);
8079}
8080
8081/// Actually emit an availability diagnostic for a reference to an unavailable
8082/// decl.
8083///
8084/// \param Ctx The context that the reference occurred in
8085/// \param ReferringDecl The exact declaration that was referenced.
8086/// \param OffendingDecl A related decl to \c ReferringDecl that has an
8087/// availability attribute corresponding to \c K attached to it. Note that this
8088/// may not be the same as ReferringDecl, i.e. if an EnumDecl is annotated and
8089/// we refer to a member EnumConstantDecl, ReferringDecl is the EnumConstantDecl
8090/// and OffendingDecl is the EnumDecl.
8091static void DoEmitAvailabilityWarning(Sema &S, AvailabilityResult K,
8092 Decl *Ctx, const NamedDecl *ReferringDecl,
8093 const NamedDecl *OffendingDecl,
8094 StringRef Message,
8095 ArrayRef<SourceLocation> Locs,
8096 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *UnknownObjCClass,
8097 const ObjCPropertyDecl *ObjCProperty,
8098 bool ObjCPropertyAccess) {
8099 // Diagnostics for deprecated or unavailable.
8100 unsigned diag, diag_message, diag_fwdclass_message;
8101 unsigned diag_available_here = diag::note_availability_specified_here;
8102 SourceLocation NoteLocation = OffendingDecl->getLocation();
8103
8104 // Matches 'diag::note_property_attribute' options.
8105 unsigned property_note_select;
8106
8107 // Matches diag::note_availability_specified_here.
8108 unsigned available_here_select_kind;
8109
8110 VersionTuple DeclVersion;
8111 if (const AvailabilityAttr *AA = getAttrForPlatform(S.Context, OffendingDecl))
8112 DeclVersion = AA->getIntroduced();
8113
8114 if (!ShouldDiagnoseAvailabilityInContext(S, K, DeclVersion, Ctx,
8115 OffendingDecl))
8116 return;
8117
8118 SourceLocation Loc = Locs.front();
8119
8120 // The declaration can have multiple availability attributes, we are looking
8121 // at one of them.
8122 const AvailabilityAttr *A = getAttrForPlatform(S.Context, OffendingDecl);
8123 if (A && A->isInherited()) {
8124 for (const Decl *Redecl = OffendingDecl->getMostRecentDecl(); Redecl;
8125 Redecl = Redecl->getPreviousDecl()) {
8126 const AvailabilityAttr *AForRedecl =
8127 getAttrForPlatform(S.Context, Redecl);
8128 if (AForRedecl && !AForRedecl->isInherited()) {
8129 // If D is a declaration with inherited attributes, the note should
8130 // point to the declaration with actual attributes.
8131 NoteLocation = Redecl->getLocation();
8132 break;
8133 }
8134 }
8135 }
8136
8137 switch (K) {
8138 case AR_NotYetIntroduced: {
8139 // We would like to emit the diagnostic even if -Wunguarded-availability is
8140 // not specified for deployment targets >= to iOS 11 or equivalent or
8141 // for declarations that were introduced in iOS 11 (macOS 10.13, ...) or
8142 // later.
8143 const AvailabilityAttr *AA =
8144 getAttrForPlatform(S.getASTContext(), OffendingDecl);
8145 VersionTuple Introduced = AA->getIntroduced();
8146
8147 bool UseNewWarning = shouldDiagnoseAvailabilityByDefault(
8148 S.Context, S.Context.getTargetInfo().getPlatformMinVersion(),
8149 Introduced);
8150 unsigned Warning = UseNewWarning ? diag::warn_unguarded_availability_new
8151 : diag::warn_unguarded_availability;
8152
8153 std::string PlatformName = AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(
8154 S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getPlatformName());
8155
8156 S.Diag(Loc, Warning) << OffendingDecl << PlatformName
8157 << Introduced.getAsString();
8158
8159 S.Diag(OffendingDecl->getLocation(),
8160 diag::note_partial_availability_specified_here)
8161 << OffendingDecl << PlatformName << Introduced.getAsString()
8162 << S.Context.getTargetInfo().getPlatformMinVersion().getAsString();
8163
8164 if (const auto *Enclosing = findEnclosingDeclToAnnotate(Ctx)) {
8165 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(Enclosing))
8166 if (TD->getDeclName().isEmpty()) {
8167 S.Diag(TD->getLocation(),
8168 diag::note_decl_unguarded_availability_silence)
8169 << /*Anonymous*/ 1 << TD->getKindName();
8170 return;
8171 }
8172 auto FixitNoteDiag =
8173 S.Diag(Enclosing->getLocation(),
8174 diag::note_decl_unguarded_availability_silence)
8175 << /*Named*/ 0 << Enclosing;
8176 // Don't offer a fixit for declarations with availability attributes.
8177 if (Enclosing->hasAttr<AvailabilityAttr>())
8178 return;
8179 if (!S.getPreprocessor().isMacroDefined("API_AVAILABLE"))
8180 return;
8181 Optional<AttributeInsertion> Insertion = createAttributeInsertion(
8182 Enclosing, S.getSourceManager(), S.getLangOpts());
8183 if (!Insertion)
8184 return;
8185 std::string PlatformName =
8186 AvailabilityAttr::getPlatformNameSourceSpelling(
8187 S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getPlatformName())
8188 .lower();
8189 std::string Introduced =
8190 OffendingDecl->getVersionIntroduced().getAsString();
8191 FixitNoteDiag << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
8192 Insertion->Loc,
8193 (llvm::Twine(Insertion->Prefix) + "API_AVAILABLE(" + PlatformName +
8194 "(" + Introduced + "))" + Insertion->Suffix)
8195 .str());
8196 }
8197 return;
8198 }
8199 case AR_Deprecated:
8200 diag = !ObjCPropertyAccess ? diag::warn_deprecated
8201 : diag::warn_property_method_deprecated;
8202 diag_message = diag::warn_deprecated_message;
8203 diag_fwdclass_message = diag::warn_deprecated_fwdclass_message;
8204 property_note_select = /* deprecated */ 0;
8205 available_here_select_kind = /* deprecated */ 2;
8206 if (const auto *AL = OffendingDecl->getAttr<DeprecatedAttr>())
8207 NoteLocation = AL->getLocation();
8208 break;
8209
8210 case AR_Unavailable:
8211 diag = !ObjCPropertyAccess ? diag::err_unavailable
8212 : diag::err_property_method_unavailable;
8213 diag_message = diag::err_unavailable_message;
8214 diag_fwdclass_message = diag::warn_unavailable_fwdclass_message;
8215 property_note_select = /* unavailable */ 1;
8216 available_here_select_kind = /* unavailable */ 0;
8217
8218 if (auto AL = OffendingDecl->getAttr<UnavailableAttr>()) {
8219 if (AL->isImplicit() && AL->getImplicitReason()) {
8220 // Most of these failures are due to extra restrictions in ARC;
8221 // reflect that in the primary diagnostic when applicable.
8222 auto flagARCError = [&] {
8223 if (S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
8224 S.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(
8225 OffendingDecl->getLocation()))
8226 diag = diag::err_unavailable_in_arc;
8227 };
8228
8229 switch (AL->getImplicitReason()) {
8230 case UnavailableAttr::IR_None: break;
8231
8232 case UnavailableAttr::IR_ARCForbiddenType:
8233 flagARCError();
8234 diag_available_here = diag::note_arc_forbidden_type;
8235 break;
8236
8237 case UnavailableAttr::IR_ForbiddenWeak:
8238 if (S.getLangOpts().ObjCWeakRuntime)
8239 diag_available_here = diag::note_arc_weak_disabled;
8240 else
8241 diag_available_here = diag::note_arc_weak_no_runtime;
8242 break;
8243
8244 case UnavailableAttr::IR_ARCForbiddenConversion:
8245 flagARCError();
8246 diag_available_here = diag::note_performs_forbidden_arc_conversion;
8247 break;
8248
8249 case UnavailableAttr::IR_ARCInitReturnsUnrelated:
8250 flagARCError();
8251 diag_available_here = diag::note_arc_init_returns_unrelated;
8252 break;
8253
8254 case UnavailableAttr::IR_ARCFieldWithOwnership:
8255 flagARCError();
8256 diag_available_here = diag::note_arc_field_with_ownership;
8257 break;
8258 }
8259 }
8260 }
8261 break;
8262
8263 case AR_Available:
8264 llvm_unreachable("Warning for availability of available declaration?");
8265 }
8266
8267 SmallVector<FixItHint, 12> FixIts;
8268 if (K == AR_Deprecated) {
8269 StringRef Replacement;
8270 if (auto AL = OffendingDecl->getAttr<DeprecatedAttr>())
8271 Replacement = AL->getReplacement();
8272 if (auto AL = getAttrForPlatform(S.Context, OffendingDecl))
8273 Replacement = AL->getReplacement();
8274
8275 CharSourceRange UseRange;
8276 if (!Replacement.empty())
8277 UseRange =
8278 CharSourceRange::getCharRange(Loc, S.getLocForEndOfToken(Loc));
8279 if (UseRange.isValid()) {
8280 if (const auto *MethodDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(ReferringDecl)) {
8281 Selector Sel = MethodDecl->getSelector();
8282 SmallVector<StringRef, 12> SelectorSlotNames;
8283 Optional<unsigned> NumParams = tryParseObjCMethodName(
8284 Replacement, SelectorSlotNames, S.getLangOpts());
8285 if (NumParams && NumParams.getValue() == Sel.getNumArgs()) {
8286 assert(SelectorSlotNames.size() == Locs.size());
8287 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Locs.size(); ++I) {
8288 if (!Sel.getNameForSlot(I).empty()) {
8289 CharSourceRange NameRange = CharSourceRange::getCharRange(
8290 Locs[I], S.getLocForEndOfToken(Locs[I]));
8291 FixIts.push_back(FixItHint::CreateReplacement(
8292 NameRange, SelectorSlotNames[I]));
8293 } else
8294 FixIts.push_back(
8295 FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Locs[I], SelectorSlotNames[I]));
8296 }
8297 } else
8298 FixIts.push_back(FixItHint::CreateReplacement(UseRange, Replacement));
8299 } else
8300 FixIts.push_back(FixItHint::CreateReplacement(UseRange, Replacement));
8301 }
8302 }
8303
8304 if (!Message.empty()) {
8305 S.Diag(Loc, diag_message) << ReferringDecl << Message << FixIts;
8306 if (ObjCProperty)
8307 S.Diag(ObjCProperty->getLocation(), diag::note_property_attribute)
8308 << ObjCProperty->getDeclName() << property_note_select;
8309 } else if (!UnknownObjCClass) {
8310 S.Diag(Loc, diag) << ReferringDecl << FixIts;
8311 if (ObjCProperty)
8312 S.Diag(ObjCProperty->getLocation(), diag::note_property_attribute)
8313 << ObjCProperty->getDeclName() << property_note_select;
8314 } else {
8315 S.Diag(Loc, diag_fwdclass_message) << ReferringDecl << FixIts;
8316 S.Diag(UnknownObjCClass->getLocation(), diag::note_forward_class);
8317 }
8318
8319 S.Diag(NoteLocation, diag_available_here)
8320 << OffendingDecl << available_here_select_kind;
8321}
8322
8323static void handleDelayedAvailabilityCheck(Sema &S, DelayedDiagnostic &DD,
8324 Decl *Ctx) {
8325 assert(DD.Kind == DelayedDiagnostic::Availability &&
8326 "Expected an availability diagnostic here");
8327
8328 DD.Triggered = true;
8329 DoEmitAvailabilityWarning(
8330 S, DD.getAvailabilityResult(), Ctx, DD.getAvailabilityReferringDecl(),
8331 DD.getAvailabilityOffendingDecl(), DD.getAvailabilityMessage(),
8332 DD.getAvailabilitySelectorLocs(), DD.getUnknownObjCClass(),
8333 DD.getObjCProperty(), false);
8334}
8335
8336void Sema::PopParsingDeclaration(ParsingDeclState state, Decl *decl) {
8337 assert(DelayedDiagnostics.getCurrentPool());
8338 DelayedDiagnosticPool &poppedPool = *DelayedDiagnostics.getCurrentPool();
8339 DelayedDiagnostics.popWithoutEmitting(state);
8340
8341 // When delaying diagnostics to run in the context of a parsed
8342 // declaration, we only want to actually emit anything if parsing
8343 // succeeds.
8344 if (!decl) return;
8345
8346 // We emit all the active diagnostics in this pool or any of its
8347 // parents. In general, we'll get one pool for the decl spec
8348 // and a child pool for each declarator; in a decl group like:
8349 // deprecated_typedef foo, *bar, baz();
8350 // only the declarator pops will be passed decls. This is correct;
8351 // we really do need to consider delayed diagnostics from the decl spec
8352 // for each of the different declarations.
8353 const DelayedDiagnosticPool *pool = &poppedPool;
8354 do {
8355 bool AnyAccessFailures = false;
8356 for (DelayedDiagnosticPool::pool_iterator
8357 i = pool->pool_begin(), e = pool->pool_end(); i != e; ++i) {
8358 // This const_cast is a bit lame. Really, Triggered should be mutable.
8359 DelayedDiagnostic &diag = const_cast<DelayedDiagnostic&>(*i);
8360 if (diag.Triggered)
8361 continue;
8362
8363 switch (diag.Kind) {
8364 case DelayedDiagnostic::Availability:
8365 // Don't bother giving deprecation/unavailable diagnostics if
8366 // the decl is invalid.
8367 if (!decl->isInvalidDecl())
8368 handleDelayedAvailabilityCheck(*this, diag, decl);
8369 break;
8370
8371 case DelayedDiagnostic::Access:
8372 // Only produce one access control diagnostic for a structured binding
8373 // declaration: we don't need to tell the user that all the fields are
8374 // inaccessible one at a time.
8375 if (AnyAccessFailures && isa<DecompositionDecl>(decl))
8376 continue;
8377 HandleDelayedAccessCheck(diag, decl);
8378 if (diag.Triggered)
8379 AnyAccessFailures = true;
8380 break;
8381
8382 case DelayedDiagnostic::ForbiddenType:
8383 handleDelayedForbiddenType(*this, diag, decl);
8384 break;
8385 }
8386 }
8387 } while ((pool = pool->getParent()));
8388}
8389
8390/// Given a set of delayed diagnostics, re-emit them as if they had
8391/// been delayed in the current context instead of in the given pool.
8392/// Essentially, this just moves them to the current pool.
8393void Sema::redelayDiagnostics(DelayedDiagnosticPool &pool) {
8394 DelayedDiagnosticPool *curPool = DelayedDiagnostics.getCurrentPool();
8395 assert(curPool && "re-emitting in undelayed context not supported");
8396 curPool->steal(pool);
8397}
8398
8399static void EmitAvailabilityWarning(Sema &S, AvailabilityResult AR,
8400 const NamedDecl *ReferringDecl,
8401 const NamedDecl *OffendingDecl,
8402 StringRef Message,
8403 ArrayRef<SourceLocation> Locs,
8404 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *UnknownObjCClass,
8405 const ObjCPropertyDecl *ObjCProperty,
8406 bool ObjCPropertyAccess) {
8407 // Delay if we're currently parsing a declaration.
8408 if (S.DelayedDiagnostics.shouldDelayDiagnostics()) {
8409 S.DelayedDiagnostics.add(
8410 DelayedDiagnostic::makeAvailability(
8411 AR, Locs, ReferringDecl, OffendingDecl, UnknownObjCClass,
8412 ObjCProperty, Message, ObjCPropertyAccess));
8413 return;
8414 }
8415
8416 Decl *Ctx = cast<Decl>(S.getCurLexicalContext());
8417 DoEmitAvailabilityWarning(S, AR, Ctx, ReferringDecl, OffendingDecl,
8418 Message, Locs, UnknownObjCClass, ObjCProperty,
8419 ObjCPropertyAccess);
8420}
8421
8422namespace {
8423
8424/// Returns true if the given statement can be a body-like child of \p Parent.
8425bool isBodyLikeChildStmt(const Stmt *S, const Stmt *Parent) {
8426 switch (Parent->getStmtClass()) {
8427 case Stmt::IfStmtClass:
8428 return cast<IfStmt>(Parent)->getThen() == S ||
8429 cast<IfStmt>(Parent)->getElse() == S;
8430 case Stmt::WhileStmtClass:
8431 return cast<WhileStmt>(Parent)->getBody() == S;
8432 case Stmt::DoStmtClass:
8433 return cast<DoStmt>(Parent)->getBody() == S;
8434 case Stmt::ForStmtClass:
8435 return cast<ForStmt>(Parent)->getBody() == S;
8436 case Stmt::CXXForRangeStmtClass:
8437 return cast<CXXForRangeStmt>(Parent)->getBody() == S;
8438 case Stmt::ObjCForCollectionStmtClass:
8439 return cast<ObjCForCollectionStmt>(Parent)->getBody() == S;
8440 case Stmt::CaseStmtClass:
8441 case Stmt::DefaultStmtClass:
8442 return cast<SwitchCase>(Parent)->getSubStmt() == S;
8443 default:
8444 return false;
8445 }
8446}
8447
8448class StmtUSEFinder : public RecursiveASTVisitor<StmtUSEFinder> {
8449 const Stmt *Target;
8450
8451public:
8452 bool VisitStmt(Stmt *S) { return S != Target; }
8453
8454 /// Returns true if the given statement is present in the given declaration.
8455 static bool isContained(const Stmt *Target, const Decl *D) {
8456 StmtUSEFinder Visitor;
8457 Visitor.Target = Target;
8458 return !Visitor.TraverseDecl(const_cast<Decl *>(D));
8459 }
8460};
8461
8462/// Traverses the AST and finds the last statement that used a given
8463/// declaration.
8464class LastDeclUSEFinder : public RecursiveASTVisitor<LastDeclUSEFinder> {
8465 const Decl *D;
8466
8467public:
8468 bool VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *DRE) {
8469 if (DRE->getDecl() == D)
8470 return false;
8471 return true;
8472 }
8473
8474 static const Stmt *findLastStmtThatUsesDecl(const Decl *D,
8475 const CompoundStmt *Scope) {
8476 LastDeclUSEFinder Visitor;
8477 Visitor.D = D;
8478 for (auto I = Scope->body_rbegin(), E = Scope->body_rend(); I != E; ++I) {
8479 const Stmt *S = *I;
8480 if (!Visitor.TraverseStmt(const_cast<Stmt *>(S)))
8481 return S;
8482 }
8483 return nullptr;
8484 }
8485};
8486
8487/// This class implements -Wunguarded-availability.
8488///
8489/// This is done with a traversal of the AST of a function that makes reference
8490/// to a partially available declaration. Whenever we encounter an \c if of the
8491/// form: \c if(@available(...)), we use the version from the condition to visit
8492/// the then statement.
8493class DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability
8494 : public RecursiveASTVisitor<DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability> {
8495 typedef RecursiveASTVisitor<DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability> Base;
8496
8497 Sema &SemaRef;
8498 Decl *Ctx;
8499
8500 /// Stack of potentially nested 'if (@available(...))'s.
8501 SmallVector<VersionTuple, 8> AvailabilityStack;
8502 SmallVector<const Stmt *, 16> StmtStack;
8503
8504 void DiagnoseDeclAvailability(NamedDecl *D, SourceRange Range,
8505 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ClassReceiver = nullptr);
8506
8507public:
8508 DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability(Sema &SemaRef, Decl *Ctx)
8509 : SemaRef(SemaRef), Ctx(Ctx) {
8510 AvailabilityStack.push_back(
8511 SemaRef.Context.getTargetInfo().getPlatformMinVersion());
8512 }
8513
8514 bool TraverseDecl(Decl *D) {
8515 // Avoid visiting nested functions to prevent duplicate warnings.
8516 if (!D || isa<FunctionDecl>(D))
8517 return true;
8518 return Base::TraverseDecl(D);
8519 }
8520
8521 bool TraverseStmt(Stmt *S) {
8522 if (!S)
8523 return true;
8524 StmtStack.push_back(S);
8525 bool Result = Base::TraverseStmt(S);
8526 StmtStack.pop_back();
8527 return Result;
8528 }
8529
8530 void IssueDiagnostics(Stmt *S) { TraverseStmt(S); }
8531
8532 bool TraverseIfStmt(IfStmt *If);
8533
8534 bool TraverseLambdaExpr(LambdaExpr *E) { return true; }
8535
8536 // for 'case X:' statements, don't bother looking at the 'X'; it can't lead
8537 // to any useful diagnostics.
8538 bool TraverseCaseStmt(CaseStmt *CS) { return TraverseStmt(CS->getSubStmt()); }
8539
8540 bool VisitObjCPropertyRefExpr(ObjCPropertyRefExpr *PRE) {
8541 if (PRE->isClassReceiver())
8542 DiagnoseDeclAvailability(PRE->getClassReceiver(), PRE->getReceiverLocation());
8543 return true;
8544 }
8545
8546 bool VisitObjCMessageExpr(ObjCMessageExpr *Msg) {
8547 if (ObjCMethodDecl *D = Msg->getMethodDecl()) {
8548 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = nullptr;
8549 QualType ReceiverTy = Msg->getClassReceiver();
8550 if (!ReceiverTy.isNull() && ReceiverTy->getAsObjCInterfaceType())
8551 ID = ReceiverTy->getAsObjCInterfaceType()->getInterface();
8552
8553 DiagnoseDeclAvailability(
8554 D, SourceRange(Msg->getSelectorStartLoc(), Msg->getEndLoc()), ID);
8555 }
8556 return true;
8557 }
8558
8559 bool VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *DRE) {
8560 DiagnoseDeclAvailability(DRE->getDecl(),
8561 SourceRange(DRE->getBeginLoc(), DRE->getEndLoc()));
8562 return true;
8563 }
8564
8565 bool VisitMemberExpr(MemberExpr *ME) {
8566 DiagnoseDeclAvailability(ME->getMemberDecl(),
8567 SourceRange(ME->getBeginLoc(), ME->getEndLoc()));
8568 return true;
8569 }
8570
8571 bool VisitObjCAvailabilityCheckExpr(ObjCAvailabilityCheckExpr *E) {
8572 SemaRef.Diag(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_at_available_unchecked_use)
8573 << (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().ObjC);
8574 return true;
8575 }
8576
8577 bool VisitTypeLoc(TypeLoc Ty);
8578};
8579
8580void DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability::DiagnoseDeclAvailability(
8581 NamedDecl *D, SourceRange Range, ObjCInterfaceDecl *ReceiverClass) {
8582 AvailabilityResult Result;
8583 const NamedDecl *OffendingDecl;
8584 std::tie(Result, OffendingDecl) =
8585 ShouldDiagnoseAvailabilityOfDecl(SemaRef, D, nullptr, ReceiverClass);
8586 if (Result != AR_Available) {
8587 // All other diagnostic kinds have already been handled in
8588 // DiagnoseAvailabilityOfDecl.
8589 if (Result != AR_NotYetIntroduced)
8590 return;
8591
8592 const AvailabilityAttr *AA =
8593 getAttrForPlatform(SemaRef.getASTContext(), OffendingDecl);
8594 VersionTuple Introduced = AA->getIntroduced();
8595
8596 if (AvailabilityStack.back() >= Introduced)
8597 return;
8598
8599 // If the context of this function is less available than D, we should not
8600 // emit a diagnostic.
8601 if (!ShouldDiagnoseAvailabilityInContext(SemaRef, Result, Introduced, Ctx,
8602 OffendingDecl))
8603 return;
8604
8605 // We would like to emit the diagnostic even if -Wunguarded-availability is
8606 // not specified for deployment targets >= to iOS 11 or equivalent or
8607 // for declarations that were introduced in iOS 11 (macOS 10.13, ...) or
8608 // later.
8609 unsigned DiagKind =
8610 shouldDiagnoseAvailabilityByDefault(
8611 SemaRef.Context,
8612 SemaRef.Context.getTargetInfo().getPlatformMinVersion(), Introduced)
8613 ? diag::warn_unguarded_availability_new
8614 : diag::warn_unguarded_availability;
8615
8616 std::string PlatformName = AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(
8617 SemaRef.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getPlatformName());
8618
8619 SemaRef.Diag(Range.getBegin(), DiagKind)
8620 << Range << D << PlatformName << Introduced.getAsString();
8621
8622 SemaRef.Diag(OffendingDecl->getLocation(),
8623 diag::note_partial_availability_specified_here)
8624 << OffendingDecl << PlatformName << Introduced.getAsString()
8625 << SemaRef.Context.getTargetInfo()
8626 .getPlatformMinVersion()
8627 .getAsString();
8628
8629 auto FixitDiag =
8630 SemaRef.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::note_unguarded_available_silence)
8631 << Range << D
8632 << (SemaRef.getLangOpts().ObjC ? /*@available*/ 0
8633 : /*__builtin_available*/ 1);
8634
8635 // Find the statement which should be enclosed in the if @available check.
8636 if (StmtStack.empty())
8637 return;
8638 const Stmt *StmtOfUse = StmtStack.back();
8639 const CompoundStmt *Scope = nullptr;
8640 for (const Stmt *S : llvm::reverse(StmtStack)) {
8641 if (const auto *CS = dyn_cast<CompoundStmt>(S)) {
8642 Scope = CS;
8643 break;
8644 }
8645 if (isBodyLikeChildStmt(StmtOfUse, S)) {
8646 // The declaration won't be seen outside of the statement, so we don't
8647 // have to wrap the uses of any declared variables in if (@available).
8648 // Therefore we can avoid setting Scope here.
8649 break;
8650 }
8651 StmtOfUse = S;
8652 }
8653 const Stmt *LastStmtOfUse = nullptr;
8654 if (isa<DeclStmt>(StmtOfUse) && Scope) {
8655 for (const Decl *D : cast<DeclStmt>(StmtOfUse)->decls()) {
8656 if (StmtUSEFinder::isContained(StmtStack.back(), D)) {
8657 LastStmtOfUse = LastDeclUSEFinder::findLastStmtThatUsesDecl(D, Scope);
8658 break;
8659 }
8660 }
8661 }
8662
8663 const SourceManager &SM = SemaRef.getSourceManager();
8664 SourceLocation IfInsertionLoc =
8665 SM.getExpansionLoc(StmtOfUse->getBeginLoc());
8666 SourceLocation StmtEndLoc =
8667 SM.getExpansionRange(
8668 (LastStmtOfUse ? LastStmtOfUse : StmtOfUse)->getEndLoc())
8669 .getEnd();
8670 if (SM.getFileID(IfInsertionLoc) != SM.getFileID(StmtEndLoc))
8671 return;
8672
8673 StringRef Indentation = Lexer::getIndentationForLine(IfInsertionLoc, SM);
8674 const char *ExtraIndentation = " ";
8675 std::string FixItString;
8676 llvm::raw_string_ostream FixItOS(FixItString);
8677 FixItOS << "if (" << (SemaRef.getLangOpts().ObjC ? "@available"
8678 : "__builtin_available")
8679 << "("
8680 << AvailabilityAttr::getPlatformNameSourceSpelling(
8681 SemaRef.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getPlatformName())
8682 << " " << Introduced.getAsString() << ", *)) {\n"
8683 << Indentation << ExtraIndentation;
8684 FixitDiag << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(IfInsertionLoc, FixItOS.str());
8685 SourceLocation ElseInsertionLoc = Lexer::findLocationAfterToken(
8686 StmtEndLoc, tok::semi, SM, SemaRef.getLangOpts(),
8687 /*SkipTrailingWhitespaceAndNewLine=*/false);
8688 if (ElseInsertionLoc.isInvalid())
8689 ElseInsertionLoc =
8690 Lexer::getLocForEndOfToken(StmtEndLoc, 0, SM, SemaRef.getLangOpts());
8691 FixItOS.str().clear();
8692 FixItOS << "\n"
8693 << Indentation << "} else {\n"
8694 << Indentation << ExtraIndentation
8695 << "// Fallback on earlier versions\n"
8696 << Indentation << "}";
8697 FixitDiag << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(ElseInsertionLoc, FixItOS.str());
8698 }
8699}
8700
8701bool DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability::VisitTypeLoc(TypeLoc Ty) {
8702 const Type *TyPtr = Ty.getTypePtr();
8703 SourceRange Range{Ty.getBeginLoc(), Ty.getEndLoc()};
8704
8705 if (Range.isInvalid())
8706 return true;
8707
8708 if (const auto *TT = dyn_cast<TagType>(TyPtr)) {
8709 TagDecl *TD = TT->getDecl();
8710 DiagnoseDeclAvailability(TD, Range);
8711
8712 } else if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(TyPtr)) {
8713 TypedefNameDecl *D = TD->getDecl();
8714 DiagnoseDeclAvailability(D, Range);
8715
8716 } else if (const auto *ObjCO = dyn_cast<ObjCObjectType>(TyPtr)) {
8717 if (NamedDecl *D = ObjCO->getInterface())
8718 DiagnoseDeclAvailability(D, Range);
8719 }
8720
8721 return true;
8722}
8723
8724bool DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability::TraverseIfStmt(IfStmt *If) {
8725 VersionTuple CondVersion;
8726 if (auto *E = dyn_cast<ObjCAvailabilityCheckExpr>(If->getCond())) {
8727 CondVersion = E->getVersion();
8728
8729 // If we're using the '*' case here or if this check is redundant, then we
8730 // use the enclosing version to check both branches.
8731 if (CondVersion.empty() || CondVersion <= AvailabilityStack.back())
8732 return TraverseStmt(If->getThen()) && TraverseStmt(If->getElse());
8733 } else {
8734 // This isn't an availability checking 'if', we can just continue.
8735 return Base::TraverseIfStmt(If);
8736 }
8737
8738 AvailabilityStack.push_back(CondVersion);
8739 bool ShouldContinue = TraverseStmt(If->getThen());
8740 AvailabilityStack.pop_back();
8741
8742 return ShouldContinue && TraverseStmt(If->getElse());
8743}
8744
8745} // end anonymous namespace
8746
8747void Sema::DiagnoseUnguardedAvailabilityViolations(Decl *D) {
8748 Stmt *Body = nullptr;
8749
8750 if (auto *FD = D->getAsFunction()) {
8751 // FIXME: We only examine the pattern decl for availability violations now,
8752 // but we should also examine instantiated templates.
8753 if (FD->isTemplateInstantiation())
8754 return;
8755
8756 Body = FD->getBody();
8757 } else if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
8758 Body = MD->getBody();
8759 else if (auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(D))
8760 Body = BD->getBody();
8761
8762 assert(Body && "Need a body here!");
8763
8764 DiagnoseUnguardedAvailability(*this, D).IssueDiagnostics(Body);
8765}
8766
8767void Sema::DiagnoseAvailabilityOfDecl(NamedDecl *D,
8768 ArrayRef<SourceLocation> Locs,
8769 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *UnknownObjCClass,
8770 bool ObjCPropertyAccess,
8771 bool AvoidPartialAvailabilityChecks,
8772 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ClassReceiver) {
8773 std::string Message;
8774 AvailabilityResult Result;
8775 const NamedDecl* OffendingDecl;
8776 // See if this declaration is unavailable, deprecated, or partial.
8777 std::tie(Result, OffendingDecl) =
8778 ShouldDiagnoseAvailabilityOfDecl(*this, D, &Message, ClassReceiver);
8779 if (Result == AR_Available)
8780 return;
8781
8782 if (Result == AR_NotYetIntroduced) {
8783 if (AvoidPartialAvailabilityChecks)
8784 return;
8785
8786 // We need to know the @available context in the current function to
8787 // diagnose this use, let DiagnoseUnguardedAvailabilityViolations do that
8788 // when we're done parsing the current function.
8789 if (getCurFunctionOrMethodDecl()) {
8790 getEnclosingFunction()->HasPotentialAvailabilityViolations = true;
8791 return;
8792 } else if (getCurBlock() || getCurLambda()) {
8793 getCurFunction()->HasPotentialAvailabilityViolations = true;
8794 return;
8795 }
8796 }
8797
8798 const ObjCPropertyDecl *ObjCPDecl = nullptr;
8799 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
8800 if (const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = MD->findPropertyDecl()) {
8801 AvailabilityResult PDeclResult = PD->getAvailability(nullptr);
8802 if (PDeclResult == Result)
8803 ObjCPDecl = PD;
8804 }
8805 }
8806
8807 EmitAvailabilityWarning(*this, Result, D, OffendingDecl, Message, Locs,
8808 UnknownObjCClass, ObjCPDecl, ObjCPropertyAccess);
8809}
